msgctxt "11_06P02"
msgid "When a Yugoslavian soldier dies for his country and his body cannot be found, his name is buried instead, spoken into an open grave by a relative."
msgstr "When a Yugoslavian soldier dies for his country and his body cannot be found, his name is buried instead, spoken into an open grave by a relative."

#: 11_06P03
msgctxt "11_06P03"
msgid "There is a monument in Malaya to a wild elephant."
msgstr "There is a monument in Malaya to a wild elephant."

#: 11_07N01
msgctxt "11_07N01"
msgid "Examine carefully. There is a story in that tomb resting with the Baron."
msgstr "Examine carefully. There is a story in that tomb resting with the Baron."

#: 11_07P01
msgctxt "11_07P01"
msgid "A doorbell?"
msgstr "A doorbell?"

#: 11_08N01
msgctxt "11_08N01"
msgid "Pay first!"
msgstr "Pay first!"

#: 11_08P01
msgctxt "11_08P01"
msgid "I could pay if the story were curious enough."
msgstr "I could pay if the story were curious enough."

#: 11_09N01
msgctxt "11_09N01"
msgid "Time is money. You have heard that said."
msgstr "Time is money. You have heard that said."

#: 11_09P01
msgctxt "11_09P01"
msgid "And an expensive one, I'll wager."
msgstr "And an expensive one, I'll wager."

#: 11_09P02
msgctxt "11_09P02"
msgid "Of course, I've just never seen it so well demonstrated."
msgstr "Of course, I've just never seen it so well demonstrated."

#: 11_10N01
msgctxt "11_10N01"
msgid "And I'm afraid I have neglected my work far too long."
msgstr "And I'm afraid I have neglected my work far too long."

#: 11_10P01
msgctxt "11_10P01"
msgid "I'm afraid I neglected to change my money."
msgstr "I'm afraid I neglected to change my money."

#: 11_11N01
msgctxt "11_11N01"
msgid "There is no need to pay, Mein Herr. I offer you a look for free."
msgstr "There is no need to pay, Mein Herr. I offer you a look for free."

#: 11_11N02
msgctxt "11_11N02"
msgid "There is only the one tomb in this graveyard, mein Herr."
msgstr "There is only the one tomb in this graveyard, mein Herr."

#: 11_11N03
msgctxt "11_11N03"
msgid "Do you know why I carry this key with me always?"
msgstr "Do you know why I carry this key with me always?"

#: 11_11P01
msgctxt "11_11P01"
msgid "I would pay handsomely to see it."
msgstr "I would pay handsomely to see it."

#: 11_11P02
msgctxt "11_11P02"
msgid "Wait a second, which tomb are we talking about?"
msgstr "Wait a second, which tomb are we talking about?"

#: 11_11P03
msgctxt "11_11P03"
msgid "Ah!"
msgstr "Ah!"

#: 11_12N01
msgctxt "11_12N01"
msgid "If there were a story, I would not offer it freely."
msgstr "If there were a story, I would not offer it freely."

#: 11_12P01
msgctxt "11_12P01"
msgid "Is there a story in it?"
msgstr "Is there a story in it?"

#: 11_13N01
msgctxt "11_13N01"
msgid "A man must eat."
msgstr "A man must eat."

#: 11_13P01
msgctxt "11_13P01"
msgid "I expect it will cost me to find out."
msgstr "I expect it will cost me to find out."

#: 11_13P02
msgctxt "11_13P02"
msgid "One of us will be able to at any rate."
msgstr "One of us will be able to at any rate."

#: 11_15P01
msgctxt "11_15P01"
msgid "Here's your money. Tell me your story about this tomb."
msgstr "Here's your money. Tell me your story about this tomb."

#: 11_16N01
msgctxt "11_16N01"
msgid "The old baron was terrified about being buried alive. The bell, it is a premature burial alarm. The undertaker built the coffin with a hole, for air, you see, and for the rope to enter. The end of the rope lies clasped tightly in the baron's cold, stiff hand. If the bell rings, I have this key to unlock the door at once."
msgstr "The old baron was terrified about being buried alive. The bell, it is a premature burial alarm. The undertaker built the coffin with a hole, for air, you see, and for the rope to enter. The end of the rope lies clasped tightly in the baron's cold, stiff hand. If the bell rings, I have this key to unlock the door at once."

#: 11_16N02
msgctxt "11_16N02"
msgid "The Baron was a very remarkable man."
msgstr "The Baron was a very remarkable man."

#: 11_16P02
msgctxt "11_16P02"
msgid "Do you believe he was buried alive and could still awaken after all these weeks?"
msgstr "Do you believe he was buried alive and could still awaken after all these weeks?"

#: 12_02N01
msgctxt "12_02N01"
msgid "Ja, mein Herr. You may explore the grounds and you may have access to any rooms downstairs where the old baron worked. That would be the sitting room and the billiards room. If the old baron left any notes, they would be most likely in one of those."
msgstr "Ja, mein Herr. You may explore the grounds and you may have access to any rooms downstairs where the old baron worked. That would be the sitting room and the billiards room. If the old baron left any notes, they would be most likely in one of those."

#: 12_02N02
msgctxt "12_02N02"
msgid "It was a high stakes poker game many years ago at the baron's club. It is said the money on the table for that single hand would rival the treasury of several small nations. The old baron drew the ace of spades to complete a royal flush and win the hand."
msgstr "It was a high stakes poker game many years ago at the baron's club. It is said the money on the table for that single hand would rival the treasury of several small nations. The old baron drew the ace of spades to complete a royal flush and win the hand."

#: 12_02N03
msgctxt "12_02N03"
msgid "Bitte, mein Herr."
msgstr "Bitte, mein Herr."

#: 12_02P01
msgctxt "12_02P01"
msgid "Did the Baron give you any instructions about me?"
msgstr "Did the Baron give you any instructions about me?"

#: 12_02P02
msgctxt "12_02P02"
msgid "How did the old baron come to build such an unusual castle?"
msgstr "How did the old baron come to build such an unusual castle?"

#: 12_02P03
msgctxt "12_02P03"
msgid "Thanks for helping out."
msgstr "Thanks for helping out."

#: 12_03N01
msgctxt "12_03N01"
msgid "It was built before my time. I do not know where it is, but I doubt it is in the upper reaches of the castle. I would have noticed."
msgstr "It was built before my time. I do not know where it is, but I doubt it is in the upper reaches of the castle. I would have noticed."

#: 12_03P01
msgctxt "12_03P01"
msgid "Your new master told me about a secret laboratory."
msgstr "Your new master told me about a secret laboratory."

#: 12_04N01
msgctxt "12_04N01"
msgid "It is difficult to forget the story if you live here."
msgstr "It is difficult to forget the story if you live here."

#: 12_04P01
msgctxt "12_04P01"
msgid "So he built this place to honor the occasion."
msgstr "So he built this place to honor the occasion."

#: 12_04P02
msgctxt "12_04P02"
msgid "I can imagine."
msgstr "I can imagine."

#: 13_02N01
msgctxt "13_02N01"
msgid "Hardly. Where my father's interests ran to the eccentric, mine are much more commonplace."
msgstr "Hardly. Where my father's interests ran to the eccentric, mine are much more commonplace."

#: 13_02N02
msgctxt "13_02N02"
msgid "Ah, but that's marvelous! You'll try to enter this tomb, then."
msgstr "Ah, but that's marvelous! You'll try to enter this tomb, then."

#: 13_02N03
msgctxt "13_02N03"
msgid "Very little, other than it's heating up, much as things are here in Europe."
msgstr "Very little, other than it's heating up, much as things are here in Europe."

#: 13_02P01
msgctxt "13_02P01"
msgid "Do you share your father's interest in the Orient?"
msgstr "Do you share your father's interest in the Orient?"

#: 13_02P02
msgctxt "13_02P02"
msgid "I'm tackling this last quest of your fathers on my own."
msgstr "I'm tackling this last quest of your fathers on my own."

#: 13_02P03
msgctxt "13_02P03"
msgid "What do you know of the current political situation in the Far East?"
msgstr "What do you know of the current political situation in the Far East?"

#: 13_02P04
msgctxt "13_02P04"
msgid "Would you be willing to part with that unusual zebra skin?"
msgstr "Would you be willing to part with that unusual zebra skin?"

#: 13_03N01
msgctxt "13_03N01"
msgid "Sport is my life!"
msgstr "Sport is my life!"

#: 13_03N02
msgctxt "13_03N02"
msgid "I admit it to you. I was captain of the fencing team at Oxford. I leave shortly for Stuttgart to try out the new Otto Union V-16, designed by Dr. Porsche."
msgstr "I admit it to you. I was captain of the fencing team at Oxford. I leave shortly for Stuttgart to try out the new Otto Union V-16, designed by Dr. Porsche."

#: 13_03N03
msgctxt "13_03N03"
msgid "Then I regret that we can have so little time together. Perhaps on my return."
msgstr "Then I regret that we can have so little time together. Perhaps on my return."

#: 13_03P01
msgctxt "13_03P01"
msgid "Tennis?"
msgstr "Tennis?"

#: 13_03P03
msgctxt "13_03P03"
msgid "Ah, the car with that ingenious push rod in place of overhead cams. I envy you. We have a lot in common. Until I dedicated myself to seeking out the curiosities of the world, I was a sportsman myself. Played some ball, covered many sports as well."
msgstr "Ah, the car with that ingenious push rod in place of overhead cams. I envy you. We have a lot in common. Until I dedicated myself to seeking out the curiosities of the world, I was a sportsman myself. Played some ball, covered many sports as well."

#: 13_03P04
msgctxt "13_03P04"
msgid "I'd enjoy that."
msgstr "I'd enjoy that."

#: 13_04N01
msgctxt "13_04N01"
msgid "It would certainly make for an interesting adventure. I look forward to reading about it."
msgstr "It would certainly make for an interesting adventure. I look forward to reading about it."

#: 13_04N02
msgctxt "13_04N02"
msgid "How could such an ancient artifact be dangerous today?"
msgstr "How could such an ancient artifact be dangerous today?"

#: 13_04N03
msgctxt "13_04N03"
msgid "My god!"
msgstr "My god!"

#: 13_04P01
msgctxt "13_04P01"
msgid "If I can."
msgstr "If I can."

#: 13_04P02
msgctxt "13_04P02"
msgid "It's more than a story for me, Baron. There may be unscrupulous forces at work to plunder the tomb of its most dangerous treasure, the Imperial Seal."
msgstr "It's more than a story for me, Baron. There may be unscrupulous forces at work to plunder the tomb of its most dangerous treasure, the Imperial Seal."

#: 13_04P03
msgctxt "13_04P03"
msgid "It could be used to unite the Eastern hordes behind a leader thirsting for power."
msgstr "It could be used to unite the Eastern hordes behind a leader thirsting for power."

#: 13_05N01
msgctxt "13_05N01"
msgid "To say the least."
msgstr "To say the least."

#: 13_05N02
msgctxt "13_05N02"
msgid "Mr. Ripley, the Nazis and their strutting counterparts in Italy and Japan are a plague that will soon spread like the Black Death itself. Unchecked, they will lead us one day into the unthinkable."
msgstr "Mr. Ripley, the Nazis and their strutting counterparts in Italy and Japan are a plague that will soon spread like the Black Death itself. Unchecked, they will lead us one day into the unthinkable."

#: 13_05N03
msgctxt "13_05N03"
msgid "The Second World War."
msgstr "The Second World War."

#: 13_05P01
msgctxt "13_05P01"
msgid "Hmm, it must be unnerving to have Hare Hitler in his brown shirts running Germany."
msgstr "Hmm, it must be unnerving to have Hare Hitler in his brown shirts running Germany."

#: 13_05P02
msgctxt "13_05P02"
msgid "I take it you're not in sympathy then with the Nazi cause."
msgstr "I take it you're not in sympathy then with the Nazi cause."

#: 13_06N01
msgctxt "13_06N01"
msgid "I'm sorry, Mr. Ripley. I'm afraid I can't. It was my father's express wish that this house and its unique accoutrement remain as you see them. And frankly, I've become quite used to them myself."
msgstr "I'm sorry, Mr. Ripley. I'm afraid I can't. It was my father's express wish that this house and its unique accoutrement remain as you see them. And frankly, I've become quite used to them myself."

#: 13_06P01
msgctxt "13_06P01"
msgid "It would make a fine addition to my auditorium in New York."
msgstr "It would make a fine addition to my auditorium in New York."

#: 13_06P02
msgctxt "13_06P02"
msgid "I understand."
msgstr "I understand."

#: 13_07N01
msgctxt "13_07N01"
msgid "Yes. Is that why you're here?"
msgstr "Yes. Is that why you're here?"

#: 13_07N02
msgctxt "13_07N02"
msgid "Nothing, I'm afraid. When did the first Emperor of China reign?"
msgstr "Nothing, I'm afraid. When did the first Emperor of China reign?"

#: 13_07N03
msgctxt "13_07N03"
msgid "And they had keys back then?"
msgstr "And they had keys back then?"

#: 13_07N04
msgctxt "13_07N04"
msgid "Then the key my father mentioned is a key to another key?"
msgstr "Then the key my father mentioned is a key to another key?"

#: 13_07N05
msgctxt "13_07N05"
msgid "It sounds incredibly complicated."
msgstr "It sounds incredibly complicated."

#: 13_07N06
msgctxt "13_07N06"
msgid "You have quite a task before you. How can I help?"
msgstr "You have quite a task before you. How can I help?"

#: 13_07P01
msgctxt "13_07P01"
msgid "The letter mentions a key to the tomb."
msgstr "The letter mentions a key to the tomb."

#: 13_07P02
msgctxt "13_07P02"
msgid "What can you tell me about it?"
msgstr "What can you tell me about it?"

#: 13_07P03
msgctxt "13_07P03"
msgid "In the third century B.C."
msgstr "In the third century B.C."

#: 13_07P04
msgctxt "13_07P04"
msgid "I suspect your father was referring to a key to decode a tablet kept at the Hall of Classics in Peiping. That tablet then holds some secret to opening the tomb."
msgstr "I suspect your father was referring to a key to decode a tablet kept at the Hall of Classics in Peiping. That tablet then holds some secret to opening the tomb."

#: 13_07P05
msgctxt "13_07P05"
msgid "Something like that."
msgstr "Something like that."

#: 13_07P06
msgctxt "13_07P06"
msgid "Liu planned it that way. The First Emperor's Seal of Office is somewhere in the tomb. Liu had a dream that only when everybody lived in peace and harmony and shared knowledge could certain ancient hieroglyphics on his tablet be translated. Once the time was right, the tomb could be opened and the power of the First Emperor's Seal of Office could be safely wielded once more."
msgstr "Liu planned it that way. The First Emperor's Seal of Office is somewhere in the tomb. Liu had a dream that only when everybody lived in peace and harmony and shared knowledge could certain ancient hieroglyphics on his tablet be translated. Once the time was right, the tomb could be opened and the power of the First Emperor's Seal of Office could be safely wielded once more."

#: 13_08N01
msgctxt "13_08N01"
msgid "Hmm... well, he didn't leave any scattered about that I've seen, but this is an unusual house in more ways than one."
msgstr "Hmm... well, he didn't leave any scattered about that I've seen, but this is an unusual house in more ways than one."

#: 13_08N02
msgctxt "13_08N02"
msgid "Oddly enough, on those rare occasions when he was at home, he spent most of his time in the billiards room. It was his sanctuary. He'd go there of an evening, puff one of his vile cigars, and work... or play."
msgstr "Oddly enough, on those rare occasions when he was at home, he spent most of his time in the billiards room. It was his sanctuary. He'd go there of an evening, puff one of his vile cigars, and work... or play."

#: 13_08P01
msgctxt "13_08P01"
msgid "Did your father leave behind any notes or Chinese artifacts?"
msgstr "Did your father leave behind any notes or Chinese artifacts?"

#: 13_08P02
msgctxt "13_08P02"
msgid "Did your father have a favorite room where he did most of his work?"
msgstr "Did your father have a favorite room where he did most of his work?"

#: 13_09N01
msgctxt "13_09N01"
msgid "Before I was born, my father gave himself for a number of years to the pursuit of esoteric science. Inventions for the improvement of mankind, the philosopher's stone, the secrets of alchemy, the usual."
msgstr "Before I was born, my father gave himself for a number of years to the pursuit of esoteric science. Inventions for the improvement of mankind, the philosopher's stone, the secrets of alchemy, the usual."

#: 13_09N02
msgctxt "13_09N02"
msgid "Unfortunately, no. Changing lead into gold would be a handy skill."
msgstr "Unfortunately, no. Changing lead into gold would be a handy skill."

#: 13_09N03
msgctxt "13_09N03"
msgid "To assist him in his research, he had a laboratory built somewhere in his house, and although as a boy I recall the occasional unpleasant chemical odor emanating from somewhere, I've never been able to locate it. He lost interest quite suddenly. Oh, it must be almost fifteen years ago now."
msgstr "To assist him in his research, he had a laboratory built somewhere in his house, and although as a boy I recall the occasional unpleasant chemical odor emanating from somewhere, I've never been able to locate it. He lost interest quite suddenly. Oh, it must be almost fifteen years ago now."

#: 13_09P01
msgctxt "13_09P01"
msgid "How do you mean?"
msgstr "How do you mean?"

#: 13_09P02
msgctxt "13_09P02"
msgid "He wasn't successful in his efforts."
msgstr "He wasn't successful in his efforts."

#: 13_09P03
msgctxt "13_09P03"
msgid "Don't I know it?"
msgstr "Don't I know it?"

#: 13_10N01
msgctxt "13_10N01"
msgid "I did, briefly, but despite all the scientists who tell us smoking improves our health, I found it reduced my wind. Not something one can afford on the tennis court or polo field. Perhaps I'm the unfortunate exception to the rule."
msgstr "I did, briefly, but despite all the scientists who tell us smoking improves our health, I found it reduced my wind. Not something one can afford on the tennis court or polo field. Perhaps I'm the unfortunate exception to the rule."

#: 13_10N02
msgctxt "13_10N02"
msgid "My father played everything. Games and puzzles were his passion."
msgstr "My father played everything. Games and puzzles were his passion."

#: 13_10P01
msgctxt "13_10P01"
msgid "I take it you don't smoke."
msgstr "I take it you don't smoke."

#: 13_10P02
msgctxt "13_10P02"
msgid "Your father played billiards?"
msgstr "Your father played billiards?"

#: 13_11N01
msgctxt "13_11N01"
msgid "Another thing we have in common."
msgstr "Another thing we have in common."

#: 13_11P01
msgctxt "13_11P01"
msgid "Actually, I don't smoke either."
msgstr "Actually, I don't smoke either."

#: 13_12N01
msgctxt "13_12N01"
msgid "Games are for children. What I love about sport is the physical endeavor, the strain of the muscles as much as the stretching of the mind, the action, if you will. The measure of physical exertion required to strike a stationary ball with a cue or to advance a backgammon pip is negligible."
msgstr "Games are for children. What I love about sport is the physical endeavor, the strain of the muscles as much as the stretching of the mind, the action, if you will. The measure of physical exertion required to strike a stationary ball with a cue or to advance a backgammon pip is negligible."

#: 13_12N02
msgctxt "13_12N02"
msgid "Hardly."
msgstr "Hardly."

#: 13_12P01
msgctxt "13_12P01"
msgid "But not yours? A sportsman like yourself?"
msgstr "But not yours? A sportsman like yourself?"

#: 13_12P02
msgctxt "13_12P02"
msgid "The thrill isn't there."
msgstr "The thrill isn't there."

#: 13_13N01
msgctxt "13_13N01"
msgid "My father has a small desk in the billiards room. You're free to explore that if you wish."
msgstr "My father has a small desk in the billiards room. You're free to explore that if you wish."

#: 13_13N02
msgctxt "13_13N02"
msgid "I should warn you about the billiards room."
msgstr "I should warn you about the billiards room."

#: 13_13N03
msgctxt "13_13N03"
msgid "Not haunted. Cursed. Say, this might be in your line of country. Have you heard of the Romanov Emerald?"
msgstr "Not haunted. Cursed. Say, this might be in your line of country. Have you heard of the Romanov Emerald?"

#: 13_13P02
msgctxt "13_13P02"
msgid "Thank you."
msgstr "Thank you."

#: 13_13P03
msgctxt "13_13P03"
msgid "Why is it haunted?"
msgstr "Why is it haunted?"

#: 13_14N01
msgctxt "13_14N01"
msgid "What do you know of its history?"
msgstr "What do you know of its history?"

#: 13_14N02
msgctxt "13_14N02"
msgid "Then you know it's history."
msgstr "Then you know it's history."

#: 13_14P01
msgctxt "13_14P01"
msgid "The Russian crown jewel? Of course!"
msgstr "The Russian crown jewel? Of course!"

#: 13_14P02
msgctxt "13_14P02"
msgid "Gosh, do you mean the emerald is in the billiards room?"
msgstr "Gosh, do you mean the emerald is in the billiards room?"

#: 13_15N01
msgctxt "13_15N01"
msgid "It came into my father's possession in 1920."
msgstr "It came into my father's possession in 1920."

#: 13_15N02
msgctxt "13_15N02"
msgid "The Emerald has hung like the sword of Damocles above this house for fifteen years. I believe it is, at least in part, responsible for my father's own illness and death."
msgstr "The Emerald has hung like the sword of Damocles above this house for fifteen years. I believe it is, at least in part, responsible for my father's own illness and death."

#: 13_15N03
msgctxt "13_15N03"
msgid "If I could, I would present it to you."
msgstr "If I could, I would present it to you."

#: 13_15N04
msgctxt "13_15N04"
msgid "Despite the fact its evil influence is most strongly felt there, the Emerald is not inside the Billiards Room, at least nowhere I can find."
msgstr "Despite the fact its evil influence is most strongly felt there, the Emerald is not inside the Billiards Room, at least nowhere I can find."

#: 13_15N05
msgctxt "13_15N05"
msgid "Mr. Ripley, with Hitler's power growing daily, Pomerania may need all its luck to survive. The sooner that stone is beyond our borders, the better."
msgstr "Mr. Ripley, with Hitler's power growing daily, Pomerania may need all its luck to survive. The sooner that stone is beyond our borders, the better."

#: 13_15N06
msgctxt "13_15N06"
msgid "Exact."
msgstr "Exact."

#: 13_15N07
msgctxt "13_15N07"
msgid "Our interesting discussion has already detained me far too long. I must not miss the train to Stuttgart. Feel free to search for this key, as you call it, but also, if you can, find the Emerald too. If you do find it, I would urge you to dispose of it as rapidly as you are able, else the curse attach itself to you."
msgstr "Our interesting discussion has already detained me far too long. I must not miss the train to Stuttgart. Feel free to search for this key, as you call it, but also, if you can, find the Emerald too. If you do find it, I would urge you to dispose of it as rapidly as you are able, else the curse attach itself to you."

#: 13_15P01
msgctxt "13_15P01"
msgid "It disappeared along with many of the other crown jewels during the revolution of 1917."
msgstr "It disappeared along with many of the other crown jewels during the revolution of 1917."

#: 13_15P02
msgctxt "13_15P02"
msgid "The emerald is supposed to be cursed. Any who possess it are doomed to bad luck, failure, even worse. Tsar Peter the second, his son Paul, Alexander the second, all were slain while it was in their possession. And of course, thanks to the Bolsheviks, Nicholas the second met with the same fate."
msgstr "The emerald is supposed to be cursed. Any who possess it are doomed to bad luck, failure, even worse. Tsar Peter the second, his son Paul, Alexander the second, all were slain while it was in their possession. And of course, thanks to the Bolsheviks, Nicholas the second met with the same fate."

#: 13_15P03
msgctxt "13_15P03"
msgid "A fabulous jewel like that would make a terrific addition to my auditorium. Unfortunately, my funds are rather limited at present."
msgstr "A fabulous jewel like that would make a terrific addition to my auditorium. Unfortunately, my funds are rather limited at present."

#: 13_15P04
msgctxt "13_15P04"
msgid "If you could..."
msgstr "If you could..."

#: 13_15P06
msgctxt "13_15P06"
msgid "You want me to have a look round for the jewel?"
msgstr "You want me to have a look round for the jewel?"

#: 13_20N01
msgctxt "13_20N01"
msgid "Fritz, I'm off!"
msgstr "Fritz, I'm off!"

#: 13_20P01
msgctxt "13_20P01"
msgid "Thank you, Baron, for your hospitality and your help. I'll do what I can."
msgstr "Thank you, Baron, for your hospitality and your help. I'll do what I can."

#: 14_02N01
msgctxt "14_02N01"
msgid "I am the Baron's gardener, not his secretary. I have duties of my own. The grounds are most extensive, as you can see. And I am only one man."
msgstr "I am the Baron's gardener, not his secretary. I have duties of my own. The grounds are most extensive, as you can see. And I am only one man."

#: 14_02N02
msgctxt "14_02N02"
msgid "Bye."
msgstr "Bye."

#: 14_02N03
msgctxt "14_02N03"
msgid "If I never see another Ace of Spades, I could die a happy man."
msgstr "If I never see another Ace of Spades, I could die a happy man."

#: 14_02N06
msgctxt "14_02N06"
msgid "Otto or Albert?"
msgstr "Otto or Albert?"

#: 14_02N07
msgctxt "14_02N07"
msgid "Yeah?"
msgstr "Yeah?"

#: 14_02N08
msgctxt "14_02N08"
msgid "TRIZER CASTLE"
msgstr "TRIZER CASTLE"

#: 14_02N09
msgctxt "14_02N09"
msgid "As you wish, my hair."
msgstr "As you wish, my hair."

#: 14_02P01
msgctxt "14_02P01"
msgid "I'm here to see Baron von Seltzer."
msgstr "I'm here to see Baron von Seltzer."

#: 14_02P02
msgctxt "14_02P02"
msgid "How do you come by the name Wolf?"
msgstr "How do you come by the name Wolf?"

#: 14_02P03
msgctxt "14_02P03"
msgid "The design of this castle is remarkable."
msgstr "The design of this castle is remarkable."

#: 14_02P04
msgctxt "14_02P04"
msgid "I have a letter signed by the 6th Baron von Seltsam."
msgstr "I have a letter signed by the 6th Baron von Seltsam."

#: 14_02P05
msgctxt "14_02P05"
msgid "I have a letter from the old baron."
msgstr "I have a letter from the old baron."

#: 14_02P06
msgctxt "14_02P06"
msgid "Where can I find the baron?"
msgstr "Where can I find the baron?"

#: 14_02P07
msgctxt "14_02P07"
msgid "I'm Robert Ripley."
msgstr "I'm Robert Ripley."

#: 14_02P08
msgctxt "14_02P08"
msgid "Is there anyone about who might assist me?"
msgstr "Is there anyone about who might assist me?"

#: 14_02P09
msgctxt "14_02P09"
msgid "Perhaps I'll talk to you later, if I may."
msgstr "Perhaps I'll talk to you later, if I may."

#: 14_03N01
msgctxt "14_03N01"
msgid "Yeah?"
msgstr "Yeah?"

#: 14_03P01
msgctxt "14_03P01"
msgid "Hello again."
msgstr "Hello again."

#: 14_04N01
msgctxt "14_04N01"
msgid "Oh, they are all polite in the castle. Their duties are light, while mine would tax a dozen younger men."
msgstr "Oh, they are all polite in the castle. Their duties are light, while mine would tax a dozen younger men."

#: 14_04P01
msgctxt "14_04P01"
msgid "I hope I'll be met with more civility there."
msgstr "I hope I'll be met with more civility there."

#: 14_05N01
msgctxt "14_05N01"
msgid "If there were a story, I would not offer it freely."
msgstr "If there were a story, I would not offer it freely."

#: 14_05P01
msgctxt "14_05P01"
msgid "Is there a story behind it?"
msgstr "Is there a story behind it?"

#: 14_06N01
msgctxt "14_06N01"
msgid "Pay first!"
msgstr "Pay first!"

#: 14_06P01
msgctxt "14_06P01"
msgid "I could pay if the story were curious enough."
msgstr "I could pay if the story were curious enough."

#: 14_07N01
msgctxt "14_07N01"
msgid "The grounds are most extensive, as you can see, and I am only one man. Our time is very precious."
msgstr "The grounds are most extensive, as you can see, and I am only one man. Our time is very precious."

#: 14_07P01
msgctxt "14_07P01"
msgid "You've led me down this garden path before."
msgstr "You've led me down this garden path before."

#: 14_07P02
msgctxt "14_07P02"
msgid "Wolf, my friend, you are a rogue."
msgstr "Wolf, my friend, you are a rogue."

#: 14_08N01
msgctxt "14_08N01"
msgid "Wolf is short for Wolfgang."
msgstr "Wolf is short for Wolfgang."

#: 14_08N02
msgctxt "14_08N02"
msgid "You are wrong, my dear. You are as a common tourist."
msgstr "You are wrong, my dear. You are as a common tourist."

#: 14_08P02
msgctxt "14_08P02"
msgid "That's it?"
msgstr "That's it?"

#: 14_09N01
msgctxt "14_09N01"
msgid "And your business, Mein Herr, is of no interest to me."
msgstr "And your business, Mein Herr, is of no interest to me."

#: 14_09P01
msgctxt "14_09P01"
msgid "My dear fellow, your business is your own, and of no interest to me."
msgstr "My dear fellow, your business is your own, and of no interest to me."

#: 14_14N01
msgctxt "14_14N01"
msgid "It was a high stakes poker game many years ago at the baron's club. It is said the money on the table for that single hand would rival the treasury of several smaller nations. The old baron drew the ace of spades to complete a royal flush and win the hand."
msgstr "It was a high stakes poker game many years ago at the baron's club. It is said the money on the table for that single hand would rival the treasury of several smaller nations. The old baron drew the ace of spades to complete a royal flush and win the hand."

#: 14_14N02
msgctxt "14_14N02"
msgid "Just so."
msgstr "Just so."

#: 14_14P02
msgctxt "14_14P02"
msgid "So he built this place to honor the occasion."
msgstr "So he built this place to honor the occasion."

#: 14_15N01
msgctxt "14_15N01"
msgid "Nein."
msgstr "Nein."

#: 14_15N02
msgctxt "14_15N02"
msgid "You do."
msgstr "You do."

#: 14_15P01
msgctxt "14_15P01"
msgid "You know the name?"
msgstr "You know the name?"

#: 14_15P03
msgctxt "14_15P03"
msgid "I demand to be taken to him at once."
msgstr "I demand to be taken to him at once."

#: 14_16N02
msgctxt "14_16N02"
msgid "There is no one else to take you to the old baron."
msgstr "There is no one else to take you to the old baron."

#: 14_16P01
msgctxt "14_16P01"
msgid "Um... Auto, I presume."
msgstr "Um... Auto, I presume."

#: 14_16P02
msgctxt "14_16P02"
msgid "Nonsense!"
msgstr "Nonsense!"

#: 14_18N01
msgctxt "14_18N01"
msgid "Otto?"
msgstr "Otto?"

#: 14_18P01
msgctxt "14_18P01"
msgid "I'm ready for you to take me to the baron."
msgstr "I'm ready for you to take me to the baron."

#: 14_18P02
msgctxt "14_18P02"
msgid "Yes, of course."
msgstr "Yes, of course."

#: 14_19N01
msgctxt "14_19N01"
msgid "This is me."
msgstr "This is me."

#: 14_20N01
msgctxt "14_20N01"
msgid "And I'm afraid I have neglected my work far too long."
msgstr "And I'm afraid I have neglected my work far too long."

#: 14_20P01
msgctxt "14_20P01"
msgid "I'm afraid I neglected to change my money."
msgstr "I'm afraid I neglected to change my money."

#: 14_22N01
msgctxt "14_22N01"
msgid "You were going to pay me!"
msgstr "You were going to pay me!"

#: 14_22N02
msgctxt "14_22N02"
msgid "As I said, pay first."
msgstr "As I said, pay first."

#: 14_22P01
msgctxt "14_22P01"
msgid "You were going to tell me how you came by the name Wolf."
msgstr "You were going to tell me how you came by the name Wolf."

#: 14_22P02
msgctxt "14_22P02"
msgid "As I said, I would pay if the story were curious enough."
msgstr "As I said, I would pay if the story were curious enough."

#: 14_22P03
msgctxt "14_22P03"
msgid "I was hoping you'd forget that part."
msgstr "I was hoping you'd forget that part."

#: 14_26N01
msgctxt "14_26N01"
msgid "We were discussing money."
msgstr "We were discussing money."

#: 14_26N04
msgctxt "14_26N04"
msgid "Just so."
msgstr "Just so."

#: 14_26P01
msgctxt "14_26P01"
msgid "We were discussing the design of this castle."
msgstr "We were discussing the design of this castle."

#: 14_26P04
msgctxt "14_26P04"
msgid "So he built this place to honor the occasion."
msgstr "So he built this place to honor the occasion."

#: 15_01N01
msgctxt "15_01N01"
msgid "Did I ask?"
msgstr "Did I ask?"

#: 15_01N02
msgctxt "15_01N02"
msgid "Not so lost anymore, it seems."
msgstr "Not so lost anymore, it seems."

#: 15_01N03
msgctxt "15_01N03"
msgid "I'm excavating this historical site."
msgstr "I'm excavating this historical site."

#: 15_01N06
msgctxt "15_01N06"
msgid "Why?"
msgstr "Why?"

#: 15_01P01
msgctxt "15_01P01"
msgid "Hello there, my name is Ripley."
msgstr "Hello there, my name is Ripley."

#: 15_01P02
msgctxt "15_01P02"
msgid "Is this the lost city of Mokomoche?"
msgstr "Is this the lost city of Mokomoche?"

#: 15_01P03
msgctxt "15_01P03"
msgid "Digging a well?"
msgstr "Digging a well?"

#: 15_01P04
msgctxt "15_01P04"
msgid "Can I buy your ladder?"
msgstr "Can I buy your ladder?"

#: 15_01P05
msgctxt "15_01P05"
msgid "Could I buy that shovel?"
msgstr "Could I buy that shovel?"

#: 15_01P06
msgctxt "15_01P06"
msgid "See here, my good man, come up out of there once."
msgstr "See here, my good man, come up out of there once."

#: 15_02N01
msgctxt "15_02N01"
msgid "I know what I'm doing."
msgstr "I know what I'm doing."

#: 15_02P01
msgctxt "15_02P01"
msgid "You could be destroying priceless artifacts with your careless digging."
msgstr "You could be destroying priceless artifacts with your careless digging."

#: 15_03N01
msgctxt "15_03N01"
msgid "My name is Menendez, if it's any concern of yours."
msgstr "My name is Menendez, if it's any concern of yours."

#: 15_03P01
msgctxt "15_03P01"
msgid "Who are you? And what are you doing here?"
msgstr "Who are you? And what are you doing here?"

#: 15_04N01
msgctxt "15_04N01"
msgid "What would you know about it?"
msgstr "What would you know about it?"

#: 15_04N02
msgctxt "15_04N02"
msgid "You know nothing. I carry one of the most respected names in all of archaeology, Menendez."
msgstr "You know nothing. I carry one of the most respected names in all of archaeology, Menendez."

#: 15_04P01
msgctxt "15_04P01"
msgid "Nonsense! It's plain to see you know nothing about archaeology."
msgstr "Nonsense! It's plain to see you know nothing about archaeology."

#: 15_04P02
msgctxt "15_04P02"
msgid "I know enough to see you haven't properly prepared the site. You're not uncovering it layer by layer. You have no plan whatsoever."
msgstr "I know enough to see you haven't properly prepared the site. You're not uncovering it layer by layer. You have no plan whatsoever."

#: 15_05N01
msgctxt "15_05N01"
msgid "Who did you say?"
msgstr "Who did you say?"

#: 15_05N02
msgctxt "15_05N02"
msgid "I may be by the time we are through talking."
msgstr "I may be by the time we are through talking."

#: 15_05P01
msgctxt "15_05P01"
msgid "You're Dr. Jorge Menendez?"
msgstr "You're Dr. Jorge Menendez?"

#: 15_05P02
msgctxt "15_05P02"
msgid "I thought you were dead."
msgstr "I thought you were dead."

#: 15_06N01
msgctxt "15_06N01"
msgid "Uh, no. I'm Emilio Menendez. Uncle Jorge was... my uncle. Twice removed. Now a third time removed, and for good."
msgstr "Uh, no. I'm Emilio Menendez. Uncle Jorge was... my uncle. Twice removed. Now a third time removed, and for good."

#: 15_06P01
msgctxt "15_06P01"
msgid "Professor of Archaeology at the National University of San Marcos in Lima. I thought you were dead."
msgstr "Professor of Archaeology at the National University of San Marcos in Lima. I thought you were dead."

#: 15_07N01
msgctxt "15_07N01"
msgid "Uh, no, I'm Emilio Menendez. You mean Uncle Jorge. He was my uncle, twice removed. Now a third time removed and for good."
msgstr "Uh, no, I'm Emilio Menendez. You mean Uncle Jorge. He was my uncle, twice removed. Now a third time removed and for good."

#: 15_07P01
msgctxt "15_07P01"
msgid "You can't be Professor Emerit Pre-Columbian Archaeology at the National University of San Marcos in Lima."
msgstr "You can't be Professor Emerit Pre-Columbian Archaeology at the National University of San Marcos in Lima."

#: 15_08N01
msgctxt "15_08N01"
msgid "Talking to some nosy busybody when I should be working."
msgstr "Talking to some nosy busybody when I should be working."

#: 15_08N02
msgctxt "15_08N02"
msgid "I would need his notes to do that. They were stolen. What are you suggesting?"
msgstr "I would need his notes to do that. They were stolen. What are you suggesting?"

#: 15_08N03
msgctxt "15_08N03"
msgid "No, I saw a little of him. We didn't talk much."
msgstr "No, I saw a little of him. We didn't talk much."

#: 15_08N04
msgctxt "15_08N04"
msgid "Yes, I have an excellently preserved shrunken head."
msgstr "Yes, I have an excellently preserved shrunken head."

#: 15_08P01
msgctxt "15_08P01"
msgid "What are you doing here, anyway?"
msgstr "What are you doing here, anyway?"

#: 15_08P02
msgctxt "15_08P02"
msgid "Are you following up on your uncle's research?"
msgstr "Are you following up on your uncle's research?"

#: 15_08P03
msgctxt "15_08P03"
msgid "Can you tell me anything about your uncle's death?"
msgstr "Can you tell me anything about your uncle's death?"

#: 15_08P04
msgctxt "15_08P04"
msgid "Have you dug up anything interesting?"
msgstr "Have you dug up anything interesting?"

#: 15_08P05
msgctxt "15_08P05"
msgid "Following up on your uncle's research?"
msgstr "Following up on your uncle's research?"

#: 15_10N01
msgctxt "15_10N01"
msgid "What do you mean by that?"
msgstr "What do you mean by that?"

#: 15_10P01
msgctxt "15_10P01"
msgid "No, I don't expect you would."
msgstr "No, I don't expect you would."

#: 15_11N01
msgctxt "15_11N01"
msgid "Like to buy it?"
msgstr "Like to buy it?"

#: 15_12N01
msgctxt "15_12N01"
msgid "750 Indy"
msgstr "750 Indy"

#: 15_12N02
msgctxt "15_12N02"
msgid "Should have thought of that before you trekked all the way up here, shouldn't you?"
msgstr "Should have thought of that before you trekked all the way up here, shouldn't you?"

#: 15_12P01
msgctxt "15_12P01"
msgid "If the price is right."
msgstr "If the price is right."

#: 15_12P02
msgctxt "15_12P02"
msgid "Yes, but I'll have to buy some Indy in Lima."
msgstr "Yes, but I'll have to buy some Indy in Lima."

#: 15_13N01
msgctxt "15_13N01"
msgid "You will be the first, senor."
msgstr "You will be the first, senor."

#: 15_13N02
msgctxt "15_13N02"
msgid "It is up to you, senor."
msgstr "It is up to you, senor."

#: 15_13P02
msgctxt "15_13P02"
msgid "I'll talk to you later."
msgstr "I'll talk to you later."

#: 15_14N01
msgctxt "15_14N01"
msgid "750 Indy"
msgstr "750 Indy"

#: 15_15N02
msgctxt "15_15N02"
msgid "Six hundred."
msgstr "Six hundred."

#: 15_15N03
msgctxt "15_15N03"
msgid "The Orinoco? They make these to order in the Amazon Basin. You pull out your wallet down there and three of their trader's neighbors will lose their heads that night. If there's a lot of money in your wallet, so may you. This head is old, very old."
msgstr "The Orinoco? They make these to order in the Amazon Basin. You pull out your wallet down there and three of their trader's neighbors will lose their heads that night. If there's a lot of money in your wallet, so may you. This head is old, very old."

#: 15_15P01
msgctxt "15_15P01"
msgid "Sold."
msgstr "Sold."

#: 15_15P02
msgctxt "15_15P02"
msgid "Will you take three hundred?"
msgstr "Will you take three hundred?"

#: 15_15P03
msgctxt "15_15P03"
msgid "No thanks, I've seen better on the Orinoco."
msgstr "No thanks, I've seen better on the Orinoco."

#: 15_16N01
msgctxt "15_16N01"
msgid "Be very careful what you suggest, senor."
msgstr "Be very careful what you suggest, senor."

#: 15_16P01
msgctxt "15_16P01"
msgid "This head looks suspiciously fresh."
msgstr "This head looks suspiciously fresh."

#: 15_16P02
msgctxt "15_16P02"
msgid "Thanks for the advice."
msgstr "Thanks for the advice."

#: 15_17N01
msgctxt "15_17N01"
msgid "400 Indy."
msgstr "400 Indy."

#: 15_17N02
msgctxt "15_17N02"
msgid "Ah, you're stealing the food from my children's mouths. 450!"
msgstr "Ah, you're stealing the food from my children's mouths. 450!"

#: 15_17P01
msgctxt "15_17P01"
msgid "Keep it!"
msgstr "Keep it!"

#: 15_17P02
msgctxt "15_17P02"
msgid "Four hundred."
msgstr "Four hundred."

#: 15_18P02
msgctxt "15_18P02"
msgid "Maybe some other time."
msgstr "Maybe some other time."

#: 15_19N01
msgctxt "15_19N01"
msgid "What have it?"
msgstr "What have it?"

#: 15_19N02
msgctxt "15_19N02"
msgid "Oh, and did you climb all the way up here for the air? My uncle and I were in the same profession, Senor. You think because they call him doctor he was any better than I?"
msgstr "Oh, and did you climb all the way up here for the air? My uncle and I were in the same profession, Senor. You think because they call him doctor he was any better than I?"

#: 15_19N03
msgctxt "15_19N03"
msgid "Be very careful what you say, senor. Grave robber, grave digger is much the same to me."
msgstr "Be very careful what you say, senor. Grave robber, grave digger is much the same to me."

#: 15_19P01
msgctxt "15_19P01"
msgid "I know your game, Menendez. You sell artifacts for profit."
msgstr "I know your game, Menendez. You sell artifacts for profit."

#: 15_19P02
msgctxt "15_19P02"
msgid "You're nothing but a common grave robber."
msgstr "You're nothing but a common grave robber."

#: 15_19P03
msgctxt "15_19P03"
msgid "He respected the past. You rape it."
msgstr "He respected the past. You rape it."

#: 15_21N01
msgctxt "15_21N01"
msgid "So I see."
msgstr "So I see."

#: 15_21P01
msgctxt "15_21P01"
msgid "I'm back!"
msgstr "I'm back!"

#: 15_22N01
msgctxt "15_22N01"
msgid "Yes, I have."
msgstr "Yes, I have."

#: 15_22P01
msgctxt "15_22P01"
msgid "Do you still have that shrunken head?"
msgstr "Do you still have that shrunken head?"

#: 15_22P04
msgctxt "15_22P04"
msgid "If you find anything interesting, let me know."
msgstr "If you find anything interesting, let me know."

#: 16_01N01
msgctxt "16_01N01"
msgid "Si senor, and where will you be traveling?"
msgstr "Si senor, and where will you be traveling?"

#: 16_01N02
msgctxt "16_01N02"
msgid "Muy bien, señor Ripley."
msgstr "Muy bien, señor Ripley."

#: 16_01N03
msgctxt "16_01N03"
msgid "How much inti will you like, senor?"
msgstr "How much inti will you like, senor?"

#: 16_01N08
msgctxt "16_01N08"
msgid "Vaya con Dios, senor."
msgstr "Vaya con Dios, senor."

#: 16_01P01
msgctxt "16_01P01"
msgid "I'd like to book passage."
msgstr "I'd like to book passage."

#: 16_01P02
msgctxt "16_01P02"
msgid "I'd like to send a parcel to New York."
msgstr "I'd like to send a parcel to New York."

#: 16_01P03
msgctxt "16_01P03"
msgid "I'd like to buy some of your local currency."
msgstr "I'd like to buy some of your local currency."

#: 16_01P04
msgctxt "16_01P04"
msgid "Sooo, we're back, we're like, I'm in the shit, this little broom again, but we're sike, it's the sii-"
msgstr "Sooo, we're back, we're like, I'm in the shit, this little broom again, but we're sike, it's the sii-"

#: 16_01P05
msgctxt "16_01P05"
msgid "I'd like to withdraw the money in my account."
msgstr "I'd like to withdraw the money in my account."

#: 16_01P06
msgctxt "16_01P06"
msgid "You have some interesting objects here."
msgstr "You have some interesting objects here."

#: 16_01P07
msgctxt "16_01P07"
msgid "I'm still intrigued by some of the interesting objects you have here."
msgstr "I'm still intrigued by some of the interesting objects you have here."

#: 16_01P08
msgctxt "16_01P08"
msgid "Thanks. Goodbye."
msgstr "Thanks. Goodbye."

#: 16_02N01
msgctxt "16_02N01"
msgid "Muy bien, señor. When will you be leaving?"
msgstr "Muy bien, señor. When will you be leaving?"

#: 16_02P05
msgctxt "16_02P05"
msgid "Easter Island."
msgstr "Easter Island."

#: 16_02P06
msgctxt "16_02P06"
msgid "Moka Moche."
msgstr "Moka Moche."

#: 16_03N01
msgctxt "16_03N01"
msgid "Easter Island, a popular destination."
msgstr "Easter Island, a popular destination."

#: 16_03N02
msgctxt "16_03N02"
msgid "See, senor, an expedition led by Dr. Tweltrees has just returned there after several weeks."
msgstr "See, senor, an expedition led by Dr. Tweltrees has just returned there after several weeks."

#: 16_03N03
msgctxt "16_03N03"
msgid "Also, two Oriental gentlemen were inquiring only yesterday."
msgstr "Also, two Oriental gentlemen were inquiring only yesterday."

#: 16_03N04
msgctxt "16_03N04"
msgid "Si senor, you know them?"
msgstr "Si senor, you know them?"

#: 16_03N05
msgctxt "16_03N05"
msgid "When will you be leaving for Easter Island, Senor Ripley?"
msgstr "When will you be leaving for Easter Island, Senor Ripley?"

#: 16_03P02
msgctxt "16_03P02"
msgid "Oh?"
msgstr "Oh?"

#: 16_03P03
msgctxt "16_03P03"
msgid "Twelve trees? Again? The doctor gets around as much as I do."
msgstr "Twelve trees? Again? The doctor gets around as much as I do."

#: 16_03P04
msgctxt "16_03P04"
msgid "One small, one big with glasses?"
msgstr "One small, one big with glasses?"

#: 16_03P05
msgctxt "16_03P05"
msgid "Hmm, they are not on my Christmas list. This is getting to be a very small world indeed."
msgstr "Hmm, they are not on my Christmas list. This is getting to be a very small world indeed."

#: 16_04N01
msgctxt "16_04N01"
msgid "Moka Moche. It is very difficult to reach. Most tourists go to Machu Picchu. They are not interested in nameless civilizations no one has heard of before."
msgstr "Moka Moche. It is very difficult to reach. Most tourists go to Machu Picchu. They are not interested in nameless civilizations no one has heard of before."

#: 16_04N02
msgctxt "16_04N02"
msgid "That would be Luis Arruno, señor. He was part of the expedition that discovered the lost city."
msgstr "That would be Luis Arruno, señor. He was part of the expedition that discovered the lost city."

#: 16_04N03
msgctxt "16_04N03"
msgid "No problema, although he will not enter the city."
msgstr "No problema, although he will not enter the city."

#: 16_04N04
msgctxt "16_04N04"
msgid "Ghosts, senor. Why else? When will you be leaving?"
msgstr "Ghosts, senor. Why else? When will you be leaving?"

#: 16_04P02
msgctxt "16_04P02"
msgid "I'm told there is a guide who knows mocha mocha. Luis something."
msgstr "I'm told there is a guide who knows mocha mocha. Luis something."

#: 16_04P03
msgctxt "16_04P03"
msgid "Could you arrange for him to guide me there?"
msgstr "Could you arrange for him to guide me there?"

#: 16_04P04
msgctxt "16_04P04"
msgid "Why?"
msgstr "Why?"

#: 16_05N01
msgctxt "16_05N01"
msgid "It will go out on tomorrow's plane."
msgstr "It will go out on tomorrow's plane."

#: 16_06N01
msgctxt "16_06N01"
msgid "Pardon, senor Ripley, your account is empty."
msgstr "Pardon, senor Ripley, your account is empty."

#: 16_07N01
msgctxt "16_07N01"
msgid "Certainly, Senor Ripley. Please sign here."
msgstr "Certainly, Senor Ripley. Please sign here."

#: 16_08P01
msgctxt "16_08P01"
msgid "NOW!"
msgstr "NOW!"

#: 16_08P02
msgctxt "16_08P02"
msgid "I'll let you know."
msgstr "I'll let you know."

#: 16_09N01
msgctxt "16_09N01"
msgid "Very good. Have a good trip, senor."
msgstr "Very good. Have a good trip, senor."

#: 16_10N01
msgctxt "16_10N01"
msgid "Perdonome, senor Ripley. Your account is empty. Will you be paying in cash?"
msgstr "Perdonome, senor Ripley. Your account is empty. Will you be paying in cash?"

#: 16_10N02
msgctxt "16_10N02"
msgid "Mr. Ripley, lo siento. As I tell you, your account is empty. Would you prefer to pay in cash?"
msgstr "Mr. Ripley, lo siento. As I tell you, your account is empty. Would you prefer to pay in cash?"

#: 16_11N01
msgctxt "16_11N01"
msgid "Very good. Have a good trip, senor."
msgstr "Very good. Have a good trip, senor."

#: 16_11P01
msgctxt "16_11P01"
msgid "Of course, of course!"
msgstr "Of course, of course!"

#: 16_12P01
msgctxt "16_12P01"
msgid "I'd better change my money. I'll need escudos on Easter Island."
msgstr "I'd better change my money. I'll need escudos on Easter Island."

#: 16_13N01
msgctxt "16_13N01"
msgid "The mechanism has been with my family for many years. My grandfather had it custom made by one of the finest clockmakers in Switzerland. The original case fell to pieces long ago. I found that coral to replace it."
msgstr "The mechanism has been with my family for many years. My grandfather had it custom made by one of the finest clockmakers in Switzerland. The original case fell to pieces long ago. I found that coral to replace it."

#: 16_13N03
msgctxt "16_13N03"
msgid "Well, the clock is old. The coral is not. I picked it up during a visit to... the seashore."
msgstr "Well, the clock is old. The coral is not. I picked it up during a visit to... the seashore."

#: 16_13N04
msgctxt "16_13N04"
msgid "The ancient city of the snake, senor."
msgstr "The ancient city of the snake, senor."

#: 16_13N06
msgctxt "16_13N06"
msgid "It is my son, Senor Ripley. Before he became ill, we would travel to the sea to watch the funny little birds. Now he must stay in bed. So I bring them to him. Our house is small and there are puffins everywhere, so some I keep here for decoration."
msgstr "It is my son, Senor Ripley. Before he became ill, we would travel to the sea to watch the funny little birds. Now he must stay in bed. So I bring them to him. Our house is small and there are puffins everywhere, so some I keep here for decoration."

#: 16_13N07
msgctxt "16_13N07"
msgid "There is some improvement, senor."
msgstr "There is some improvement, senor."

#: 16_13P01
msgctxt "16_13P01"
msgid "This clock, may I ask where it came from?"
msgstr "This clock, may I ask where it came from?"

#: 16_13P02
msgctxt "16_13P02"
msgid "Where did you say the clock came from?"
msgstr "Where did you say the clock came from?"

#: 16_13P03
msgctxt "16_13P03"
msgid "I'm intrigued by that old clock there."
msgstr "I'm intrigued by that old clock there."

#: 16_13P04
msgctxt "16_13P04"
msgid "Where was that stele found?"
msgstr "Where was that stele found?"

#: 16_13P05
msgctxt "16_13P05"
msgid "Where did you say that stele was found?"
msgstr "Where did you say that stele was found?"

#: 16_13P06
msgctxt "16_13P06"
msgid "Someone here must like puffins."
msgstr "Someone here must like puffins."

#: 16_13P07
msgctxt "16_13P07"
msgid "How is your son, Matteo?"
msgstr "How is your son, Matteo?"

#: 16_14N01
msgctxt "16_14N01"
msgid "Sí, señor. My grandfather used to say, people are always watching the clock. He wanted one that would look back."
msgstr "Sí, señor. My grandfather used to say, people are always watching the clock. He wanted one that would look back."

#: 16_14P01
msgctxt "16_14P01"
msgid "Was the original also shaped like that?"
msgstr "Was the original also shaped like that?"

#: 16_15N01
msgctxt "16_15N01"
msgid "It is in God's hands."
msgstr "It is in God's hands."

#: 16_15P01
msgctxt "16_15P01"
msgid "Oh, I'm sorry to hear he's sick. What do the doctors say?"
msgstr "Oh, I'm sorry to hear he's sick. What do the doctors say?"

#: 16_16N02
msgctxt "16_16N02"
msgid "Our house is small, and there are puffins everywhere, so some I keep here for decoration."
msgstr "Our house is small, and there are puffins everywhere, so some I keep here for decoration."

#: 16_16P01
msgctxt "16_16P01"
msgid "An unhappy visit?"
msgstr "An unhappy visit?"

#: 16_16P02
msgctxt "16_16P02"
msgid "Ah, the puffins."
msgstr "Ah, the puffins."

#: 16_16P03
msgctxt "16_16P03"
msgid "I'm sorry to hear your son sick. What did the doctors say?"
msgstr "I'm sorry to hear your son sick. What did the doctors say?"

#: 16_17N01
msgctxt "16_17N01"
msgid "They are his most treasured possessions."
msgstr "They are his most treasured possessions."

#: 16_17P01
msgctxt "16_17P01"
msgid "Ah, your son. I remember you said he was ill. How much he enjoyed those visits to the seashore, and the puffins."
msgstr "Ah, your son. I remember you said he was ill. How much he enjoyed those visits to the seashore, and the puffins."

#: 16_18N01
msgctxt "16_18N01"
msgid "No, Senor Ripley. I am sorry, but it is a family heirloom."
msgstr "No, Senor Ripley. I am sorry, but it is a family heirloom."

#: 16_18N02
msgctxt "16_18N02"
msgid "Lo siento mucho, señor, but where would I find such an unusual shape to replace it?"
msgstr "Lo siento mucho, señor, but where would I find such an unusual shape to replace it?"

#: 16_18P01
msgctxt "16_18P01"
msgid "Could I purchase your clock?"
msgstr "Could I purchase your clock?"

#: 16_18P02
msgctxt "16_18P02"
msgid "How about just the choral, then?"
msgstr "How about just the choral, then?"

#: 16_19P01
msgctxt "16_19P01"
msgid "I'll keep my eyes open for something that might do just as well."
msgstr "I'll keep my eyes open for something that might do just as well."

#: 16_20P01
msgctxt "16_20P01"
msgid "I recall seeing something on Easter Island at my work. Funny, now that I come to think of it, it was shaped like a puffin as well. Now, where was it?"
msgstr "I recall seeing something on Easter Island at my work. Funny, now that I come to think of it, it was shaped like a puffin as well. Now, where was it?"

#: 16_21N01
msgctxt "16_21N01"
msgid "No problem, senor. When will you be leaving?"
msgstr "No problem, senor. When will you be leaving?"

#: 16_22N01
msgctxt "16_22N01"
msgid "They are his most treasured possessions."
msgstr "They are his most treasured possessions."

#: 16_22N02
msgctxt "16_22N02"
msgid "Gracias, senor. It is in God's hands."
msgstr "Gracias, senor. It is in God's hands."

#: 16_22P01
msgctxt "16_22P01"
msgid "I'm glad to hear it. I remember you said how much you enjoyed those visits to the seashore, and the puffins."
msgstr "I'm glad to hear it. I remember you said how much you enjoyed those visits to the seashore, and the puffins."

#: 16_22P02
msgctxt "16_22P02"
msgid "I hope he recovers soon."
msgstr "I hope he recovers soon."

#: 16_24P01
msgctxt "16_24P01"
msgid "I'm ready to leave now."
msgstr "I'm ready to leave now."

#: 16_27P01
msgctxt "16_27P01"
msgid "Change my mind."
msgstr "Change my mind."

#: 17_01N01
msgctxt "17_01N01"
msgid "Would you hand me my shirt, please?"
msgstr "Would you hand me my shirt, please?"

#: 17_01N02
msgctxt "17_01N02"
msgid "Yes, would you hand me my shirt, please?"
msgstr "Yes, would you hand me my shirt, please?"

#: 17_01N03
msgctxt "17_01N03"
msgid "How dare you sneak up on me like that?"
msgstr "How dare you sneak up on me like that?"

#: 17_01N04
msgctxt "17_01N04"
msgid "Many of the natives dress far more casually."
msgstr "Many of the natives dress far more casually."

#: 17_01N05
msgctxt "17_01N05"
msgid "At a disadvantage, would you hand me my shirt, please?"
msgstr "At a disadvantage, would you hand me my shirt, please?"

#: 17_01P01
msgctxt "17_01P01"
msgid "I am looking for Dr. Twelve Trees."
msgstr "I am looking for Dr. Twelve Trees."

#: 17_01P02
msgctxt "17_01P02"
msgid "Are you part of the Twelve Trees Expedition?"
msgstr "Are you part of the Twelve Trees Expedition?"

#: 17_01P03
msgctxt "17_01P03"
msgid "Whew! That's the most attractive pair of shoulders I've ever seen on an archaeologist."
msgstr "Whew! That's the most attractive pair of shoulders I've ever seen on an archaeologist."

#: 17_01P04
msgctxt "17_01P04"
msgid "Is that the standard kit these days for archaeologists?"
msgstr "Is that the standard kit these days for archaeologists?"

#: 17_01P05
msgctxt "17_01P05"
msgid "I'm Robert Ripley and you are..."
msgstr "I'm Robert Ripley and you are..."

#: 17_02P01
msgctxt "17_02P01"
msgid "It was unintentional, madam. Miss, I assure you."
msgstr "It was unintentional, madam. Miss, I assure you."

#: 17_03P01
msgctxt "17_03P01"
msgid "I'm liking Easter Island already."
msgstr "I'm liking Easter Island already."

#: 17_04N02
msgctxt "17_04N02"
msgid "Give me the shirt."
msgstr "Give me the shirt."

#: 17_04N03
msgctxt "17_04N03"
msgid "Swell."
msgstr "Swell."

#: 17_04N04
msgctxt "17_04N04"
msgid "May I help you?"
msgstr "May I help you?"

#: 17_04N05
msgctxt "17_04N05"
msgid "You were leering at Dr. Twelve Trees a moment ago."
msgstr "You were leering at Dr. Twelve Trees a moment ago."

#: 17_04N06
msgctxt "17_04N06"
msgid "I know who you are, Mr. Ripley. I recognized you."
msgstr "I know who you are, Mr. Ripley. I recognized you."

#: 17_04N07
msgctxt "17_04N07"
msgid "As far as I'm concerned, we share no common interests. I'm a scientist."
msgstr "As far as I'm concerned, we share no common interests. I'm a scientist."

#: 17_04N08
msgctxt "17_04N08"
msgid "You're in..."
msgstr "You're in..."

#: 17_04N09
msgctxt "17_04N09"
msgid "Was there something else?"
msgstr "Was there something else?"

#: 17_04N99
msgctxt "17_04N99"
msgid "Showbiz."
msgstr "Showbiz."

#: 17_04P01
msgctxt "17_04P01"
msgid "Delighted!"
msgstr "Delighted!"

#: 17_04P02
msgctxt "17_04P02"
msgid "Uh, terribly sorry. Just be a moment."
msgstr "Uh, terribly sorry. Just be a moment."

#: 17_04P06
msgctxt "17_04P06"
msgid "Oh, really? That is to say, I wasn't leering. I'm Robert Ripley. I believe we share a common interest. I had some questions."
msgstr "Oh, really? That is to say, I wasn't leering. I'm Robert Ripley. I believe we share a common interest. I had some questions."

#: 17_04P07
msgctxt "17_04P07"
msgid "Ah!"
msgstr "Ah!"

#: 17_05N01
msgctxt "17_05N01"
msgid "Master who?"
msgstr "Master who?"

#: 17_05N02
msgctxt "17_05N02"
msgid "I was in thieves for a while. What stopped you?"
msgstr "I was in thieves for a while. What stopped you?"

#: 17_05N03
msgctxt "17_05N03"
msgid "It's no secret."
msgstr "It's no secret."

#: 17_05N04
msgctxt "17_05N04"
msgid "Are you trying to be offensive?"
msgstr "Are you trying to be offensive?"

#: 17_05N05
msgctxt "17_05N05"
msgid "Now, if you have to ask, I have no answer for you."
msgstr "Now, if you have to ask, I have no answer for you."

#: 17_05N06
msgctxt "17_05N06"
msgid "Me too."
msgstr "Me too."

#: 17_05N07
msgctxt "17_05N07"
msgid "The woman who prays?"
msgstr "The woman who prays?"

#: 17_05P01
msgctxt "17_05P01"
msgid "We're both interested in Master Lu."
msgstr "We're both interested in Master Lu."

#: 17_05P02
msgctxt "17_05P02"
msgid "I tried to contact you in Egypt."
msgstr "I tried to contact you in Egypt."

#: 17_05P03
msgctxt "17_05P03"
msgid "I understand you were in Peiping recently."
msgstr "I understand you were in Peiping recently."

#: 17_05P04
msgctxt "17_05P04"
msgid "We both try to expand the world's knowledge."
msgstr "We both try to expand the world's knowledge."

#: 17_05P05
msgctxt "17_05P05"
msgid "What's wrong with showbiz?"
msgstr "What's wrong with showbiz?"

#: 17_05P06
msgctxt "17_05P06"
msgid "Sorry I bothered you."
msgstr "Sorry I bothered you."

#: 17_05P07
msgctxt "17_05P07"
msgid "Who is that old woman at the cove north of here?"
msgstr "Who is that old woman at the cove north of here?"

#: 17_06N01
msgctxt "17_06N01"
msgid "Hardly. I search for facts. You settle for the sensational."
msgstr "Hardly. I search for facts. You settle for the sensational."

#: 17_06N02
msgctxt "17_06N02"
msgid "Please."
msgstr "Please."

#: 17_06N03
msgctxt "17_06N03"
msgid "What do you want, then?"
msgstr "What do you want, then?"

#: 17_06P01
msgctxt "17_06P01"
msgid "You don't find the comparison flattering, I take it."
msgstr "You don't find the comparison flattering, I take it."

#: 17_06P02
msgctxt "17_06P02"
msgid "All of my features are carefully documented."
msgstr "All of my features are carefully documented."

#: 17_06P03
msgctxt "17_06P03"
msgid "Doctor, I don't want to quarrel with you."
msgstr "Doctor, I don't want to quarrel with you."

#: 17_07N01
msgctxt "17_07N01"
msgid "Of what possible interest could an ancient sage have to the man who brought us an hourglass filled with jelly beans?"
msgstr "Of what possible interest could an ancient sage have to the man who brought us an hourglass filled with jelly beans?"

#: 17_07N02
msgctxt "17_07N02"
msgid "Answer my question. Maybe then I'll answer yours."
msgstr "Answer my question. Maybe then I'll answer yours."

#: 17_07P01
msgctxt "17_07P01"
msgid "Don't fence with me, doctor. You're supposed to be the leading Western authority on the man."
msgstr "Don't fence with me, doctor. You're supposed to be the leading Western authority on the man."

#: 17_07P02
msgctxt "17_07P02"
msgid "Ah, then you've been to the auditorium."
msgstr "Ah, then you've been to the auditorium."

#: 17_08N01
msgctxt "17_08N01"
msgid "Master who?"
msgstr "Master who?"

#: 17_08P01
msgctxt "17_08P01"
msgid "On the trail of Master Lu?"
msgstr "On the trail of Master Lu?"

#: 17_09N01
msgctxt "17_09N01"
msgid "What? But why would anyone..."
msgstr "What? But why would anyone..."

#: 17_09N02
msgctxt "17_09N02"
msgid "I'm a scientist, not a thief."
msgstr "I'm a scientist, not a thief."

#: 17_09N03
msgctxt "17_09N03"
msgid "Why are you here, Mr. Ripley?"
msgstr "Why are you here, Mr. Ripley?"

#: 17_09P01
msgctxt "17_09P01"
msgid "Right after you visited the Hall of Classics, an attempt was made to steal a certain tablet of Master Luz."
msgstr "Right after you visited the Hall of Classics, an attempt was made to steal a certain tablet of Master Luz."

#: 17_09P02
msgctxt "17_09P02"
msgid "Then you don't know anything about it?"
msgstr "Then you don't know anything about it?"

#: 17_09P03
msgctxt "17_09P03"
msgid "Someone might say archaeologists steal the past all the time. The British Museum is full of antiquities removed from their proper resting sites by scientists."
msgstr "Someone might say archaeologists steal the past all the time. The British Museum is full of antiquities removed from their proper resting sites by scientists."

#: 17_11N01
msgctxt "17_11N01"
msgid "Then, why do it, Mr. Ripley?"
msgstr "Then, why do it, Mr. Ripley?"

#: 17_11N02
msgctxt "17_11N02"
msgid "You already are. Please, come to the point."
msgstr "You already are. Please, come to the point."

#: 17_11P01
msgctxt "17_11P01"
msgid "Sorry to trouble you again."
msgstr "Sorry to trouble you again."

#: 17_11P02
msgctxt "17_11P02"
msgid "I do need to talk to you."
msgstr "I do need to talk to you."

#: 17_12N01
msgctxt "17_12N01"
msgid "RongoRongo tablets."
msgstr "RongoRongo tablets."

#: 17_12N02
msgctxt "17_12N02"
msgid "Yes, this is a fragile archaeological dig site. Please keep your hands and feet off."
msgstr "Yes, this is a fragile archaeological dig site. Please keep your hands and feet off."

#: 17_12P01
msgctxt "17_12P01"
msgid "May I ask why you went to see Master Lu's tablet at the Hall of Classics?"
msgstr "May I ask why you went to see Master Lu's tablet at the Hall of Classics?"

#: 17_12P02
msgctxt "17_12P02"
msgid "Mind if I look around?"
msgstr "Mind if I look around?"

#: 17_13N01
msgctxt "17_13N01"
msgid "RongoRongo tablets."
msgstr "RongoRongo tablets."

#: 17_13P01
msgctxt "17_13P01"
msgid "May I ask why you recently visited the Hall of Classics?"
msgstr "May I ask why you recently visited the Hall of Classics?"

#: 17_14N01
msgctxt "17_14N01"
msgid "There are sacred wood tablets found on this island. They've never been deciphered. I hope Lou's tablet might provide a clue to their translation."
msgstr "There are sacred wood tablets found on this island. They've never been deciphered. I hope Lou's tablet might provide a clue to their translation."

#: 17_14N02
msgctxt "17_14N02"
msgid "There is definitely RongoRongo script on Lou's tablet, but it's intermingled with others. A translation is almost impossible. The islanders hid or buried most of their tablets generations ago. I was hoping to find some at the foot of this altar."
msgstr "There is definitely RongoRongo script on Lou's tablet, but it's intermingled with others. A translation is almost impossible. The islanders hid or buried most of their tablets generations ago. I was hoping to find some at the foot of this altar."

#: 17_14N03
msgctxt "17_14N03"
msgid "Mr. Ripley, you're a fast talker, I'll give you that. But I want some answers from you."
msgstr "Mr. Ripley, you're a fast talker, I'll give you that. But I want some answers from you."

#: 17_14P01
msgctxt "17_14P01"
msgid "Take two and heartburn bubbles away."
msgstr "Take two and heartburn bubbles away."

#: 17_14P02
msgctxt "17_14P02"
msgid "And did it?"
msgstr "And did it?"

#: 17_14P03
msgctxt "17_14P03"
msgid "I was wondering..."
msgstr "I was wondering..."

#: 17_16N04
msgctxt "17_16N04"
msgid "I'll count the minutes."
msgstr "I'll count the minutes."

#: 17_16P01
msgctxt "17_16P01"
msgid "I'm not sure I can trust you."
msgstr "I'm not sure I can trust you."

#: 17_16P03
msgctxt "17_16P03"
msgid "An attempt was made to steal Master Lu's tablet."
msgstr "An attempt was made to steal Master Lu's tablet."

#: 17_16P04
msgctxt "17_16P04"
msgid "Maybe we should talk later."
msgstr "Maybe we should talk later."

#: 17_17N02
msgctxt "17_17N02"
msgid "Mr. Ripley, it wasn't necessary to track me halfway across the world to criticize my profession. Next time, write a letter."
msgstr "Mr. Ripley, it wasn't necessary to track me halfway across the world to criticize my profession. Next time, write a letter."

#: 17_17P01
msgctxt "17_17P01"
msgid "Right after you saw it."
msgstr "Right after you saw it."

#: 17_17P03
msgctxt "17_17P03"
msgid "I need your help, but..."
msgstr "I need your help, but..."

#: 17_19N01
msgctxt "17_19N01"
msgid "It has nothing to do with me."
msgstr "It has nothing to do with me."

#: 17_19P01
msgctxt "17_19P01"
msgid "I was intercepted by two cutthroats who almost made an end of me in the desert."
msgstr "I was intercepted by two cutthroats who almost made an end of me in the desert."

#: 17_19P02
msgctxt "17_19P02"
msgid "I wish I could be sure of that."
msgstr "I wish I could be sure of that."

#: 17_20N01
msgctxt "17_20N01"
msgid "I can tell."
msgstr "I can tell."

#: 17_20N02
msgctxt "17_20N02"
msgid "How do I know you're not?"
msgstr "How do I know you're not?"

#: 17_20P02
msgctxt "17_20P02"
msgid "How do I know you're not after the secrets of Master Lu for some sinister purpose?"
msgstr "How do I know you're not after the secrets of Master Lu for some sinister purpose?"

#: 17_21N01
msgctxt "17_21N01"
msgid "You're right. We do have something in common."
msgstr "You're right. We do have something in common."

#: 17_22N01
msgctxt "17_22N01"
msgid "Oh."
msgstr "Oh."

#: 17_22P01
msgctxt "17_22P01"
msgid "There's something you should know."
msgstr "There's something you should know."

#: 17_23N01
msgctxt "17_23N01"
msgid "Back so soon!"
msgstr "Back so soon!"

#: 17_23P01
msgctxt "17_23P01"
msgid "Did you miss me?"
msgstr "Did you miss me?"

#: 17_24N01
msgctxt "17_24N01"
msgid "Really? I barely noticed you were gone."
msgstr "Really? I barely noticed you were gone."

#: 17_24P01
msgctxt "17_24P01"
msgid "Soon, I've been away for weeks."
msgstr "Soon, I've been away for weeks."

#: 17_25N01
msgctxt "17_25N01"
msgid "Sounds as if you better decide whether you can trust me or not."
msgstr "Sounds as if you better decide whether you can trust me or not."

#: 17_26N01
msgctxt "17_26N01"
msgid "You made the right choice."
msgstr "You made the right choice."

#: 17_26N02
msgctxt "17_26N02"
msgid "Well, then you're wasting my time. I have work to do."
msgstr "Well, then you're wasting my time. I have work to do."

#: 17_26P01
msgctxt "17_26P01"
msgid "Look, okay, I'll trust you."
msgstr "Look, okay, I'll trust you."

#: 17_26P02
msgctxt "17_26P02"
msgid "I'm sorry, I can't risk it. There's too much at stake."
msgstr "I'm sorry, I can't risk it. There's too much at stake."

#: 17_27N01
msgctxt "17_27N01"
msgid "Mr. Ripley, no one has entered the tomb in over two thousand years. What makes you think you can succeed where generations before you have failed?"
msgstr "Mr. Ripley, no one has entered the tomb in over two thousand years. What makes you think you can succeed where generations before you have failed?"

#: 17_27N02
msgctxt "17_27N02"
msgid "It's such a crazy story. I almost believe you."
msgstr "It's such a crazy story. I almost believe you."

#: 17_27N03
msgctxt "17_27N03"
msgid "I'm not sure. I found a fragment of script on a stone head north of here, but I doubt it will be of much use to you."
msgstr "I'm not sure. I found a fragment of script on a stone head north of here, but I doubt it will be of much use to you."

#: 17_27N04
msgctxt "17_27N04"
msgid "This way."
msgstr "This way."

#: 17_27P01
msgctxt "17_27P01"
msgid "Somebody, possibly the Japanese or the Nazis or the Chinese communists, it could even be Russians or mobsters for all I know, but somebody is after the first emperor's seal of office. I intend to beat them to it."
msgstr "Somebody, possibly the Japanese or the Nazis or the Chinese communists, it could even be Russians or mobsters for all I know, but somebody is after the first emperor's seal of office. I intend to beat them to it."

#: 17_27P02
msgctxt "17_27P02"
msgid "I don't know that I can. I only know I have to try. I'm the only person in a position to put all the pieces of Master Lu's puzzle together. I came here trying to find a clue to deciphering the Easter Island script on Lu's tablet, and to talk to you."
msgstr "I don't know that I can. I only know I have to try. I'm the only person in a position to put all the pieces of Master Lu's puzzle together. I came here trying to find a clue to deciphering the Easter Island script on Lu's tablet, and to talk to you."

#: 17_27P03
msgctxt "17_27P03"
msgid "Crazy stories of my stock and trade. Can you help me?"
msgstr "Crazy stories of my stock and trade. Can you help me?"

#: 17_27P04
msgctxt "17_27P04"
msgid "I'd like to see it."
msgstr "I'd like to see it."

#: 17_28N01
msgctxt "17_28N01"
msgid "It's about time. Why are you here?"
msgstr "It's about time. Why are you here?"

#: 17_28P01
msgctxt "17_28P01"
msgid "It looks like I have no choice. I have to trust you."
msgstr "It looks like I have no choice. I have to trust you."

#: 17_29N01
msgctxt "17_29N01"
msgid "Suppose you tell me why you're here first."
msgstr "Suppose you tell me why you're here first."

#: 17_29P01
msgctxt "17_29P01"
msgid "Yes."
msgstr "Yes."

#: 17_31N01
msgctxt "17_31N01"
msgid "Yes, it is."
msgstr "Yes, it is."

#: 17_31P01
msgctxt "17_31P01"
msgid "I was taking a look at the island. Beautiful place."
msgstr "I was taking a look at the island. Beautiful place."

#: 18_03N01
msgctxt "18_03N01"
msgid "Did you learn anything?"
msgstr "Did you learn anything?"

#: 18_03N02
msgctxt "18_03N02"
msgid "I'm sure if you can help that old woman she might be able to tell us something."
msgstr "I'm sure if you can help that old woman she might be able to tell us something."

#: 18_03N03
msgctxt "18_03N03"
msgid "You haven't seen my poll, have you?"
msgstr "You haven't seen my poll, have you?"

#: 18_03N04
msgctxt "18_03N04"
msgid "I had it propped in the corner of the pit. I draped a tarp over it so I can work in the rain."
msgstr "I had it propped in the corner of the pit. I draped a tarp over it so I can work in the rain."

#: 18_03P01
msgctxt "18_03P01"
msgid "I'm back!"
msgstr "I'm back!"

#: 18_03P02
msgctxt "18_03P02"
msgid "Not much."
msgstr "Not much."

#: 18_03P04
msgctxt "18_03P04"
msgid "Uh, what, Paul?"
msgstr "Uh, what, Paul?"

#: 18_03P05
msgctxt "18_03P05"
msgid "I'll keep my eyes open."
msgstr "I'll keep my eyes open."

#: 18_05N01
msgctxt "18_05N01"
msgid "Any luck with the old woman?"
msgstr "Any luck with the old woman?"

#: 18_05N02
msgctxt "18_05N02"
msgid "I beg your pardon?"
msgstr "I beg your pardon?"

#: 18_05N03
msgctxt "18_05N03"
msgid "Hmm... pieces of obsidian used to create the pupils of the eyes came from a quarry to the west of here. Thanks to generations of thieves, I'm not sure what's left."
msgstr "Hmm... pieces of obsidian used to create the pupils of the eyes came from a quarry to the west of here. Thanks to generations of thieves, I'm not sure what's left."

#: 18_05P01
msgctxt "18_05P01"
msgid "Hello!"
msgstr "Hello!"

#: 18_05P02
msgctxt "18_05P02"
msgid "She insists that the watching god needs both eyes to see."
msgstr "She insists that the watching god needs both eyes to see."

#: 18_05P03
msgctxt "18_05P03"
msgid "I've ridden the statue, now I need to find an eye."
msgstr "I've ridden the statue, now I need to find an eye."

#: 18_07P01
msgctxt "18_07P01"
msgid "Dr. Twelve Trees."
msgstr "Dr. Twelve Trees."

#: 18_09N01
msgctxt "18_09N01"
msgid "That's terrific news! Did you learn anything from her?"
msgstr "That's terrific news! Did you learn anything from her?"

#: 18_09P01
msgctxt "18_09P01"
msgid "The watching god can see again. We also found the remains of the old woman's ancestor in a hole in the hillside beneath where the statue lay."
msgstr "The watching god can see again. We also found the remains of the old woman's ancestor in a hole in the hillside beneath where the statue lay."

#: 18_10N01
msgctxt "18_10N01"
msgid "Why didn't you explore it?"
msgstr "Why didn't you explore it?"

#: 18_10N02
msgctxt "18_10N02"
msgid "What kind of secret?"
msgstr "What kind of secret?"

#: 18_10N03
msgctxt "18_10N03"
msgid "I've already neglected my dig."
msgstr "I've already neglected my dig."

#: 18_10P01
msgctxt "18_10P01"
msgid "The hole where her ancestor was buried might be worth searching."
msgstr "The hole where her ancestor was buried might be worth searching."

#: 18_10P02
msgctxt "18_10P02"
msgid "The old woman told me her ancestor knew a great secret."
msgstr "The old woman told me her ancestor knew a great secret."

#: 18_10P03
msgctxt "18_10P03"
msgid "Could you help me?"
msgstr "Could you help me?"

#: 18_11N01
msgctxt "18_11N01"
msgid "I'll help."
msgstr "I'll help."

#: 18_11P01
msgctxt "18_11P01"
msgid "I can't reach it on my own."
msgstr "I can't reach it on my own."

#: 18_12N01
msgctxt "18_12N01"
msgid "Show me!"
msgstr "Show me!"

#: 18_12P01
msgctxt "18_12P01"
msgid "She was staring at the hole where we found his bones when she said it."
msgstr "She was staring at the hole where we found his bones when she said it."

#: 18_12P02
msgctxt "18_12P02"
msgid "With pleasure."
msgstr "With pleasure."

#: 18_13N01
msgctxt "18_13N01"
msgid "Really?"
msgstr "Really?"

#: 18_13P01
msgctxt "18_13P01"
msgid "I have another hole for you to explore."
msgstr "I have another hole for you to explore."

#: 18_14N01
msgctxt "18_14N01"
msgid "You know, I never found my pole. I know there's a lot of stealing on the island, but it was worthless."
msgstr "You know, I never found my pole. I know there's a lot of stealing on the island, but it was worthless."

#: 18_14P02
msgctxt "18_14P02"
msgid "I guess somebody found a use for it."
msgstr "I guess somebody found a use for it."

#: 18_15N01
msgctxt "18_15N01"
msgid "I seem to have lost my lighter. You haven't seen it, have you?"
msgstr "I seem to have lost my lighter. You haven't seen it, have you?"

#: 18_15P02
msgctxt "18_15P02"
msgid "Uh, gee, uh, no."
msgstr "Uh, gee, uh, no."

#: 19_02N01
msgctxt "19_02N01"
msgid "Only fragments. I'm hoping my exploration by the altar may produce something."
msgstr "Only fragments. I'm hoping my exploration by the altar may produce something."

#: 19_02N02
msgctxt "19_02N02"
msgid "Mr. Ripley, I'm a trained archaeologist, and it's difficult enough for me."
msgstr "Mr. Ripley, I'm a trained archaeologist, and it's difficult enough for me."

#: 19_02P01
msgctxt "19_02P01"
msgid "Have you seen any other examples?"
msgstr "Have you seen any other examples?"

#: 19_02P02
msgctxt "19_02P02"
msgid "I wonder if I could turn up some more."
msgstr "I wonder if I could turn up some more."

#: 19_03N01
msgctxt "19_03N01"
msgid "I'll bet."
msgstr "I'll bet."

#: 19_03N02
msgctxt "19_03N02"
msgid "If you do find some more script, that will be payment enough."
msgstr "If you do find some more script, that will be payment enough."

#: 19_03N03
msgctxt "19_03N03"
msgid "There is someone you might want to talk to."
msgstr "There is someone you might want to talk to."

#: 19_03P01
msgctxt "19_03P01"
msgid "Well, I don't know. I have a way of stumbling over things other people pass by."
msgstr "Well, I don't know. I have a way of stumbling over things other people pass by."

#: 19_03P02
msgctxt "19_03P02"
msgid "I'm very sorry about that. Please allow me to pay for the damage."
msgstr "I'm very sorry about that. Please allow me to pay for the damage."

#: 19_03P04
msgctxt "19_03P04"
msgid "Who?"
msgstr "Who?"

#: 19_04N01
msgctxt "19_04N01"
msgid "Before you wander off, there is someone you might want to talk to."
msgstr "Before you wander off, there is someone you might want to talk to."

#: 19_05N01
msgctxt "19_05N01"
msgid "An old woman who comes each day to a cove north of here to pray to the watchers."
msgstr "An old woman who comes each day to a cove north of here to pray to the watchers."

#: 19_05P02
msgctxt "19_05P02"
msgid "Sounds like there's an interesting story attached to this old woman."
msgstr "Sounds like there's an interesting story attached to this old woman."

#: 19_06N01
msgctxt "19_06N01"
msgid "Remember the old woman you saw in the cove north of here?"
msgstr "Remember the old woman you saw in the cove north of here?"

#: 19_06P02
msgctxt "19_06P02"
msgid "Yes, tell me about her."
msgstr "Yes, tell me about her."

#: 19_07N01
msgctxt "19_07N01"
msgid "Long ago, there were two tribes on the island, the Long Ears, who were the rulers, and the Short Ears, their subjects. The Long Ears ordered the Short Ears to build these famed Easter Island statues."
msgstr "Long ago, there were two tribes on the island, the Long Ears, who were the rulers, and the Short Ears, their subjects. The Long Ears ordered the Short Ears to build these famed Easter Island statues."

#: 19_07N02
msgctxt "19_07N02"
msgid "The long ears next order the short ears to clear the land of rocks and stones and throw them into the sea."
msgstr "The long ears next order the short ears to clear the land of rocks and stones and throw them into the sea."

#: 19_07N03
msgctxt "19_07N03"
msgid "One theory states the long ears felt the other stones detracted from the majesty of the statues. But the short ears rebelled and determined to attack their oppressors."
msgstr "One theory states the long ears felt the other stones detracted from the majesty of the statues. But the short ears rebelled and determined to attack their oppressors."

#: 19_07N04
msgctxt "19_07N04"
msgid "There were two watchers. One, a man who kept an eye on the sea approach to the Long Ears lands and a guardian god who all believed would punish the Short Ears if he saw them pass."
msgstr "There were two watchers. One, a man who kept an eye on the sea approach to the Long Ears lands and a guardian god who all believed would punish the Short Ears if he saw them pass."

#: 19_07N99
msgctxt "19_07N99"
msgid "A huge ditch stretched the width of the island and prevented attack by land. It was filled with wood and could be ignited to repel invaders. They knew they must attack from the sea. The watchers stood in their way. Come with me!"
msgstr "A huge ditch stretched the width of the island and prevented attack by land. It was filled with wood and could be ignited to repel invaders. They knew they must attack from the sea. The watchers stood in their way. Come with me!"

#: 19_07P02
msgctxt "19_07P02"
msgid "A remarkable achievement."
msgstr "A remarkable achievement."

#: 19_07P03
msgctxt "19_07P03"
msgid "Why?"
msgstr "Why?"

#: 201M01
msgctxt "201M01"
msgid "Yes, there's fear everywhere."
msgstr "Yes, there's fear everywhere."

#: 201M02
msgctxt "201M02"
msgid "I will."
msgstr "I will."

#: 201M03
msgctxt "201M03"
msgid "(Chinese)"
msgstr "(Chinese)"

#: 201M04
msgctxt "201M04"
msgid "Yes, we'll need travel permits to get to Xian province. I'll work on it."
msgstr "Yes, we'll need travel permits to get to Xian province. I'll work on it."

#: 201M06
msgctxt "201M06"
msgid "It was impossible. The Japanese are everywhere. I suspect they want to be the first ones to open the tomb."
msgstr "It was impossible. The Japanese are everywhere. I suspect they want to be the first ones to open the tomb."

#: 201M07
msgctxt "201M07"
msgid "Xi'an province is outside their control, but once my mission was learned, I've been followed, and they are attempting to have our travel permits revoked."
msgstr "Xi'an province is outside their control, but once my mission was learned, I've been followed, and they are attempting to have our travel permits revoked."

#: 201M08
msgctxt "201M08"
msgid "But even if we can reach it, how will we get into the tomb?"
msgstr "But even if we can reach it, how will we get into the tomb?"

#: 201M09
msgctxt "201M09"
msgid "Yes, I have them. Here is the translation of the script you found in the temple. The Chinese was literal. I suppose so specific characters could be matched up next to their"
msgstr "Yes, I have them. Here is the translation of the script you found in the temple. The Chinese was literal. I suppose so specific characters could be matched up next to their"

#: 201R01
msgctxt "201R01"
msgid "The city feels different than when we were last here, doesn't it?"
msgstr "The city feels different than when we were last here, doesn't it?"

#: 201R02
msgctxt "201R02"
msgid "After we visit the Hall of Classics, go see your grandmother. Make sure she's okay."
msgstr "After we visit the Hall of Classics, go see your grandmother. Make sure she's okay."

#: 201R03
msgctxt "201R03"
msgid "Hello, Chien-Chu."
msgstr "Hello, Chien-Chu."

#: 201R04
msgctxt "201R04"
msgid "Any messages for me?"
msgstr "Any messages for me?"

#: 201R05
msgctxt "201R05"
msgid "Hmm... I sent a radiogram to Baron von Seltzim in New York that I was going after the Emerald Seal."
msgstr "Hmm... I sent a radiogram to Baron von Seltzim in New York that I was going after the Emerald Seal."

#: 201R06
msgctxt "201R06"
msgid "Hmm... I sent a radiogram to Baron von Seltzamp that I was going after the Emerald Seal."
msgstr "Hmm... I sent a radiogram to Baron von Seltzamp that I was going after the Emerald Seal."

#: 201R07
msgctxt "201R07"
msgid "All Posh Express offices look pretty much the same."
msgstr "All Posh Express offices look pretty much the same."

#: 201R08
msgctxt "201R08"
msgid "A classic vase in the Sung tradition. Good attempt, but I'm afraid it's a copy."
msgstr "A classic vase in the Sung tradition. Good attempt, but I'm afraid it's a copy."

#: 201R09
msgctxt "201R09"
msgid "The Forbidden City, home to the Imperial Family. Peiping Opera, the Great Wall of China built by Xue Huangdi in only fifteen years. Jiananmen Square. Jiananmen means heavenly peace. May it always remain a haven of heavenly peace in the dark days to come."
msgstr "The Forbidden City, home to the Imperial Family. Peiping Opera, the Great Wall of China built by Xue Huangdi in only fifteen years. Jiananmen Square. Jiananmen means heavenly peace. May it always remain a haven of heavenly peace in the dark days to come."

#: 201R10
msgctxt "201R10"
msgid "From Auckland to Zanzibar, there's always a posh express office when you need it."
msgstr "From Auckland to Zanzibar, there's always a posh express office when you need it."

#: 201R11
msgctxt "201R11"
msgid "Beyond that rice paper is Peiping, a city of a thousand faces. Mysterious, exotic, and these days increasingly dangerous."
msgstr "Beyond that rice paper is Peiping, a city of a thousand faces. Mysterious, exotic, and these days increasingly dangerous."

#: 201R12
msgctxt "201R12"
msgid "No time for reading!"
msgstr "No time for reading!"

#: 201R13
msgctxt "201R13"
msgid "Jiang Shu knows Peiping and its environs better than any other man in China."
msgstr "Jiang Shu knows Peiping and its environs better than any other man in China."

#: 201R14
msgctxt "201R14"
msgid "That rug may look authentic, but Jian Xu tells me it was made by some guy named Sam Glass in Manchester, England."
msgstr "That rug may look authentic, but Jian Xu tells me it was made by some guy named Sam Glass in Manchester, England."

#: 201R15
msgctxt "201R15"
msgid "From everything I've seen since we landed, travel outside the city looks very difficult."
msgstr "From everything I've seen since we landed, travel outside the city looks very difficult."

#: 201R16
msgctxt "201R16"
msgid "First stop, the Hall of Classics."
msgstr "First stop, the Hall of Classics."

#: 201R17
msgctxt "201R17"
msgid "We need to find out as much about Master Lu as we can."
msgstr "We need to find out as much about Master Lu as we can."

#: 201R18
msgctxt "201R18"
msgid "Mei, I'll leave the travel permits to you."
msgstr "Mei, I'll leave the travel permits to you."

#: 201R19
msgctxt "201R19"
msgid "Ripley, you don't need a postcard."
msgstr "Ripley, you don't need a postcard."

#: 201R20
msgctxt "201R20"
msgid "I don't really need four-year-old copies of posh traveling."
msgstr "I don't really need four-year-old copies of posh traveling."

#: 201R21
msgctxt "201R21"
msgid "Ripley, get a grip on yourself."
msgstr "Ripley, get a grip on yourself."

#: 201R22
msgctxt "201R22"
msgid "You don't need that."
msgstr "You don't need that."

#: 201R23
msgctxt "201R23"
msgid "This is no time to play the fool."
msgstr "This is no time to play the fool."

#: 201R24
msgctxt "201R24"
msgid "You can't do that."
msgstr "You can't do that."

#: 201R25
msgctxt "201R25"
msgid "I'd sketch the vase if it were authentic. It's not. And there's nothing else of interest to sketch in here."
msgstr "I'd sketch the vase if it were authentic. It's not. And there's nothing else of interest to sketch in here."

#: 201R26
msgctxt "201R26"
msgid "Mr. Ripley, sir, wanted to remind you to be on the lookout for oddities while you save the world. Sincerely, Feng Li. I'll try to remember, my friend."
msgstr "Mr. Ripley, sir, wanted to remind you to be on the lookout for oddities while you save the world. Sincerely, Feng Li. I'll try to remember, my friend."

#: 201R26A
msgctxt "201R26A"
msgid "Mr. Ripley, sir, wanted to remind you to be on the lookout for oddities while you save the world. Sincerely, Feng Li."
msgstr "Mr. Ripley, sir, wanted to remind you to be on the lookout for oddities while you save the world. Sincerely, Feng Li."

#: 201R27
msgctxt "201R27"
msgid "Nothing from a Baron von Seltsam in Danzig?"
msgstr "Nothing from a Baron von Seltsam in Danzig?"

#: 201R28
msgctxt "201R28"
msgid "Curious. After that business in Egypt and Feng Li's narrow escape..."
msgstr "Curious. After that business in Egypt and Feng Li's narrow escape..."

#: 201R29
msgctxt "201R29"
msgid "I hope not."
msgstr "I hope not."

#: 201R30
msgctxt "201R30"
msgid "Mei, any luck with our travel permits?"
msgstr "Mei, any luck with our travel permits?"

#: 201R31
msgctxt "201R31"
msgid "Then all we need is to decipher Master Lu's tablet and find a way into the tomb. Did you arrange for the necessary equipment and labor for the excavation?"
msgstr "Then all we need is to decipher Master Lu's tablet and find a way into the tomb. Did you arrange for the necessary equipment and labor for the excavation?"

#: 201R32
msgctxt "201R32"
msgid "What's stopping them?"
msgstr "What's stopping them?"

#: 201R33
msgctxt "201R33"
msgid "After all the time it took to secure them, we can't allow that. We can't tarry, Mei. The Baron was right. The world is on the brink of war. Nothing can stop it now. It falls to us to try and protect the seal from those who would exploit it."
msgstr "After all the time it took to secure them, we can't allow that. We can't tarry, Mei. The Baron was right. The world is on the brink of war. Nothing can stop it now. It falls to us to try and protect the seal from those who would exploit it."

#: 201R34
msgctxt "201R34"
msgid "We haven't come this far to be thwarted by a few tons of dirt."
msgstr "We haven't come this far to be thwarted by a few tons of dirt."

#: 201R35
msgctxt "201R35"
msgid "TOGETHER"
msgstr "TOGETHER"

#: 201R36
msgctxt "201R36"
msgid "No time for business now, old man. We have a world to save."
msgstr "No time for business now, old man. We have a world to save."

#: 201R37
msgctxt "201R37"
msgid "Lamps like that were made for decoration, not illumination."
msgstr "Lamps like that were made for decoration, not illumination."

#: 201R38
msgctxt "201R38"
msgid "Did I remember to ask my landlady to water my plants?"
msgstr "Did I remember to ask my landlady to water my plants?"

#: 201R39
msgctxt "201R39"
msgid "It certainly makes a statement, but I wouldn't want to sit on it."
msgstr "It certainly makes a statement, but I wouldn't want to sit on it."

#: 201R40
msgctxt "201R40"
msgid "Thanks to modern inventions like telephones and radio, our world seems smaller every day."
msgstr "Thanks to modern inventions like telephones and radio, our world seems smaller every day."

