msgid "There are messages for you."
msgstr "There are messages for you."

#: 201X06
msgctxt "201X06"
msgid "Do you miss the Ripley? No."
msgstr "Do you miss the Ripley? No."

#: 201X07
msgctxt "201X07"
msgid "Anything wrong?"
msgstr "Anything wrong?"

#: 201X08
msgctxt "201X08"
msgid "Mr. Ripley, you have several radiograms from your New York office."
msgstr "Mr. Ripley, you have several radiograms from your New York office."

#: 201X09
msgctxt "201X09"
msgid "Hello, Mr. Ripley."
msgstr "Hello, Mr. Ripley."

#: 202R01
msgctxt "202R01"
msgid "Boy, this trader stall sure has a lot of useful stuff in it."
msgstr "Boy, this trader stall sure has a lot of useful stuff in it."

#: 202R02
msgctxt "202R02"
msgid "I wonder what the trader's business hours are."
msgstr "I wonder what the trader's business hours are."

#: 202R03
msgctxt "202R03"
msgid "I can't believe it! This place is never open!"
msgstr "I can't believe it! This place is never open!"

#: 202R04
msgctxt "202R04"
msgid "Oh, come on! I'd buy everything in there!"
msgstr "Oh, come on! I'd buy everything in there!"

#: 202R05
msgctxt "202R05"
msgid "Ugh, face it Ripley, you're never gonna get your hands on any of that stuff."
msgstr "Ugh, face it Ripley, you're never gonna get your hands on any of that stuff."

#: 202R06
msgctxt "202R06"
msgid "Ripley, get a grip on yourself."
msgstr "Ripley, get a grip on yourself."

#: 202R08
msgctxt "202R08"
msgid "This is no time to play the fool."
msgstr "This is no time to play the fool."

#: 202R09
msgctxt "202R09"
msgid "You can't do that."
msgstr "You can't do that."

#: 202R10
msgctxt "202R10"
msgid "A rope attached to a grappling hook, useful for climbing over things."
msgstr "A rope attached to a grappling hook, useful for climbing over things."

#: 202R11
msgctxt "202R11"
msgid "An oil lantern. Great for finding your way through dark, twisty passageways."
msgstr "An oil lantern. Great for finding your way through dark, twisty passageways."

#: 202R12
msgctxt "202R12"
msgid "You can never have too many shovels."
msgstr "You can never have too many shovels."

#: 202R13
msgctxt "202R13"
msgid "Those look like skeleton keys."
msgstr "Those look like skeleton keys."

#: 202R14
msgctxt "202R14"
msgid "Looks like a map to some kind of maze."
msgstr "Looks like a map to some kind of maze."

#: 202R15
msgctxt "202R15"
msgid "An axe always comes in handy."
msgstr "An axe always comes in handy."

#: 202R16
msgctxt "202R16"
msgid "Lots of interesting things for an adventure like myself, but nothing much worth sketching."
