msgctxt "204R28"
msgid "The Chinese used ferocious statues like this Fu dog to ward off evil spirits. I'd hate to tangle with the evil spirit that one was built to face."
msgstr "The Chinese used ferocious statues like this Fu dog to ward off evil spirits. I'd hate to tangle with the evil spirit that one was built to face."

#: 204R29
msgctxt "204R29"
msgid "Mei, you'd better get back to trying to secure our travel permits. I'll be in touch. Give my best to your grandmother."
msgstr "Mei, you'd better get back to trying to secure our travel permits. I'll be in touch. Give my best to your grandmother."

#: 204R31
msgctxt "204R31"
msgid "There's no time."
msgstr "There's no time."

#: 204R32
msgctxt "204R32"
msgid "I'm not thinking."
msgstr "I'm not thinking."

#: 204R33
msgctxt "204R33"
msgid "That will work."
msgstr "That will work."

#: 204R34
msgctxt "204R34"
msgid "Any luck with our travel permits, Mei?"
msgstr "Any luck with our travel permits, Mei?"

#: 204R35
msgctxt "204R35"
msgid "Keep trying. We must get to Xian province and have a look at the first emperor's tomb."
msgstr "Keep trying. We must get to Xian province and have a look at the first emperor's tomb."

#: 204R36
msgctxt "204R36"
msgid "How is your grandmother holding up?"
msgstr "How is your grandmother holding up?"

#: 204R37
msgctxt "204R37"
msgid "So, Lu traveled to Peru, Easter Island, and Sikkim, and the written script from these lands were used to create his tablet. And that tablet obviously holds some sort of secret to entering the first emperor's tomb."
msgstr "So, Lu traveled to Peru, Easter Island, and Sikkim, and the written script from these lands were used to create his tablet. And that tablet obviously holds some sort of secret to entering the first emperor's tomb."

#: 204R38
msgctxt "204R38"
msgid "You're right! Ripley, it looks like you're going to have to be traveling in the master's footsteps, retracing Lou's journey around the world, hoping to find a Rosetta stone for each language."
msgstr "You're right! Ripley, it looks like you're going to have to be traveling in the master's footsteps, retracing Lou's journey around the world, hoping to find a Rosetta stone for each language."

#: 204R39
msgctxt "204R39"
msgid "If that were true, the Baron could have deciphered the tablet already. I suspect the key may only prove to be one piece of Master Lu's riddle. The only one who can tell me for sure is the Baron himself."
msgstr "If that were true, the Baron could have deciphered the tablet already. I suspect the key may only prove to be one piece of Master Lu's riddle. The only one who can tell me for sure is the Baron himself."

#: 204R40
msgctxt "204R40"
msgid "That must have fallen out of one of the holes when I pushed a spoke through."
msgstr "That must have fallen out of one of the holes when I pushed a spoke through."

#: 204R41
msgctxt "204R41"
msgid "A silver butterfly. These were once used as currency in China. I wonder how long it lay in that hole, forgotten."
msgstr "A silver butterfly. These were once used as currency in China. I wonder how long it lay in that hole, forgotten."

#: 204R42
msgctxt "204R42"
msgid "I'd better hang on to that for now."
msgstr "I'd better hang on to that for now."

#: 204R43
msgctxt "204R43"
msgid "An oddity like that is worth far more to me in New York."
msgstr "An oddity like that is worth far more to me in New York."

#: 204R47
msgctxt "204R47"
msgid "I don't like the looks of this. The acolyte who guarded Lou's tablet is gone as well."
msgstr "I don't like the looks of this. The acolyte who guarded Lou's tablet is gone as well."

#: 204R48
msgctxt "204R48"
msgid "Looks like Confucian priests aren't much concerned with capitalism."
msgstr "Looks like Confucian priests aren't much concerned with capitalism."

#: 204R49
msgctxt "204R49"
msgid "Next time I will be."
msgstr "Next time I will be."

#: 204R50
msgctxt "204R50"
msgid "The mallet is the property of the temple. I'd better put it back."
msgstr "The mallet is the property of the temple. I'd better put it back."

#: 204R51
msgctxt "204R51"
msgid "A fellow must have graduated from the same guard school as the chaps at Buckingham Palace."
msgstr "A fellow must have graduated from the same guard school as the chaps at Buckingham Palace."

#: 204R52
msgctxt "204R52"
msgid "I wish Mei were here. She could translate the tablets for me."
msgstr "I wish Mei were here. She could translate the tablets for me."

#: 204R61
msgctxt "204R61"
msgid "The bronze gong used to summon the priest."
msgstr "The bronze gong used to summon the priest."

#: 204R62
msgctxt "204R62"
msgid "This is no time for sightseeing. Mei is in deadly danger."
msgstr "This is no time for sightseeing. Mei is in deadly danger."

#: 204R63
msgctxt "204R63"
msgid "I'm not leaving Mei!"
msgstr "I'm not leaving Mei!"

#: 204Y01
msgctxt "204Y01"
msgid "(Chinese) Sir, is there anything I can do for you?"
msgstr "(Chinese) Sir, is there anything I can do for you?"

#: 205K01
msgctxt "205K01"
msgid "I'm delighted to hear that, Mr. Ripley. My name is Quang. We've never been formally introduced."
msgstr "I'm delighted to hear that, Mr. Ripley. My name is Quang. We've never been formally introduced."

#: 205K02
msgctxt "205K02"
msgid "Oops!"
msgstr "Oops!"

#: 205K03
msgctxt "205K03"
msgid "I'm a businessman. I work for whomever pays me."
msgstr "I'm a businessman. I work for whomever pays me."

#: 205K04
msgctxt "205K04"
msgid "No, I'm simply very good at finding things. I'm a retriever, you might say. I fetch."
msgstr "No, I'm simply very good at finding things. I'm a retriever, you might say. I fetch."

#: 205K05
msgctxt "205K05"
msgid "It's Shen Gao, my large associate here, who kills people."
msgstr "It's Shen Gao, my large associate here, who kills people."

#: 205K06
msgctxt "205K06"
msgid "Not quite."
msgstr "Not quite."

#: 205K07
msgctxt "205K07"
msgid "Now."
msgstr "Now."

#: 205M01
msgctxt "205M01"
msgid "You're a traitor!"
msgstr "You're a traitor!"

#: 205M02
msgctxt "205M02"
msgid "Robert!"
msgstr "Robert!"

#: 205M03
msgctxt "205M03"
msgid "Oh, Robert. In another moment..."
msgstr "Oh, Robert. In another moment..."

#: 205M04
msgctxt "205M04"
msgid "What about your journal?"
msgstr "What about your journal?"

#: 205M05
msgctxt "205M05"
msgid "And the key is destroyed. What will we do?"
msgstr "And the key is destroyed. What will we do?"

#: 205M06
msgctxt "205M06"
msgid "Robert, you're a genius. But Quang has a head start, and we still don't know a way into the tomb."
msgstr "Robert, you're a genius. But Quang has a head start, and we still don't know a way into the tomb."

#: 205R01
msgctxt "205R01"
msgid "Careful, Mei. The floor is very uneven here."
msgstr "Careful, Mei. The floor is very uneven here."

#: 205R02
msgctxt "205R02"
msgid "There they are, Mei. Script from Easter Island, Mokamoche and Sikkim."
msgstr "There they are, Mei. Script from Easter Island, Mokamoche and Sikkim."

#: 205R04
msgctxt "205R04"
msgid "You're working for the Japanese, aren't you?"
msgstr "You're working for the Japanese, aren't you?"

#: 205R05
msgctxt "205R05"
msgid "Business man, you're nothing but a murderer for hire."
msgstr "Business man, you're nothing but a murderer for hire."

#: 205R06
msgctxt "205R06"
msgid "Say, listen, you're not mad because I blew you up on Easter Island, are you? Gasoline? Fired? These things happen."
msgstr "Say, listen, you're not mad because I blew you up on Easter Island, are you? Gasoline? Fired? These things happen."

#: 205R07
msgctxt "205R07"
msgid "Wait a second. I've grown quite attached to some of that stuff."
msgstr "Wait a second. I've grown quite attached to some of that stuff."

#: 205R08
msgctxt "205R08"
msgid "I think I should warn you."
msgstr "I think I should warn you."

#: 205R09
msgctxt "205R09"
msgid "You're not the only one who knows martial arts."
msgstr "You're not the only one who knows martial arts."

#: 205R10
msgctxt "205R10"
msgid "Heck no! If it was me, you wouldn't be in so much trouble right now!"
msgstr "Heck no! If it was me, you wouldn't be in so much trouble right now!"

#: 205R11
msgctxt "205R11"
msgid "Stay back, Mei."
msgstr "Stay back, Mei."

#: 205R12
msgctxt "205R12"
msgid "It's the acolyte! He's dead! Shot! Watch your step!"
msgstr "It's the acolyte! He's dead! Shot! Watch your step!"

#: 205R12A
msgctxt "205R12A"
msgid "It's the acolyte! He's dead!"
msgstr "It's the acolyte! He's dead!"

#: 205R12B
msgctxt "205R12B"
msgid "SHOT!"
msgstr "SHOT!"

#: 205R12C
msgctxt "205R12C"
msgid "Watch your step."
msgstr "Watch your step."

#: 205R13
msgctxt "205R13"
msgid "Yes, push man five, blue, pull man one red. This must be it. Mei, we've solved the riddle of Master Lu!"
msgstr "Yes, push man five, blue, pull man one red. This must be it. Mei, we've solved the riddle of Master Lu!"

#: 205R13A
msgctxt "205R13A"
msgid "Push, man, five. Blue, pull, man, one, red."
msgstr "Push, man, five. Blue, pull, man, one, red."

#: 205R14
msgctxt "205R14"
msgid "There must be something in here I can use to help me."
msgstr "There must be something in here I can use to help me."

#: 205R15
msgctxt "205R15"
msgid "The gun landed on the red hot coals in that brazier."
msgstr "The gun landed on the red hot coals in that brazier."

#: 205R16
msgctxt "205R16"
msgid "The gong will shield me from the bullets."
msgstr "The gong will shield me from the bullets."

#: 205R17
msgctxt "205R17"
msgid "A piece of charcoal has fallen from the brazier."
msgstr "A piece of charcoal has fallen from the brazier."

#: 205R18
msgctxt "205R18"
msgid "The history and literature of China inscribed on two tons of limestone."
msgstr "The history and literature of China inscribed on two tons of limestone."

#: 205R19
msgctxt "205R19"
msgid "The tablet is slightly tilted."
msgstr "The tablet is slightly tilted."

#: 205R20
msgctxt "205R20"
msgid "She's holding her own, but soon Shen Gao's strength and size will tell."
msgstr "She's holding her own, but soon Shen Gao's strength and size will tell."

#: 205R21
msgctxt "205R21"
msgid "A man his size and he moves like a cat."
msgstr "A man his size and he moves like a cat."

#: 205R22
msgctxt "205R22"
msgid "The key to lose tablet. Useless rubble now."
msgstr "The key to lose tablet. Useless rubble now."

#: 205R23
msgctxt "205R23"
msgid "Quang tore out all my notes."
msgstr "Quang tore out all my notes."

#: 205R24
msgctxt "205R24"
msgid "I'd better hang on to that for now."
msgstr "I'd better hang on to that for now."

#: 205R25
msgctxt "205R25"
msgid "Oh, that was too close for comfort."
msgstr "Oh, that was too close for comfort."

#: 205R26
msgctxt "205R26"
msgid "Ripley, save Mei Chen. You can clean up later."
msgstr "Ripley, save Mei Chen. You can clean up later."

#: 205R27
msgctxt "205R27"
msgid "I'll worry about the journal after I save Mei Chen."
msgstr "I'll worry about the journal after I save Mei Chen."

#: 205R28
msgctxt "205R28"
msgid "The tablet is far too heavy to lift."
msgstr "The tablet is far too heavy to lift."

#: 205R29
msgctxt "205R29"
msgid "The brazier is bolted to the floor."
msgstr "The brazier is bolted to the floor."

#: 205R30
msgctxt "205R30"
msgid "It would take a lot more force than I can muster to move that."
msgstr "It would take a lot more force than I can muster to move that."

#: 205R31
msgctxt "205R31"
msgid "Hmm... the subsidence of the floor in this alcove has made that tablet pretty unstable."
msgstr "Hmm... the subsidence of the floor in this alcove has made that tablet pretty unstable."

#: 205R32
msgctxt "205R32"
msgid "This one is unsteady as well."
msgstr "This one is unsteady as well."

#: 205R33
msgctxt "205R33"
msgid "What am I thinking of? If I push this over, the other tablets would topple like dominoes. Mei would be crushed."
msgstr "What am I thinking of? If I push this over, the other tablets would topple like dominoes. Mei would be crushed."

#: 205R34
msgctxt "205R34"
msgid "With enough effort, I suspect I could overbalance this."
msgstr "With enough effort, I suspect I could overbalance this."

#: 205R35
msgctxt "205R35"
msgid "Ripley, get a grip on yourself."
msgstr "Ripley, get a grip on yourself."

#: 205R36
msgctxt "205R36"
msgid "You don't need that."
msgstr "You don't need that."

#: 205R37
msgctxt "205R37"
msgid "This is no time to play the fool."
msgstr "This is no time to play the fool."

#: 205R38
msgctxt "205R38"
msgid "There's no time."
msgstr "There's no time."

#: 205R39
msgctxt "205R39"
msgid "I'm not thinking."
msgstr "I'm not thinking."

#: 205R40
msgctxt "205R40"
msgid "That will work."
msgstr "That will work."

#: 205R41
msgctxt "205R41"
msgid "You can't do that."
msgstr "You can't do that."

#: 205R42
msgctxt "205R42"
msgid "This is no time for drawing pictures."
msgstr "This is no time for drawing pictures."

#: 205R43
msgctxt "205R43"
msgid "My pencil is buried under four tons of ancient history."
msgstr "My pencil is buried under four tons of ancient history."

#: 205R44
msgctxt "205R44"
msgid "Gosh, you were swell."
msgstr "Gosh, you were swell."

#: 205R45
msgctxt "205R45"
msgid "I'll have a look."
msgstr "I'll have a look."

#: 205R46
msgctxt "205R46"
msgid "I can see it in the gap between the tablets, but it's too far in to reach."
msgstr "I can see it in the gap between the tablets, but it's too far in to reach."

#: 205R47
msgctxt "205R47"
msgid "This pavilion houses Master Lu's tablet."
msgstr "This pavilion houses Master Lu's tablet."

#: 205R48
msgctxt "205R48"
msgid "The gong shielded me from the bullets."
msgstr "The gong shielded me from the bullets."

#: 205R49
msgctxt "205R49"
msgid "I'll never look at dominoes quite the same way again."
msgstr "I'll never look at dominoes quite the same way again."

#: 205R50
msgctxt "205R50"
msgid "There isn't anyone quite like her."
msgstr "There isn't anyone quite like her."

#: 205R51
msgctxt "205R51"
msgid "I know Shen Gao is a killer, but I wish there had been another way."
msgstr "I know Shen Gao is a killer, but I wish there had been another way."

#: 205R52
msgctxt "205R52"
msgid "My journal is under there. Just out of reach."
msgstr "My journal is under there. Just out of reach."

#: 205R53
msgctxt "205R53"
msgid "The gun is red hot. I don't have time to wait for it to cool."
msgstr "The gun is red hot. I don't have time to wait for it to cool."

#: 205R54
msgctxt "205R54"
msgid "I'd better leave it where it is, just in case there's a bullet left in that gun."
msgstr "I'd better leave it where it is, just in case there's a bullet left in that gun."

#: 205R55
msgctxt "205R55"
msgid "The mallet has served its purpose. I'll leave it behind."
msgstr "The mallet has served its purpose. I'll leave it behind."

#: 205R56
msgctxt "205R56"
msgid "I'd better leave those, otherwise Shen Gao might not be found for a while."
msgstr "I'd better leave those, otherwise Shen Gao might not be found for a while."

#: 205R57
msgctxt "205R57"
msgid "I've damaged enough tablets. I'll leave those standing."
msgstr "I've damaged enough tablets. I'll leave those standing."

#: 205R58
msgctxt "205R58"
msgid "Buck up, Mei. We're not done yet."
msgstr "Buck up, Mei. We're not done yet."

#: 205R59
msgctxt "205R59"
msgid "There is only one place to go now. The first emperor's tomb. But unless I know the answer to lose Riddle, I doubt I'll meet with much success there."
msgstr "There is only one place to go now. The first emperor's tomb. But unless I know the answer to lose Riddle, I doubt I'll meet with much success there."

#: 205R60
msgctxt "205R60"
msgid "I'd better hang on to that for now."
msgstr "I'd better hang on to that for now."

#: 205R64
msgctxt "205R64"
msgid "I'd better leave it alone just in case there's a bullet left in that gun."
msgstr "I'd better leave it alone just in case there's a bullet left in that gun."

#: 205R65
msgctxt "205R65"
msgid "Ripley, you're no match for him physically."
msgstr "Ripley, you're no match for him physically."

#: 205R66
msgctxt "205R66"
msgid "The brazier is full of searing hot coals."
msgstr "The brazier is full of searing hot coals."

#: 205S01
msgctxt "205S01"
msgid "Now."
msgstr "Now."

#: 205S02
msgctxt "205S02"
msgid "You?"
msgstr "You?"

#: 207P01
msgctxt "207P01"
msgid "Thief! Thief! Thief!"
msgstr "Thief! Thief! Thief!"

#: 207P01A
msgctxt "207P01A"
msgid "Leave metal! Leave metal! Metal for blacksmith! Blacksmith give money for metal!"
msgstr "Leave metal! Leave metal! Metal for blacksmith! Blacksmith give money for metal!"

#: 207R01
msgctxt "207R01"
msgid "A peasant? A beggar? He seems to be oblivious to the world, but I wonder..."
msgstr "A peasant? A beggar? He seems to be oblivious to the world, but I wonder..."

#: 207R02
msgctxt "207R02"
msgid "I'm not sure he's as oblivious to the world as he'd like the world to believe."
msgstr "I'm not sure he's as oblivious to the world as he'd like the world to believe."

#: 207R03
msgctxt "207R03"
msgid "Nothing but a bunch of apparently useless metal objects. I guess the fellow must collect them, then sell them to the blacksmith, but... What's that?"
msgstr "Nothing but a bunch of apparently useless metal objects. I guess the fellow must collect them, then sell them to the blacksmith, but... What's that?"

#: 207R03A
msgctxt "207R03A"
msgid "Could I look at that small amulet there?"
msgstr "Could I look at that small amulet there?"

#: 207R03B
msgctxt "207R03B"
msgid "Nothing but a bunch of apparently useless metal objects."
msgstr "Nothing but a bunch of apparently useless metal objects."

#: 207R04
msgctxt "207R04"
msgid "Goodness gracious, it's a Chinese rebus amulet. Two musical stones joined by a disc. It's inscribed, may you be assured, double good fortune."
msgstr "Goodness gracious, it's a Chinese rebus amulet. Two musical stones joined by a disc. It's inscribed, may you be assured, double good fortune."

#: 207R04A
msgctxt "207R04A"
msgid "This is a Chinese Rebus Amulet."
msgstr "This is a Chinese Rebus Amulet."

#: 207R05
msgctxt "207R05"
msgid "Hmm... the remains of an old cart."
msgstr "Hmm... the remains of an old cart."

#: 207R05A
msgctxt "207R05A"
msgid "The remains of an old cart."
msgstr "The remains of an old cart."

#: 207R06
msgctxt "207R06"
msgid "Ordinary lead pipes."
msgstr "Ordinary lead pipes."

#: 207R07
msgctxt "207R07"
msgid "A broken wheel."
msgstr "A broken wheel."

#: 207R08
msgctxt "207R08"
msgid "Seven wooden spokes have broken from the wheel."
msgstr "Seven wooden spokes have broken from the wheel."

#: 207R09
msgctxt "207R09"
msgid "Ripley, get a grip on yourself."
msgstr "Ripley, get a grip on yourself."

#: 207R10
msgctxt "207R10"
msgid "You don't need that."
msgstr "You don't need that."

#: 207R11
msgctxt "207R11"
msgid "This is no time to play the fool."
msgstr "This is no time to play the fool."

#: 207R12
msgctxt "207R12"
msgid "You can't do that."
msgstr "You can't do that."

#: 207R13
msgctxt "207R13"
msgid "Nothing of interest to sketch in here."
msgstr "Nothing of interest to sketch in here."

#: 207R14
msgctxt "207R14"
msgid "A blacksmith's forge."
msgstr "A blacksmith's forge."

#: 207R15
msgctxt "207R15"
msgid "Neatly stacked wood."
msgstr "Neatly stacked wood."

#: 207R16
msgctxt "207R16"
msgid "A broken vase."
msgstr "A broken vase."

#: 207R17
msgctxt "207R17"
msgid "An anvil."
msgstr "An anvil."

#: 207R18
msgctxt "207R18"
msgid "Advice."
msgstr "Advice."

#: 207R19
msgctxt "207R19"
msgid "A sign in Chinese characters."
msgstr "A sign in Chinese characters."

#: 207R20
msgctxt "207R20"
msgid "Jars of grease and oil."
msgstr "Jars of grease and oil."

#: 207R21
msgctxt "207R21"
msgid "The metal rim of the wheel is rusted and crumbling."
msgstr "The metal rim of the wheel is rusted and crumbling."

#: 207R22
msgctxt "207R22"
msgid "All that's left of the wheel are broken pieces of wood."
msgstr "All that's left of the wheel are broken pieces of wood."

#: 207R23
msgctxt "207R23"
msgid "This courtyard must be used by the blacksmith."
msgstr "This courtyard must be used by the blacksmith."

#: 207R23A
msgctxt "207R23A"
msgid "This courtyard is behind what appears to be a blacksmith's shop."
msgstr "This courtyard is behind what appears to be a blacksmith's shop."

#: 207R24
msgctxt "207R24"
msgid "It's closed."
msgstr "It's closed."

#: 207R25
msgctxt "207R25"
msgid "There's not enough left of the wheel to be useful."
msgstr "There's not enough left of the wheel to be useful."

#: 207R26
msgctxt "207R26"
msgid "The wheel is firmly attached to the cart."
msgstr "The wheel is firmly attached to the cart."

#: 207R27
msgctxt "207R27"
msgid "It's far too heavy to move."
msgstr "It's far too heavy to move."

#: 207R28
msgctxt "207R28"
msgid "The animal is too heavy."
msgstr "The animal is too heavy."

#: 207R29
msgctxt "207R29"
msgid "It's broken."
msgstr "It's broken."

#: 207R30
msgctxt "207R30"
msgid "The sign won't do me any good."
msgstr "The sign won't do me any good."

#: 207R31
msgctxt "207R31"
msgid "The jars of grease and oil are far too messy to carry around."
msgstr "The jars of grease and oil are far too messy to carry around."

#: 207R32
msgctxt "207R32"
msgid "The vise is bolted to the bench."
msgstr "The vise is bolted to the bench."

#: 207R33
msgctxt "207R33"
msgid "It's locked."
msgstr "It's locked."

#: 207R34
msgctxt "207R34"
msgid "But what's that?"
msgstr "But what's that?"

#: 207R35
msgctxt "207R35"
msgid "I'm not a thief. I'll leave a fair price."
msgstr "I'm not a thief. I'll leave a fair price."

#: 207R35A
msgctxt "207R35A"
msgid "I'm not a thief."
msgstr "I'm not a thief."

#: 207R36
msgctxt "207R36"
msgid "The lead pipes are quite ordinary. I can pick one up anywhere if I need it. It'll save me lugging these around."
msgstr "The lead pipes are quite ordinary. I can pick one up anywhere if I need it. It'll save me lugging these around."

#: 207R37
msgctxt "207R37"
msgid "There's no time."
msgstr "There's no time."

#: 207R38
msgctxt "207R38"
msgid "I'm not thinking."
msgstr "I'm not thinking."

#: 207R39
msgctxt "207R39"
msgid "That will work."
msgstr "That will work."

#: 207R40
msgctxt "207R40"
msgid "This neatly-stacked wood obviously belongs to someone. If I need some, I can find it elsewhere."
msgstr "This neatly-stacked wood obviously belongs to someone. If I need some, I can find it elsewhere."

#: 207R41
msgctxt "207R41"
msgid "I'd better hang on to that for now."
msgstr "I'd better hang on to that for now."

#: 207R42
msgctxt "207R42"
msgid "I'd better hang on to that for now."
msgstr "I'd better hang on to that for now."

#: 20_02N01
msgctxt "20_02N01"
msgid "I pray..."
msgstr "I pray..."

#: 20_02N02
msgctxt "20_02N02"
msgid "Are you a missionary?"
msgstr "Are you a missionary?"

#: 20_02P01
msgctxt "20_02P01"
msgid "May I talk to you for a moment?"
msgstr "May I talk to you for a moment?"

#: 20_02P02
msgctxt "20_02P02"
msgid "Excuse me, I'd like to help you."
msgstr "Excuse me, I'd like to help you."

#: 20_03N01
msgctxt "20_03N01"
msgid "So that the grandfather of all my grandfathers may rest with honor instead of scorn."
msgstr "So that the grandfather of all my grandfathers may rest with honor instead of scorn."

#: 20_03N02
msgctxt "20_03N02"
msgid "Missionaries have their uses."
msgstr "Missionaries have their uses."

#: 20_03P01
msgctxt "20_03P01"
msgid "That your God may see again?"
msgstr "That your God may see again?"

#: 20_03P02
msgctxt "20_03P02"
msgid "You speak excellent English."
msgstr "You speak excellent English."

#: 20_04N01
msgctxt "20_04N01"
msgid "The missionary who came here did not understand why I pray."
msgstr "The missionary who came here did not understand why I pray."

#: 20_04N02
msgctxt "20_04N02"
msgid "So that the grandfather of all my grandfathers may rest with honor instead of score."
msgstr "So that the grandfather of all my grandfathers may rest with honor instead of score."

#: 20_04P01
msgctxt "20_04P01"
msgid "No."
msgstr "No."

#: 20_04P02
msgctxt "20_04P02"
msgid "But I do understand. You pray that your God may see again."
msgstr "But I do understand. You pray that your God may see again."

#: 20_05N01
msgctxt "20_05N01"
msgid "As a child, I had a vision, as my mother before me, and her mother before her, that one would come from over the sea, even as my people came in times long forgotten. That one would make the watching god see again."
msgstr "As a child, I had a vision, as my mother before me, and her mother before her, that one would come from over the sea, even as my people came in times long forgotten. That one would make the watching god see again."

#: 20_05N02
msgctxt "20_05N02"
msgid "In my vision, the one who would come was much taller."
msgstr "In my vision, the one who would come was much taller."

#: 20_05P01
msgctxt "20_05P01"
msgid "Can I help you in any way?"
msgstr "Can I help you in any way?"

#: 20_05P03
msgctxt "20_05P03"
msgid "When you had the vision, you were much smaller."
msgstr "When you had the vision, you were much smaller."

#: 21_02N01
msgctxt "21_02N01"
msgid "The temple is open to no one except those of the temple."
msgstr "The temple is open to no one except those of the temple."

#: 21_02N02
msgctxt "21_02N02"
msgid "The path to true enlightenment is not easily found."
msgstr "The path to true enlightenment is not easily found."

#: 21_02N03
msgctxt "21_02N03"
msgid "You know of Lou?"
msgstr "You know of Lou?"

#: 21_02N04
msgctxt "21_02N04"
msgid "Only those of the temple may enter."
msgstr "Only those of the temple may enter."

#: 21_02P01
msgctxt "21_02P01"
msgid "Is the temple open to the public?"
msgstr "Is the temple open to the public?"

#: 21_02P02
msgctxt "21_02P02"
msgid "Why is the temple called the Temple of the Hidden Way?"
msgstr "Why is the temple called the Temple of the Hidden Way?"

#: 21_02P03
msgctxt "21_02P03"
msgid "I'm trying to follow the movements of an ancient wise man called Master Lu."
msgstr "I'm trying to follow the movements of an ancient wise man called Master Lu."

#: 21_02P04
msgctxt "21_02P04"
msgid "I'd very much like to see the temple."
msgstr "I'd very much like to see the temple."

#: 21_03N01
msgctxt "21_03N01"
msgid "We have no need of money here."
msgstr "We have no need of money here."

#: 21_03P01
msgctxt "21_03P01"
msgid "Could I make a small contribution to you personally?"
msgstr "Could I make a small contribution to you personally?"

#: 21_04N01
msgctxt "21_04N01"
msgid "Centuries before the temple was built, it is written he sought the elixir of eternal life."
msgstr "Centuries before the temple was built, it is written he sought the elixir of eternal life."

#: 21_04P01
msgctxt "21_04P01"
msgid "Did he visit here then?"
msgstr "Did he visit here then?"

#: 21_05N01
msgctxt "21_05N01"
msgid "Forsake the material world. Spend nine years in solitude and penance in the mountains, then you may apply to join the temple."
msgstr "Forsake the material world. Spend nine years in solitude and penance in the mountains, then you may apply to join the temple."

#: 21_05P01
msgctxt "21_05P01"
msgid "Any way I can join up?"
msgstr "Any way I can join up?"

