#: 301R17
msgctxt "301R17"
msgid "Ripley, you don't need a postcard, you live here."
msgstr "Ripley, you don't need a postcard, you live here."

#: 301R18
msgctxt "301R18"
msgid "Mr. Ripley, sir. You still not send any oddities. Customers need new sensations. We need catch. Fast. Sincerely, Feng Li."
msgstr "Mr. Ripley, sir. You still not send any oddities. Customers need new sensations. We need catch. Fast. Sincerely, Feng Li."

#: 301R19
msgctxt "301R19"
msgid "Mr. Ripley, sir, we need oddities. Customers going to Central Park to watch ducks instead of coming here. Bills passed due. Feng Li low on candles. Help. Sincerely, Feng Li."
msgstr "Mr. Ripley, sir, we need oddities. Customers going to Central Park to watch ducks instead of coming here. Bills passed due. Feng Li low on candles. Help. Sincerely, Feng Li."

#: 301R20
msgctxt "301R20"
msgid "Mr. Ripley, sir. Lights and water cut off shortly. Only three customers today from Ohio. No more oddities, no more auditorium. Situation desperate. Sincerely, Feng Li."
msgstr "Mr. Ripley, sir. Lights and water cut off shortly. Only three customers today from Ohio. No more oddities, no more auditorium. Situation desperate. Sincerely, Feng Li."

#: 301R21
msgctxt "301R21"
msgid "Mr. Ripley, sir. Non-stop chair-sitter take walk. Marshals put padlock on door. Warrant out for your arrest. Don't return to New York until you send oddities first and Feng Li can reopen and pay bills. Sincerely, Feng Li."
msgstr "Mr. Ripley, sir. Non-stop chair-sitter take walk. Marshals put padlock on door. Warrant out for your arrest. Don't return to New York until you send oddities first and Feng Li can reopen and pay bills. Sincerely, Feng Li."

#: 301R22
msgctxt "301R22"
msgid "Yes?"
msgstr "Yes?"

#: 301R23
msgctxt "301R23"
msgid "Ripley, get a grip on yourself."
msgstr "Ripley, get a grip on yourself."

#: 301R24
msgctxt "301R24"
msgid "You don't need that."
msgstr "You don't need that."

#: 301R25
msgctxt "301R25"
msgid "This is no time to play the fool."
msgstr "This is no time to play the fool."

#: 301R26
msgctxt "301R26"
msgid "You can't do that."
msgstr "You can't do that."

#: 301R27
msgctxt "301R27"
msgid "Thanks to modern inventions like telephones and radio, our world seems smaller every day."
msgstr "Thanks to modern inventions like telephones and radio, our world seems smaller every day."

#: 301R28
msgctxt "301R28"
msgid "I must ask my landlady to water my plants while I'm away."
msgstr "I must ask my landlady to water my plants while I'm away."

#: 301R29
msgctxt "301R29"
msgid "It certainly makes a statement, but I wouldn't want to sit on it."
msgstr "It certainly makes a statement, but I wouldn't want to sit on it."

#: 301R30
msgctxt "301R30"
msgid "I can't be too free with my limited funds. I'll undoubtedly need every penny before all this is over."
msgstr "I can't be too free with my limited funds. I'll undoubtedly need every penny before all this is over."

#: 301R31
msgctxt "301R31"
msgid "Time enough to rest later."
msgstr "Time enough to rest later."

#: 301R32
msgctxt "301R32"
msgid "Call me old-fashioned, but I like to do all my business in person."
msgstr "Call me old-fashioned, but I like to do all my business in person."

#: 301R33
msgctxt "301R33"
msgid "Ripley, keep your hands off!"
msgstr "Ripley, keep your hands off!"

#: 301R34
msgctxt "301R34"
msgid "There's no time."
msgstr "There's no time."

#: 301R35
msgctxt "301R35"
msgid "I'm not thinking."
msgstr "I'm not thinking."

#: 301R36
msgctxt "301R36"
msgid "That will work."
msgstr "That will work."

#: 301R37
msgctxt "301R37"
msgid "I enjoy the New York high life, but it's always a relief to get back into my working tugs."
msgstr "I enjoy the New York high life, but it's always a relief to get back into my working tugs."

#: 301R38
msgctxt "301R38"
msgid "It's a copy of that radiogram Feng Li sent before. Mr. Ripley, sir. Non-stop chair-sitter take walk. Marshals put padlock on door. Warrant out for your arrest. Don't return to New York until you send oddities first and Feng Li can reopen and pay bills. Sincerely, Feng Li."
msgstr "It's a copy of that radiogram Feng Li sent before. Mr. Ripley, sir. Non-stop chair-sitter take walk. Marshals put padlock on door. Warrant out for your arrest. Don't return to New York until you send oddities first and Feng Li can reopen and pay bills. Sincerely, Feng Li."

#: 301R39
msgctxt "301R39"
msgid "I'd better hang on to that for now."
msgstr "I'd better hang on to that for now."

#: 301S01
msgctxt "301S01"
msgid "Mr. Robert Ripley?"
msgstr "Mr. Robert Ripley?"

#: 301S02
msgctxt "301S02"
msgid "I have a warrant for your arrest, sir, issued by the District Attorney's Office of the State of New York. You should have paid your bills, Mr. Ripley."
msgstr "I have a warrant for your arrest, sir, issued by the District Attorney's Office of the State of New York. You should have paid your bills, Mr. Ripley."

#: 303F01
msgctxt "303F01"
msgid "Help! Help!"
msgstr "Help! Help!"

#: 303F02
msgctxt "303F02"
msgid "But Mr. Ripley, sir, where you go?"
msgstr "But Mr. Ripley, sir, where you go?"

#: 303F03
msgctxt "303F03"
msgid "I know, I grew up there too."
msgstr "I know, I grew up there too."

#: 303F04
msgctxt "303F04"
msgid "But Mr. Ripley, you haven't seen new exhibits. Almost made a profit this month."
msgstr "But Mr. Ripley, you haven't seen new exhibits. Almost made a profit this month."

#: 303F05
msgctxt "303F05"
msgid "Send me any new exhibits you find."
msgstr "Send me any new exhibits you find."

#: 303F06
msgctxt "303F06"
msgid "Feng Li look after museum."
msgstr "Feng Li look after museum."

#: 303F07
msgctxt "303F07"
msgid "If you need money, check Posh Express account."
msgstr "If you need money, check Posh Express account."

#: 303F08
msgctxt "303F08"
msgid "No new exhibits, no new money."
msgstr "No new exhibits, no new money."

#: 303F09
msgctxt "303F09"
msgid "Spot look just like Ireland to me, Mr. Ripley."
msgstr "Spot look just like Ireland to me, Mr. Ripley."

#: 303F10
msgctxt "303F10"
msgid "Cow has spot on it, shaped exactly like map of Ireland."
msgstr "Cow has spot on it, shaped exactly like map of Ireland."

#: 303F11
msgctxt "303F11"
msgid "Could also be New Jersey."
msgstr "Could also be New Jersey."

#: 303F12
msgctxt "303F12"
msgid "No wonder we not make so much money."
msgstr "No wonder we not make so much money."

#: 303F13
msgctxt "303F13"
msgid "Big puffball getting a bit dusty. I clean."
msgstr "Big puffball getting a bit dusty. I clean."

#: 303F14
msgctxt "303F14"
msgid "It's no Empire State Building."
msgstr "It's no Empire State Building."

#: 303F15
msgctxt "303F15"
msgid "Tomato shaped like human torso getting a bit ripe, Mr. Ripley."
msgstr "Tomato shaped like human torso getting a bit ripe, Mr. Ripley."

#: 303M01
msgctxt "303M01"
msgid "Feng Li doesn't need lights with that candle on his head. We don't need lights either, do we?"
msgstr "Feng Li doesn't need lights with that candle on his head. We don't need lights either, do we?"

#: 303M02
msgctxt "303M02"
msgid "The King Cobra is gone!"
msgstr "The King Cobra is gone!"

#: 303M03
msgctxt "303M03"
msgid "Robert, wait!"
msgstr "Robert, wait!"

#: 303M04
msgctxt "303M04"
msgid "But why the urgency?"
msgstr "But why the urgency?"

#: 303M05
msgctxt "303M05"
msgid "We can't stay here long."
msgstr "We can't stay here long."

#: 303M06
msgctxt "303M06"
msgid "You need to get tickets to Peiping."
msgstr "You need to get tickets to Peiping."

#: 303M07
msgctxt "303M07"
msgid "Lucky I never had a chance to unpack my bags."
msgstr "Lucky I never had a chance to unpack my bags."

#: 303R01
msgctxt "303R01"
msgid "Curious? The door was open, yet the lights aren't on."
msgstr "Curious? The door was open, yet the lights aren't on."

#: 303R02
msgctxt "303R02"
msgid "Look there!"
msgstr "Look there!"

#: 303R03
msgctxt "303R03"
msgid "We need more information about this Master Lu. The place to get it is the Hall of Classics of the Imperial School."
msgstr "We need more information about this Master Lu. The place to get it is the Hall of Classics of the Imperial School."

#: 303R04
msgctxt "303R04"
msgid "Someone's after the Emperor's seal locked in the tomb."
msgstr "Someone's after the Emperor's seal locked in the tomb."

#: 303R05
msgctxt "303R05"
msgid "Feng Li, put the Cobra back in the case. Show the customers how you mesmerized it with your candle."
msgstr "Feng Li, put the Cobra back in the case. Show the customers how you mesmerized it with your candle."

#: 303R06
msgctxt "303R06"
msgid "Feng Li, until you get a new Cobra, put the bloody sword in the case, and you'll have a story to tell."
msgstr "Feng Li, until you get a new Cobra, put the bloody sword in the case, and you'll have a story to tell."

#: 303R07
msgctxt "303R07"
msgid "Charge Extra."
msgstr "Charge Extra."

#: 303R08
msgctxt "303R08"
msgid "Posh Express office. From there, Pei Ping. Beautiful in the springtime."
msgstr "Posh Express office. From there, Pei Ping. Beautiful in the springtime."

#: 303R09
msgctxt "303R09"
msgid "Oh, very well, Feng Li. But I mustn't tarry too long. The shadow of another great war hangs over the East. The Imperial Seal is a powerful talisman. It could be used to unite China under a single dictator like Hitler or Mussolini. We don't need another of those fellows."
msgstr "Oh, very well, Feng Li. But I mustn't tarry too long. The shadow of another great war hangs over the East. The Imperial Seal is a powerful talisman. It could be used to unite China under a single dictator like Hitler or Mussolini. We don't need another of those fellows."

#: 303R10
msgctxt "303R10"
msgid "Schloss Pickas, Free City of Danzig, January 19, 1935. Dear Mr. Ripley, in the province of Xian in China is a little-known monument that ranks among the wonders of the world. You may be interested in it as a subject for your amusing newspaper feature, which appears even here in our little city-state, perched between Germany and Poland. I speak of the tomb of Qin Xie Huangdi, the man who united China for the first time and reigned as emperor some 2300 years ago. For his eternal resting place, he had a great chamber excavated and covered with a copper dome, representing the heavens. Inside he built a veritable miniature China, complete with temples, palaces and buildings of all sorts, overlooking rivers and even a sea of mercury. Row upon row of terracotta soldiers guard the way to unimaginable treasures, including the emperor's emerald seal, a powerful talisman. The chief architect of the place was a certain sage known as Master Lu. At the emperor's command, Liu had traveled across the seas, searching for an elixir of immortality. And though he failed in his quest, he did bring home much arcane knowledge. Liu devised many cunning traps to ensure that the emperor's tomb would never be plundered. Indeed, to this day, no one has so much as penetrated the great mound of earth, now called Mount Li, that covers the dome. I have devoted many years of study to this remarkable monument, compared with which the great pyramids of Egypt are but clumsy heaps of stone. And lately my efforts have been rewarded. Something has come into my hands that I believe provides the key to the tomb. Alas, my health is failing. I am unable to visit the Liu materials in the Hall of Classics at the Imperial School in Peiping, or mount the necessary expeditions to uncover the few remaining clues to Master Lu's secret. One of the leading authorities on this period in China, a Doctor Twelve Trees, is rumored to be in thieves, but so far I've had no success verifying the rumor. I am writing to you, Mr. Ripley, to ask if you would be willing to undertake a joint venture with me. I will carry the banner of science, and you that of the fantastic. I am certain that nowhere in the works of man will you find anything more worthy of inclusion in your believe-it-or-not feature than the tomb of Xue Huangdi. Respectfully yours, Otto Sixth Baron von Seltzen."
msgstr "Schloss Pickas, Free City of Danzig, January 19, 1935. Dear Mr. Ripley, in the province of Xian in China is a little-known monument that ranks among the wonders of the world. You may be interested in it as a subject for your amusing newspaper feature, which appears even here in our little city-state, perched between Germany and Poland. I speak of the tomb of Qin Xie Huangdi, the man who united China for the first time and reigned as emperor some 2300 years ago. For his eternal resting place, he had a great chamber excavated and covered with a copper dome, representing the heavens. Inside he built a veritable miniature China, complete with temples, palaces and buildings of all sorts, overlooking rivers and even a sea of mercury. Row upon row of terracotta soldiers guard the way to unimaginable treasures, including the emperor's emerald seal, a powerful talisman. The chief architect of the place was a certain sage known as Master Lu. At the emperor's command, Liu had traveled across the seas, searching for an elixir of immortality. And though he failed in his quest, he did bring home much arcane knowledge. Liu devised many cunning traps to ensure that the emperor's tomb would never be plundered. Indeed, to this day, no one has so much as penetrated the great mound of earth, now called Mount Li, that covers the dome. I have devoted many years of study to this remarkable monument, compared with which the great pyramids of Egypt are but clumsy heaps of stone. And lately my efforts have been rewarded. Something has come into my hands that I believe provides the key to the tomb. Alas, my health is failing. I am unable to visit the Liu materials in the Hall of Classics at the Imperial School in Peiping, or mount the necessary expeditions to uncover the few remaining clues to Master Lu's secret. One of the leading authorities on this period in China, a Doctor Twelve Trees, is rumored to be in thieves, but so far I've had no success verifying the rumor. I am writing to you, Mr. Ripley, to ask if you would be willing to undertake a joint venture with me. I will carry the banner of science, and you that of the fantastic. I am certain that nowhere in the works of man will you find anything more worthy of inclusion in your believe-it-or-not feature than the tomb of Xue Huangdi. Respectfully yours, Otto Sixth Baron von Seltzen."

#: 303R11
msgctxt "303R11"
msgid "Dear Mr. Ripley..."
msgstr "Dear Mr. Ripley..."

#: 303R12
msgctxt "303R12"
msgid "In the province of Xian in China is a little-known monument that ranks among the wonders of the world. You may be interested in it as a subject for your amusing newspaper feature, which appears even here in our little city-state perched between Germany and Poland."
msgstr "In the province of Xian in China is a little-known monument that ranks among the wonders of the world. You may be interested in it as a subject for your amusing newspaper feature, which appears even here in our little city-state perched between Germany and Poland."

#: 303R13
msgctxt "303R13"
msgid "I speak of the tomb of Qin Xie Huangdi, the man who united China for the first time and reigned as emperor some 2300 years ago. For his eternal resting place, he had a great chamber excavated and covered with a copper dome, representing the heavens."
msgstr "I speak of the tomb of Qin Xie Huangdi, the man who united China for the first time and reigned as emperor some 2300 years ago. For his eternal resting place, he had a great chamber excavated and covered with a copper dome, representing the heavens."

#: 303R14
msgctxt "303R14"
msgid "Inside he built a veritable miniature China, complete with temples, palaces, and buildings of all sorts, overlooking rivers and even a sea of mercury. Row upon row of terracotta soldiers guard the way to unimaginable treasures, including the emperor's great jade seal, a powerful talisman."
msgstr "Inside he built a veritable miniature China, complete with temples, palaces, and buildings of all sorts, overlooking rivers and even a sea of mercury. Row upon row of terracotta soldiers guard the way to unimaginable treasures, including the emperor's great jade seal, a powerful talisman."

#: 303R15
msgctxt "303R15"
msgid "The chief architect of the place was a certain sage known as Master Lu. At the emperor's command, Liu had traveled across the seas searching for an elixir of immortality. And though he failed in his quest, he did bring home much arcane knowledge."
msgstr "The chief architect of the place was a certain sage known as Master Lu. At the emperor's command, Liu had traveled across the seas searching for an elixir of immortality. And though he failed in his quest, he did bring home much arcane knowledge."

#: 303R16
msgctxt "303R16"
msgid "Liu devised many cunning traps to ensure that the Emperor's tomb would never be plundered. Indeed, to this day, no one has so much as penetrated the great mound of earth, now called Mount Li, that covers the dome."
msgstr "Liu devised many cunning traps to ensure that the Emperor's tomb would never be plundered. Indeed, to this day, no one has so much as penetrated the great mound of earth, now called Mount Li, that covers the dome."

#: 303R17
msgctxt "303R17"
msgid "I have devoted many years of study to this remarkable monument, compared with which the great pyramids of Egypt are but clumsy heaps of stone. And lately my efforts have been rewarded. Something has come into my hands that I believe provides the key to the tomb."
msgstr "I have devoted many years of study to this remarkable monument, compared with which the great pyramids of Egypt are but clumsy heaps of stone. And lately my efforts have been rewarded. Something has come into my hands that I believe provides the key to the tomb."

#: 303R18
msgctxt "303R18"
msgid "Alas, my health is failing. I am unable to visit the Liu materials in the Hall of Classics at the Imperial School in Peiping, or mount the necessary expeditions to uncover the few remaining clues to Master Lu's secret."
msgstr "Alas, my health is failing. I am unable to visit the Liu materials in the Hall of Classics at the Imperial School in Peiping, or mount the necessary expeditions to uncover the few remaining clues to Master Lu's secret."

#: 303R19
msgctxt "303R19"
msgid "One of the leading authorities on this period in China, a Dr. Twelve Trees, is rumored to be in Thebes, but so far I've had no success verifying the rumor."
msgstr "One of the leading authorities on this period in China, a Dr. Twelve Trees, is rumored to be in Thebes, but so far I've had no success verifying the rumor."

#: 303R20
msgctxt "303R20"
msgid "I am writing to you, Mr. Ripley, to ask if you would be willing to undertake a joint venture with me. I will carry the banner of science and you that of the fantastic."
msgstr "I am writing to you, Mr. Ripley, to ask if you would be willing to undertake a joint venture with me. I will carry the banner of science and you that of the fantastic."

#: 303R21
msgctxt "303R21"
msgid "I am certain that nowhere in the works of man will you find anything more worthy of inclusion in your, believe it or not, feature than the tomb of Xue Huangdi."
msgstr "I am certain that nowhere in the works of man will you find anything more worthy of inclusion in your, believe it or not, feature than the tomb of Xue Huangdi."

#: 303R22
msgctxt "303R22"
msgid "Respectfully Yours, Otto 6th Baron von Seltzen."
msgstr "Respectfully Yours, Otto 6th Baron von Seltzen."

#: 303R23
msgctxt "303R23"
msgid "These exhibits will be priceless one day. Human beings have a wonderful fascination for the bizarre."
msgstr "These exhibits will be priceless one day. Human beings have a wonderful fascination for the bizarre."

#: 303R24
msgctxt "303R24"
msgid "Yes! Remarkable!"
msgstr "Yes! Remarkable!"

#: 303R25
msgctxt "303R25"
msgid "A giant matchstick made from toothpicks."
msgstr "A giant matchstick made from toothpicks."

#: 303R26
msgctxt "303R26"
msgid "Twenty-eight pounds of fungus. Amazing!"
msgstr "Twenty-eight pounds of fungus. Amazing!"

#: 303R27
msgctxt "303R27"
msgid "Tourists like it!"
msgstr "Tourists like it!"

#: 303R28
msgctxt "303R28"
msgid "We need more amazing exhibits, Feng Li. They're out there somewhere. I just have to find them."
msgstr "We need more amazing exhibits, Feng Li. They're out there somewhere. I just have to find them."

#: 303R28A
msgctxt "303R28A"
msgid "We need more amazing exhibits. They are out there somewhere. I just have to find them."
msgstr "We need more amazing exhibits. They are out there somewhere. I just have to find them."

#: 303R29
msgctxt "303R29"
msgid "The Iron Maiden. Her embrace meant death to religious heretics in Germany."
msgstr "The Iron Maiden. Her embrace meant death to religious heretics in Germany."

#: 303R30
msgctxt "303R30"
msgid "Scientists discovered hair grew on this mummy long after death."
msgstr "Scientists discovered hair grew on this mummy long after death."

#: 303R31
msgctxt "303R31"
msgid "This creature, long thought extinct, sports a single razor sharp claw and five eyes."
msgstr "This creature, long thought extinct, sports a single razor sharp claw and five eyes."

#: 303R32
msgctxt "303R32"
msgid "The sooner that case is filled again, the better. It's prominently displayed in our newspaper ads."
msgstr "The sooner that case is filled again, the better. It's prominently displayed in our newspaper ads."

#: 303R33
msgctxt "303R33"
msgid "Ah, Elmo Azarius, incredible man, drives twenty penny nails into his nasal passages with a hammer and has never had a cold."
msgstr "Ah, Elmo Azarius, incredible man, drives twenty penny nails into his nasal passages with a hammer and has never had a cold."

#: 303R34
msgctxt "303R34"
msgid "The ticket window."
msgstr "The ticket window."

#: 303R35
msgctxt "303R35"
msgid "Pictures of oddities are all very well, but the real thing on display is what sells tickets."
msgstr "Pictures of oddities are all very well, but the real thing on display is what sells tickets."

#: 303R36
msgctxt "303R36"
msgid "A giant matchstick made from toothpicks. Nobody else has one."
msgstr "A giant matchstick made from toothpicks. Nobody else has one."

#: 303R37
msgctxt "303R37"
msgid "Twenty-eight pounds of fungus... and it's all mine."
msgstr "Twenty-eight pounds of fungus... and it's all mine."

#: 303R38
msgctxt "303R38"
msgid "I like snakes the best when there is a wall of glass between us."
msgstr "I like snakes the best when there is a wall of glass between us."

#: 303R39
msgctxt "303R39"
msgid "Ripley, get a grip on yourself."
msgstr "Ripley, get a grip on yourself."

#: 303R40
msgctxt "303R40"
msgid "You don't need that."
msgstr "You don't need that."

#: 303R41
msgctxt "303R41"
msgid "This is no time to play the fool."
msgstr "This is no time to play the fool."

#: 303R42
msgctxt "303R42"
msgid "You can't do that."
msgstr "You can't do that."

#: 303R43
msgctxt "303R43"
msgid "I have that. I don't need a sketch of it."
msgstr "I have that. I don't need a sketch of it."

#: 303R45
msgctxt "303R45"
msgid "There's no time."
msgstr "There's no time."

#: 303R46
msgctxt "303R46"
msgid "I'm not thinking."
msgstr "I'm not thinking."

#: 303R47
msgctxt "303R47"
msgid "That will work."
msgstr "That will work."

#: 303R48
msgctxt "303R48"
msgid "I'd better hang on to that for now."
msgstr "I'd better hang on to that for now."

#: 304F01
msgctxt "304F01"
msgid "Mr. Ripley, please be quick!"
msgstr "Mr. Ripley, please be quick!"

#: 304F02
msgctxt "304F02"
msgid "Two very bad Chinese men forced their way in after closing time."
msgstr "Two very bad Chinese men forced their way in after closing time."

#: 304F03
msgctxt "304F03"
msgid "Yes, yes!"
msgstr "Yes, yes!"

#: 304F04
msgctxt "304F04"
msgid "Your file on a tomb of Qin Shi Huang."
msgstr "Your file on a tomb of Qin Shi Huang."

#: 304F05
msgctxt "304F05"
msgid "Who?"
msgstr "Who?"

#: 304M01
msgctxt "304M01"
msgid "Robert, DO SOMETHING!"
msgstr "Robert, DO SOMETHING!"

#: 304M02
msgctxt "304M02"
msgid "Oh, Robert, you've killed your most valuable exhibit."
msgstr "Oh, Robert, you've killed your most valuable exhibit."

#: 304M03
msgctxt "304M03"
msgid "Oh, well done! You've saved Feng Li and the snake!"
msgstr "Oh, well done! You've saved Feng Li and the snake!"

#: 304M04
msgctxt "304M04"
msgid "What happened, Feng Li?"
msgstr "What happened, Feng Li?"

#: 304M05
msgctxt "304M05"
msgid "Qin Shi Huang, China's first emperor."
msgstr "Qin Shi Huang, China's first emperor."

#: 304M06
msgctxt "304M06"
msgid "Why would these men be interested in the Emperor's tomb?"
msgstr "Why would these men be interested in the Emperor's tomb?"

#: 304M07
msgctxt "304M07"
msgid "Yes, to visit my grandmother. But I wasn't going until October."
msgstr "Yes, to visit my grandmother. But I wasn't going until October."

#: 304M08
msgctxt "304M08"
msgid "I know it's very pretty. I grew up there, but..."
msgstr "I know it's very pretty. I grew up there, but..."

#: 304R01
msgctxt "304R01"
msgid "I can't leave Feng Li while he's in danger."
msgstr "I can't leave Feng Li while he's in danger."

#: 304R02
msgctxt "304R02"
msgid "This office must contain a weapon or something."
msgstr "This office must contain a weapon or something."

#: 304R03
msgctxt "304R03"
msgid "Feng Li mesmerized the creature with his candle."
msgstr "Feng Li mesmerized the creature with his candle."

#: 304R04
msgctxt "304R04"
msgid "No time to get made a safety."
msgstr "No time to get made a safety."

#: 304R05
msgctxt "304R05"
msgid "Masks and shields from all over the world."
msgstr "Masks and shields from all over the world."

#: 304R06
msgctxt "304R06"
msgid "My collection of beer steins."
msgstr "My collection of beer steins."

#: 304R07
msgctxt "304R07"
msgid "No hope, I suppose, of getting the Cobra drunk."
msgstr "No hope, I suppose, of getting the Cobra drunk."

#: 304R08
msgctxt "304R08"
msgid "When I bought that Cobra, I was delighted with its size. I'm not so delighted anymore."
msgstr "When I bought that Cobra, I was delighted with its size. I'm not so delighted anymore."

#: 304R09
msgctxt "304R09"
msgid "I wonder if I've got anything filed under handling cobras."
msgstr "I wonder if I've got anything filed under handling cobras."

#: 304R10
msgctxt "304R10"
msgid "Ah, what's that on the flat file cabinet?"
msgstr "Ah, what's that on the flat file cabinet?"

#: 304R11
msgctxt "304R11"
msgid "This sword, belonging to one of the 47 Ronin, the most famous of all Samurai, still holds its razor edge after more than two centuries."
msgstr "This sword, belonging to one of the 47 Ronin, the most famous of all Samurai, still holds its razor edge after more than two centuries."

#: 304R12
msgctxt "304R12"
msgid "The snake handling stick. The fools must have tossed it there after using it to bring the cobra in here."
msgstr "The snake handling stick. The fools must have tossed it there after using it to bring the cobra in here."

#: 304R13
msgctxt "304R13"
msgid "Champs or chumps? I can reminisce about my first cartoon when things aren't as tense."
msgstr "Champs or chumps? I can reminisce about my first cartoon when things aren't as tense."

#: 304R14
msgctxt "304R14"
msgid "That trunk has seen many far corners of this world. Empty now."
msgstr "That trunk has seen many far corners of this world. Empty now."

