msgstr "That will work."

#: 305R46
msgctxt "305R46"
msgid "That silver butterfly was once used in China for currency."
msgstr "That silver butterfly was once used in China for currency."

#: 305R47
msgctxt "305R47"
msgid "That horn from Easter Island was carved from a single piece of whalebone and was instrumental in saving the life of the famed archaeologist, Dr. Samantha Twelve Treats."
msgstr "That horn from Easter Island was carved from a single piece of whalebone and was instrumental in saving the life of the famed archaeologist, Dr. Samantha Twelve Treats."

#: 305R47A
msgctxt "305R47A"
msgid "That horn from Easter Island was carved from a single piece of whalebone."
msgstr "That horn from Easter Island was carved from a single piece of whalebone."

#: 305R48
msgctxt "305R48"
msgid "Made only of native materials like sticks and shells, intricate navigational charts like this were constructed by the islanders of the South Pacific. This particular map, several hundred years old, pointed the way to glyphs which may one day provide the key to translating Easter Island's forgotten time."
msgstr "Made only of native materials like sticks and shells, intricate navigational charts like this were constructed by the islanders of the South Pacific. This particular map, several hundred years old, pointed the way to glyphs which may one day provide the key to translating Easter Island's forgotten time."

#: 305R49
msgctxt "305R49"
msgid "This chisel used to build an elaborate maze beneath the Temple of the Hidden Way in Sikkim has been fashioned in the shape of a Yeti, the legendary creature we call the Abominable Snowman of the Himalayas."
msgstr "This chisel used to build an elaborate maze beneath the Temple of the Hidden Way in Sikkim has been fashioned in the shape of a Yeti, the legendary creature we call the Abominable Snowman of the Himalayas."

#: 305R50
msgctxt "305R50"
msgid "This incense holder from the Temple of the Hidden Way in Sikkim has three bowls. They are labeled Love, Peace, and Serenity. A different herb would be burned depending on which state the monk wished to achieve."
msgstr "This incense holder from the Temple of the Hidden Way in Sikkim has three bowls. They are labeled Love, Peace, and Serenity. A different herb would be burned depending on which state the monk wished to achieve."

#: 305R51
msgctxt "305R51"
msgid "A fabulous crystal skull from the Andes Mountains, fashioned by a now-forgotten race that predated the Inca. This skull acted like a prism to separate all the colors of the spectrum for some religious ceremony. The exact purpose of the rite remains a mystery, but for the people who fashioned the skull, death and human sacrifice were a central part of their lives."
msgstr "A fabulous crystal skull from the Andes Mountains, fashioned by a now-forgotten race that predated the Inca. This skull acted like a prism to separate all the colors of the spectrum for some religious ceremony. The exact purpose of the rite remains a mystery, but for the people who fashioned the skull, death and human sacrifice were a central part of their lives."

#: 305R52
msgctxt "305R52"
msgid "This is the cheapest stamp in the world, worth only four thousandths of a cent."
msgstr "This is the cheapest stamp in the world, worth only four thousandths of a cent."

#: 305R53
msgctxt "305R53"
msgid "Banknotes like this one, worth 50 million marks, were used as prescription blanks by doctors."
msgstr "Banknotes like this one, worth 50 million marks, were used as prescription blanks by doctors."

#: 305R54
msgctxt "305R54"
msgid "I'd better hang on to that for now."
msgstr "I'd better hang on to that for now."

#: 305R55
msgctxt "305R55"
msgid "Poor little fellow has been through enough already. I'd best leave him where he is."
msgstr "Poor little fellow has been through enough already. I'd best leave him where he is."

#: 30_01N01
msgctxt "30_01N01"
msgid "I know the prayer of serenity."
msgstr "I know the prayer of serenity."

#: 30_01N02
msgctxt "30_01N02"
msgid "When I have learned it, then you may know."
msgstr "When I have learned it, then you may know."

#: 30_01N03
msgctxt "30_01N03"
msgid "He who seeks peace has been here ten years longer than I."
msgstr "He who seeks peace has been here ten years longer than I."

#: 30_01N04
msgctxt "30_01N04"
msgid "Perhaps I'll talk to you later, if I may."
msgstr "Perhaps I'll talk to you later, if I may."

#: 30_01P01
msgctxt "30_01P01"
msgid "What is the prayer you have learned?"
msgstr "What is the prayer you have learned?"

#: 30_01P02
msgctxt "30_01P02"
msgid "What is the prayer you study?"
msgstr "What is the prayer you study?"

#: 30_01P03
msgctxt "30_01P03"
msgid "Have you studied long?"
msgstr "Have you studied long?"

#: 352R01
msgctxt "352R01"
msgid "It's open."
msgstr "It's open."

#: 354F01
msgctxt "354F01"
msgid "Mr. Ripley, quick! Only a bit of candle left!"
msgstr "Mr. Ripley, quick! Only a bit of candle left!"

#: 354F02
msgctxt "354F02"
msgid "Mr. Ripley, help me!"
msgstr "Mr. Ripley, help me!"

#: 401R01
msgctxt "401R01"
msgid "Guten Tag, Horst!"
msgstr "Guten Tag, Horst!"

#: 401R02
msgctxt "401R02"
msgid "Horst, are you familiar with Baron von Seltsam's castle?"
msgstr "Horst, are you familiar with Baron von Seltsam's castle?"

#: 401R03
msgctxt "401R03"
msgid "I'll need transportation."
msgstr "I'll need transportation."

#: 401R05
msgctxt "401R05"
msgid "That giant beer stein would make a fine addition to my collection. Is the beer stein for sale by any chance?"
msgstr "That giant beer stein would make a fine addition to my collection. Is the beer stein for sale by any chance?"

#: 401R06
msgctxt "401R06"
msgid "Man must have the stamina of a Brahma bull."
msgstr "Man must have the stamina of a Brahma bull."

#: 401R07
msgctxt "401R07"
msgid "A formidable beer stein! A pity it's not for sale."
msgstr "A formidable beer stein! A pity it's not for sale."

#: 401R08
msgctxt "401R08"
msgid "The medieval city of Danzig with its narrow winding streets. The Church of St. Mary. Langarten, spacious public gardens that rival the Tuileries of Paris. A beautiful city underappreciated by the common tourist."
msgstr "The medieval city of Danzig with its narrow winding streets. The Church of St. Mary. Langarten, spacious public gardens that rival the Tuileries of Paris. A beautiful city underappreciated by the common tourist."

#: 401R10
msgctxt "401R10"
msgid "Magnificent leathered windows. Shame they hide the view."
msgstr "Magnificent leathered windows. Shame they hide the view."

#: 401R12
msgctxt "401R12"
msgid "Horsed is a fine example of Posh Express courtesy and efficiency."
msgstr "Horsed is a fine example of Posh Express courtesy and efficiency."

#: 401R13
msgctxt "401R13"
msgid "No time for revelry!"
msgstr "No time for revelry!"

#: 401R22
msgctxt "401R22"
msgid "A low railing separates the desk from the rest of the office."
msgstr "A low railing separates the desk from the rest of the office."

#: 401R23
msgctxt "401R23"
msgid "Where horse can work with clients."
msgstr "Where horse can work with clients."

#: 401R24
msgctxt "401R24"
msgid "Where would we be without such modern appliances?"
msgstr "Where would we be without such modern appliances?"

#: 401R25
msgctxt "401R25"
msgid "For the life of me, I can't remember if I reminded my landlady to water the plants in my apartment."
msgstr "For the life of me, I can't remember if I reminded my landlady to water the plants in my apartment."

#: 401R29
msgctxt "401R29"
msgid "I'd like to get a message to the Danzig Chief of Police. I'm curious to learn exactly how the last Baron von Seltsam died."
msgstr "I'd like to get a message to the Danzig Chief of Police. I'm curious to learn exactly how the last Baron von Seltsam died."

#: 401R30
msgctxt "401R30"
msgid "No, but certain events make the timing of the Baron's death troubling. Can you get a message to the Chief of Police?"
msgstr "No, but certain events make the timing of the Baron's death troubling. Can you get a message to the Chief of Police?"

#: 401R31
msgctxt "401R31"
msgid "The baron's son hounded me about this as well. I can state, without hesitation, that the old baron died of pneumonia. The only curse on the old baron was a tendency to sleep with the windows open. Pleased to keep out of police affairs. Signed Krut, Chief of Police, Free City of Danzig."
msgstr "The baron's son hounded me about this as well. I can state, without hesitation, that the old baron died of pneumonia. The only curse on the old baron was a tendency to sleep with the windows open. Pleased to keep out of police affairs. Signed Krut, Chief of Police, Free City of Danzig."

#: 401R31A
msgctxt "401R31A"
msgid "Pleased to keep out of police affairs. Signed Crutt, Chief of Police, Free City of Danzig."
msgstr "Pleased to keep out of police affairs. Signed Crutt, Chief of Police, Free City of Danzig."

#: 401R32
msgctxt "401R32"
msgid "Horst, I want to send a radiogram to Lima, Peru, to a professor Menendez at the university."
msgstr "Horst, I want to send a radiogram to Lima, Peru, to a professor Menendez at the university."

#: 401R33
msgctxt "401R33"
msgid "I also have a special parcel to send to New York."
msgstr "I also have a special parcel to send to New York."

#: 401R34
msgctxt "401R34"
msgid "Horst, I have a special parcel to send in New York."
msgstr "Horst, I have a special parcel to send in New York."

#: 401R35
msgctxt "401R35"
msgid "A turtle of distinction, and I've packed lots of his favorite treats in with him for the long journey home. Handle with care."
msgstr "A turtle of distinction, and I've packed lots of his favorite treats in with him for the long journey home. Handle with care."

#: 401R36
msgctxt "401R36"
msgid "Mr. Ripley Sir, thank you very much for returning Little Turtle Friend. Glad to report he arrived safely, although for some reason he not much like maple sugar treats anymore. Sincerely, Feng Li."
msgstr "Mr. Ripley Sir, thank you very much for returning Little Turtle Friend. Glad to report he arrived safely, although for some reason he not much like maple sugar treats anymore. Sincerely, Feng Li."

#: 401R37
msgctxt "401R37"
msgid "Mr. Ripley, sir. Emerald, look nice, but act bad. Remind Feng Li of first wife. Feng Li thinks it must be cursed. After it on display only two hours, shark fall on one customer. Another customer have allergic reaction to puffball. Each day only get worse. I send back Emerald to you, sincerely, Feng Li."
msgstr "Mr. Ripley, sir. Emerald, look nice, but act bad. Remind Feng Li of first wife. Feng Li thinks it must be cursed. After it on display only two hours, shark fall on one customer. Another customer have allergic reaction to puffball. Each day only get worse. I send back Emerald to you, sincerely, Feng Li."

#: 401R37A
msgctxt "401R37A"
msgid "After it on display only two hours, cow turntable motor break down. Shark fall on one customer. Another customer have allergic reaction to puffball. Each day only get worse. I send back Emerald to you sincerely, Feng Li."
msgstr "After it on display only two hours, cow turntable motor break down. Shark fall on one customer. Another customer have allergic reaction to puffball. Each day only get worse. I send back Emerald to you sincerely, Feng Li."

#: 401R38
msgctxt "401R38"
msgid "Mr. Ripley sir, no want emerald. Rocking man fall off chair. Customers get into fist fight. Almost squished tomato torso. Feng Li's eyebrows catch on fire. First time ever. I refuse delivery if you send emerald to me again. Sincerely, Feng Li."
msgstr "Mr. Ripley sir, no want emerald. Rocking man fall off chair. Customers get into fist fight. Almost squished tomato torso. Feng Li's eyebrows catch on fire. First time ever. I refuse delivery if you send emerald to me again. Sincerely, Feng Li."

#: 401R39
msgctxt "401R39"
msgid "Refuse delivery. Feng Li warned me that's what he'd do."
msgstr "Refuse delivery. Feng Li warned me that's what he'd do."

#: 401R40
msgctxt "401R40"
msgid "I can catch a taxi to the castle."
msgstr "I can catch a taxi to the castle."

#: 401R41
msgctxt "401R41"
msgid "The coat rack has been put to its proper use."
msgstr "The coat rack has been put to its proper use."

#: 401X01
msgctxt "401X01"
msgid "Herr Ripley, it is good to see you again."
msgstr "Herr Ripley, it is good to see you again."

#: 401X02
msgctxt "401X02"
msgid "There is a message for you."
msgstr "There is a message for you."

#: 401X03
msgctxt "401X03"
msgid "There are messages for you."
msgstr "There are messages for you."

#: 401X04
msgctxt "401X04"
msgid "Oh, indeed, my hair. It is a local attraction."
msgstr "Oh, indeed, my hair. It is a local attraction."

#: 401X05
msgctxt "401X05"
msgid "There is a taxi stand in the next block."
msgstr "There is a taxi stand in the next block."

#: 401X06
msgctxt "401X06"
msgid "I'm sorry, Hare Ripley, but no, he belonged to my uncle, France. He drained every drop on the first night of Oktoberfest, twelve years ago."
msgstr "I'm sorry, Hare Ripley, but no, he belonged to my uncle, France. He drained every drop on the first night of Oktoberfest, twelve years ago."

#: 401X07
msgctxt "401X07"
msgid "It is difficult to say. I will ask him when he comes out of the coma."
msgstr "It is difficult to say. I will ask him when he comes out of the coma."

#: 401X08
msgctxt "401X08"
msgid "Good day, Mr. Ripley."
msgstr "Good day, Mr. Ripley."

#: 401X09
msgctxt "401X09"
msgid "You suspect foul play?"
msgstr "You suspect foul play?"

#: 401X10
msgctxt "401X10"
msgid "Leave it to me, Herr Ripley."
msgstr "Leave it to me, Herr Ripley."

#: 401X11
msgctxt "401X11"
msgid "They're good here, Ripley."
msgstr "They're good here, Ripley."

#: 401X12
msgctxt "401X12"
msgid "SPECIAL?"
msgstr "SPECIAL?"

#: 401X13
msgctxt "401X13"
msgid "Auf jeden Fall, Herr Ripley."
msgstr "Auf jeden Fall, Herr Ripley."

#: 402R01
msgctxt "402R01"
msgid "Hello, my name is Ripley."
msgstr "Hello, my name is Ripley."

#: 402R02
msgctxt "402R02"
msgid "And this, I take it, is Ace of Spades Castle."
msgstr "And this, I take it, is Ace of Spades Castle."

#: 402R03
msgctxt "402R03"
msgid "I'm no common tourist."
msgstr "I'm no common tourist."

#: 402R04
msgctxt "402R04"
msgid "Sorry to bother you."
msgstr "Sorry to bother you."

#: 402R05
msgctxt "402R05"
msgid "I don't mean to be a pest."
msgstr "I don't mean to be a pest."

#: 402R06
msgctxt "402R06"
msgid "Just one more thing..."
msgstr "Just one more thing..."

#: 402R07
msgctxt "402R07"
msgid "Sorry."
msgstr "Sorry."

#: 402R08
msgctxt "402R08"
msgid "Magnificent castle! I'll bet there's a story behind the reoccurring motif."
msgstr "Magnificent castle! I'll bet there's a story behind the reoccurring motif."

#: 402R09
msgctxt "402R09"
msgid "It's shaped like the Ace of Spades."
msgstr "It's shaped like the Ace of Spades."

#: 402R10
msgctxt "402R10"
msgid "Beautifully tended flower bed."
msgstr "Beautifully tended flower bed."

#: 402R11
msgctxt "402R11"
msgid "There is a persistent architectural theme about this castle."
msgstr "There is a persistent architectural theme about this castle."

#: 402R12
msgctxt "402R12"
msgid "That man is one of the only things I've seen around here not shaped like the Ace of Spades."
msgstr "That man is one of the only things I've seen around here not shaped like the Ace of Spades."

#: 402R13
msgctxt "402R13"
msgid "Even casual conversation with Wolf could put a serious dent in my bank account."
msgstr "Even casual conversation with Wolf could put a serious dent in my bank account."

#: 402R14
msgctxt "402R14"
msgid "The ironwork of the gate is shaped like the ace of spades."
msgstr "The ironwork of the gate is shaped like the ace of spades."

#: 402R15
msgctxt "402R15"
msgid "The old wheelbarrow is not shaped like the Ace of Spades."
msgstr "The old wheelbarrow is not shaped like the Ace of Spades."

#: 402R16
msgctxt "402R16"
msgid "I'd better not meddle with the topiary, especially while he's wielding those shears."
msgstr "I'd better not meddle with the topiary, especially while he's wielding those shears."

#: 402R17
msgctxt "402R17"
msgid "It's a nice wheelbarrow, but I really don't have much use for it."
msgstr "It's a nice wheelbarrow, but I really don't have much use for it."

#: 402R18
msgctxt "402R18"
msgid "The topiary is firmly rooted in the ground."
msgstr "The topiary is firmly rooted in the ground."

#: 402R28
msgctxt "402R28"
msgid "Mr. Robert Ripley to see the Barrett."
msgstr "Mr. Robert Ripley to see the Barrett."

#: 402R29
msgctxt "402R29"
msgid "Hello again."
msgstr "Hello again."

#: 402R30
msgctxt "402R30"
msgid "Magnificent castle! If a bit one-note for my taste."
msgstr "Magnificent castle! If a bit one-note for my taste."

#: 402R31
msgctxt "402R31"
msgid "It's Robert Ripley again."
msgstr "It's Robert Ripley again."

#: 402R32
msgctxt "402R32"
msgid "NOPE!"
msgstr "NOPE!"

#: 402W01
msgctxt "402W01"
msgid "I am called Wolf."
msgstr "I am called Wolf."

#: 402W02
msgctxt "402W02"
msgid "Your powers of observation do you credit, Mein Herr, but the castle to the tourist is not open. I'm sorry."
msgstr "Your powers of observation do you credit, Mein Herr, but the castle to the tourist is not open. I'm sorry."

#: 402W03
msgctxt "402W03"
msgid "I'm a busy man, please let me work."
msgstr "I'm a busy man, please let me work."

#: 402W04
msgctxt "402W04"
msgid "I have no time for endless conversation."
msgstr "I have no time for endless conversation."

#: 402W05
msgctxt "402W05"
msgid "Find someone else to answer your questions."
msgstr "Find someone else to answer your questions."

#: 402W06
msgctxt "402W06"
msgid "My hair, my job is difficult enough. If you steal my tools, it will be impossible."
msgstr "My hair, my job is difficult enough. If you steal my tools, it will be impossible."

#: 402W07
msgctxt "402W07"
msgid "Danke, mein Herr. A man can never have too much small change."
msgstr "Danke, mein Herr. A man can never have too much small change."

#: 402W08
msgctxt "402W08"
msgid "Do I look like the Rothschild's bank? I have no use for foreign currency."
msgstr "Do I look like the Rothschild's bank? I have no use for foreign currency."

#: 402W09
msgctxt "402W09"
msgid "Yeah?"
msgstr "Yeah?"

#: 402W10
msgctxt "402W10"
msgid "Herr Ripley! The bell! I thought it might be you!"
msgstr "Herr Ripley! The bell! I thought it might be you!"

#: 402W11
msgctxt "402W11"
msgid "God in Himmel! The old baron!"
msgstr "God in Himmel! The old baron!"

#: 403R01
msgctxt "403R01"
msgid "The old baron is dead?"
msgstr "The old baron is dead?"

#: 403R02
msgctxt "403R02"
msgid "When did he die?"
msgstr "When did he die?"

#: 403R03
msgctxt "403R03"
msgid "February. Not long after Otto wrote me the letter. He mentions in it he was ill."
msgstr "February. Not long after Otto wrote me the letter. He mentions in it he was ill."

#: 403R04
msgctxt "403R04"
msgid "This graveyard would not be out of place in the works of Poe or that new fellow Lovecraft."
msgstr "This graveyard would not be out of place in the works of Poe or that new fellow Lovecraft."

#: 403R05
msgctxt "403R05"
msgid "That tomb is certainly impressive."
msgstr "That tomb is certainly impressive."

#: 403R05A
msgctxt "403R05A"
msgid "What's that in the corner? A bell?"
msgstr "What's that in the corner? A bell?"

#: 403R06
msgctxt "403R06"
msgid "A ventilation opening."
msgstr "A ventilation opening."

#: 403R06A
msgctxt "403R06A"
msgid "I remember reading that they are necessary to disperse certain gases."
msgstr "I remember reading that they are necessary to disperse certain gases."

#: 403R07
msgctxt "403R07"
msgid "A tomb with a doorbell? That can't be customary."
msgstr "A tomb with a doorbell? That can't be customary."

#: 403R08
msgctxt "403R08"
msgid "Sturdy stone urns filled with dirt."
msgstr "Sturdy stone urns filled with dirt."

#: 403R09
msgctxt "403R09"
msgid "That's quite a stone wall."
msgstr "That's quite a stone wall."

#: 403R09A
msgctxt "403R09A"
msgid "I wonder why it was built so high? To keep someone out or to keep something in?"
msgstr "I wonder why it was built so high? To keep someone out or to keep something in?"

#: 403R10
msgctxt "403R10"
msgid "Someone's left a ladder leaning against the tomb."
msgstr "Someone's left a ladder leaning against the tomb."

#: 403R11
msgctxt "403R11"
msgid "Here lies an atheist, all dressed up and no place to go."
msgstr "Here lies an atheist, all dressed up and no place to go."

#: 403R12
msgctxt "403R12"
msgid "I promise never to marry again, Jacob."
msgstr "I promise never to marry again, Jacob."

#: 403R13
msgctxt "403R13"
msgid "Beneath the stone, a lump of clay, lies the man called Peter Hannels, who early in the month of May, took off his winter flannels."
msgstr "Beneath the stone, a lump of clay, lies the man called Peter Hannels, who early in the month of May, took off his winter flannels."

#: 403R14
msgctxt "403R14"
msgid "Let the stone bear this headline. The writer below met one last deadline."
msgstr "Let the stone bear this headline. The writer below met one last deadline."

#: 403R15
msgctxt "403R15"
msgid "Here lies Lotta Dust."
msgstr "Here lies Lotta Dust."

#: 403R16
msgctxt "403R16"
msgid "Here lies the body of Gretel Sprechtestunnel, who pleased many a man and never vexed one, unlike the woman under the next stone."
msgstr "Here lies the body of Gretel Sprechtestunnel, who pleased many a man and never vexed one, unlike the woman under the next stone."

#: 403R17
msgctxt "403R17"
msgid "This stone was raised by Frieda's lord, not Frieda's virtues to record, for they are known to all the town. This stone was raised to keep her down."
msgstr "This stone was raised by Frieda's lord, not Frieda's virtues to record, for they are known to all the town. This stone was raised to keep her down."

#: 403R18
msgctxt "403R18"
msgid "His foot is slipped and he did fall. Help, help! he cried. And that was all."
msgstr "His foot is slipped and he did fall. Help, help! he cried. And that was all."

#: 403R19
msgctxt "403R19"
msgid "Here lies the body of Erika Bent. She kicked up her heels and away she went."
msgstr "Here lies the body of Erika Bent. She kicked up her heels and away she went."

#: 403R20
msgctxt "403R20"
msgid "Stephen and Time are now both even. Stephen beat Time, now Time beat Stephen."
msgstr "Stephen and Time are now both even. Stephen beat Time, now Time beat Stephen."

#: 403R21
msgctxt "403R21"
msgid "Here lies a poor toss tennis ball, racketed from spring to fall."
msgstr "Here lies a poor toss tennis ball, racketed from spring to fall."

#: 403R22
msgctxt "403R22"
msgid "At rest beneath this slab of stone lies Stingy Verner Viatt. He died one morning just at ten and saved a dinner by it."
msgstr "At rest beneath this slab of stone lies Stingy Verner Viatt. He died one morning just at ten and saved a dinner by it."

#: 403R23
msgctxt "403R23"
msgid "Here lies Yohan Yeast. Pardon me for not rising."
msgstr "Here lies Yohan Yeast. Pardon me for not rising."

#: 403R24
msgctxt "403R24"
msgid "Here lies the body of Heinrich Blake, stepped on the gas instead of the brake."
msgstr "Here lies the body of Heinrich Blake, stepped on the gas instead of the brake."

#: 403R25
msgctxt "403R25"
msgid "I started out in life with the idea that the world had an opening for me... and it did."
msgstr "I started out in life with the idea that the world had an opening for me... and it did."

#: 403R26
msgctxt "403R26"
msgid "It was a cough that carried him off. It was a coffin they carried him off in."
msgstr "It was a cough that carried him off. It was a coffin they carried him off in."

#: 403R27
msgctxt "403R27"
msgid "...sacred to the memory of Rolf Baumgartner, who died August 6, 1800. His widow, aged 24, lives at 7 Lindenstrasse and possesses every qualification for a good wife."
msgstr "...sacred to the memory of Rolf Baumgartner, who died August 6, 1800. His widow, aged 24, lives at 7 Lindenstrasse and possesses every qualification for a good wife."

#: 403R28
msgctxt "403R28"
msgid "The urns are filled with dirt and far too heavy."
msgstr "The urns are filled with dirt and far too heavy."

#: 403R29
msgctxt "403R29"
msgid "All I can really see from this angle is that wooden beam that runs the length of the tomb and a rope hanging down next to it."
msgstr "All I can really see from this angle is that wooden beam that runs the length of the tomb and a rope hanging down next to it."

#: 403R30
msgctxt "403R30"
msgid "I can't reach the bell."
msgstr "I can't reach the bell."

#: 403R31
msgctxt "403R31"
msgid "I'll need something less unwieldy to ring the bell."
msgstr "I'll need something less unwieldy to ring the bell."

#: 403R32
msgctxt "403R32"
msgid "I don't need the ladder to climb over the wall. There's a perfectly good gate."
msgstr "I don't need the ladder to climb over the wall. There's a perfectly good gate."

#: 403R33
msgctxt "403R33"
msgid "It would be more seemly to simply sketch the epitaphs."
msgstr "It would be more seemly to simply sketch the epitaphs."

#: 403R41
msgctxt "403R41"
msgid "The epitaphs on the tombstones might provide enough material for more than one cartoon."
msgstr "The epitaphs on the tombstones might provide enough material for more than one cartoon."

#: 403R42
msgctxt "403R42"
msgid "I've already sketched the best epitaphs."
msgstr "I've already sketched the best epitaphs."

#: 403R43
msgctxt "403R43"
msgid "Sorry to bother you."
msgstr "Sorry to bother you."

#: 403R44
msgctxt "403R44"
msgid "I don't mean to be a pest."
msgstr "I don't mean to be a pest."

#: 403R45
msgctxt "403R45"
msgid "Just one more thing..."
msgstr "Just one more thing..."

#: 403R46
msgctxt "403R46"
msgid "That must belong to the gardener."
msgstr "That must belong to the gardener."

#: 403R47
msgctxt "403R47"
msgid "Sorry."
msgstr "Sorry."

#: 403R48
msgctxt "403R48"
msgid "Ripley, you have more important things to do than tease an old man."
msgstr "Ripley, you have more important things to do than tease an old man."

#: 403R49
msgctxt "403R49"
msgid "I'll put one treat on the beam and save the rest for a rainy day."
msgstr "I'll put one treat on the beam and save the rest for a rainy day."

#: 403R50
msgctxt "403R50"
msgid "He just sits there like a turtle."
msgstr "He just sits there like a turtle."

#: 403R51
msgctxt "403R51"
msgid "Wow! Aided in one gulp! Little fella sure loves those things!"
msgstr "Wow! Aided in one gulp! Little fella sure loves those things!"

#: 403R52
msgctxt "403R52"
msgid "I've already got a turtle treat."
msgstr "I've already got a turtle treat."

#: 403R53
msgctxt "403R53"
msgid "The Gardener's Edger."
msgstr "The Gardener's Edger."

#: 403R54
msgctxt "403R54"
msgid "The shovel isn't quite long enough to reach the bell."
msgstr "The shovel isn't quite long enough to reach the bell."

#: 403R55
msgctxt "403R55"
msgid "A tomb with a doorbell. That's one for Ripley."
msgstr "A tomb with a doorbell. That's one for Ripley."

#: 403W01
msgctxt "403W01"
msgid "Otto, the sixth Baron von Celtsam, mein Herr."
msgstr "Otto, the sixth Baron von Celtsam, mein Herr."

#: 403W02
msgctxt "403W02"
msgid "Your powers of observation continue to amaze me."
msgstr "Your powers of observation continue to amaze me."

#: 403W03
msgctxt "403W03"
msgid "February. The Baron's son Albert has inherited the title."
msgstr "February. The Baron's son Albert has inherited the title."

#: 403W04
msgctxt "403W04"
msgid "Just so."
msgstr "Just so."

#: 403W05
msgctxt "403W05"
msgid "I'm a busy man, please let me work."
msgstr "I'm a busy man, please let me work."

#: 403W06
msgctxt "403W06"
msgid "I have no time for endless conversation."
msgstr "I have no time for endless conversation."

#: 403W07
msgctxt "403W07"
msgid "Find someone else to answer your questions."
msgstr "Find someone else to answer your questions."

#: 403W08
msgctxt "403W08"
msgid "Please do not touch my hair."
msgstr "Please do not touch my hair."

#: 403W09
msgctxt "403W09"
msgid "Danke, mein Herr. A man can never have too much small change."
msgstr "Danke, mein Herr. A man can never have too much small change."

#: 403W11
msgctxt "403W11"
msgid "Do not meddle with the bell, mein Herr. It is disrespectful to the old Baron."
msgstr "Do not meddle with the bell, mein Herr. It is disrespectful to the old Baron."

#: 403W12
msgctxt "403W12"
msgid "Yeah, you should be."
msgstr "Yeah, you should be."

#: 403W13
msgctxt "403W13"
msgid "You again! I should have guessed."
msgstr "You again! I should have guessed."

#: 403W14
msgctxt "403W14"
msgid "NO RESPECT!"
msgstr "NO RESPECT!"

#: 403W15
msgctxt "403W15"
msgid "What? Have you nothing better to do?"
msgstr "What? Have you nothing better to do?"

#: 403W16
msgctxt "403W16"
msgid "I am an old man, Mein Herr. Please! I have enough work to tire me without running here because of your foolishness!"
msgstr "I am an old man, Mein Herr. Please! I have enough work to tire me without running here because of your foolishness!"

#: 403W17
msgctxt "403W17"
msgid "This must stop. I will tell the Baron when he returns. He will not be allowed to set foot on the grounds again."
msgstr "This must stop. I will tell the Baron when he returns. He will not be allowed to set foot on the grounds again."

#: 403W18
msgctxt "403W18"
msgid "You have escaped from the asylum! Play your games! Ring it all you like! I will not come running here again!"
msgstr "You have escaped from the asylum! Play your games! Ring it all you like! I will not come running here again!"

#: 404R01
msgctxt "404R01"
msgid "I have a letter from his father. It's quite urgent."
msgstr "I have a letter from his father. It's quite urgent."

#: 404R02
msgctxt "404R02"
msgid "I have a letter from his father. It's quite urgent."
msgstr "I have a letter from his father. It's quite urgent."

#: 404R03
msgctxt "404R03"
msgid "I have a letter from him."
msgstr "I have a letter from him."

#: 404R04
msgctxt "404R04"
msgid "No, it's signed AUTO."
msgstr "No, it's signed AUTO."

#: 404R05
msgctxt "404R05"
msgid "Not long after he wrote me the letter, he mentions in it he was ill. I'm sorry."
msgstr "Not long after he wrote me the letter, he mentions in it he was ill. I'm sorry."

#: 404R06
msgctxt "404R06"
msgid "Maybe I better see the sun, then. It's quite urgent."
msgstr "Maybe I better see the sun, then. It's quite urgent."

#: 404R07
msgctxt "404R07"
msgid "The castle's entry is immense. I wonder how they clear the cobwebs."
msgstr "The castle's entry is immense. I wonder how they clear the cobwebs."

#: 404R08
msgctxt "404R08"
msgid "The section of wall the door is set into is an ace of spades."
msgstr "The section of wall the door is set into is an ace of spades."

#: 404R08A
msgctxt "404R08A"
msgid "The section of wall the door to the billiards room is set into is an ace of spades."
msgstr "The section of wall the door to the billiards room is set into is an ace of spades."

#: 404R09
msgctxt "404R09"
msgid "The section of wall the door to the sitting room is set into is an ace of spades."
msgstr "The section of wall the door to the sitting room is set into is an ace of spades."

#: 404R10
msgctxt "404R10"
msgid "The section of wall the door is set into is not an ace of spades, but there are spades carved into it."
msgstr "The section of wall the door is set into is not an ace of spades, but there are spades carved into it."

#: 404R11
msgctxt "404R11"
msgid "The section of wall that massive door is set into is an ace of spades."
msgstr "The section of wall that massive door is set into is an ace of spades."

#: 404R12
msgctxt "404R12"
msgid "The motif is tiresomely familiar."
msgstr "The motif is tiresomely familiar."

#: 404R13
msgctxt "404R13"
msgid "A former Baron von Seltsam, no doubt."
msgstr "A former Baron von Seltsam, no doubt."

#: 404R14
msgctxt "404R14"
msgid "An old and dusty portrait. Another von Seltsam, I suspect."
msgstr "An old and dusty portrait. Another von Seltsam, I suspect."

#: 404R15
msgctxt "404R15"
msgid "Ripley, you're a guest in this castle. It would be impolite to insist."
msgstr "Ripley, you're a guest in this castle. It would be impolite to insist."

#: 404R16
msgctxt "404R16"
msgid "Can you think of anything else that might help me?"
msgstr "Can you think of anything else that might help me?"

#: 404R17
msgctxt "404R17"
msgid "Any ideas where I should look next?"
msgstr "Any ideas where I should look next?"

#: 404R18
msgctxt "404R18"
msgid "Any old stories you haven't told me?"
msgstr "Any old stories you haven't told me?"

#: 404R19
msgctxt "404R19"
msgid "Anything else about the old baron I should know?"
msgstr "Anything else about the old baron I should know?"

#: 404R20
msgctxt "404R20"
msgid "What happened to Wolf? I don't see him anywhere."
msgstr "What happened to Wolf? I don't see him anywhere."

#: 404R21
msgctxt "404R21"
msgid "I'm sorry."
msgstr "I'm sorry."

#: 404R22
msgctxt "404R22"
msgid "Um... right."
msgstr "Um... right."

#: 404R23
msgctxt "404R23"
msgid "Sorry."
msgstr "Sorry."

#: 404R30
msgctxt "404R30"
msgid "The man is the picture of a trusted family retainer."
msgstr "The man is the picture of a trusted family retainer."

#: 404R30A
msgctxt "404R30A"
msgid "The brass work on the door strikes a familiar note."
msgstr "The brass work on the door strikes a familiar note."

#: 404U01
msgctxt "404U01"
msgid "From Mr. Albert, mein Herr?"
msgstr "From Mr. Albert, mein Herr?"

#: 404U02
msgctxt "404U02"
msgid "Ah, that would be the old Baron mine here. He died in February, I'm afraid."
msgstr "Ah, that would be the old Baron mine here. He died in February, I'm afraid."

#: 404U03
msgctxt "404U03"
msgid "As are we all, my dear. The old baron was well loved, as is his son."
msgstr "As are we all, my dear. The old baron was well loved, as is his son."

#: 404U04
msgctxt "404U04"
msgid "Please do wait in the sitting room, mein Herr."
msgstr "Please do wait in the sitting room, mein Herr."

#: 404U05
msgctxt "404U05"
msgid "I'm sorry, Mein Herr. Into that part of the castle you may not go."
msgstr "I'm sorry, Mein Herr. Into that part of the castle you may not go."

#: 404U06
msgctxt "404U06"
msgid "Nein."
msgstr "Nein."

#: 404U07
msgctxt "404U07"
msgid "I am sorry."
msgstr "I am sorry."

#: 404U08
msgctxt "404U08"
msgid "I have told you all I know."
msgstr "I have told you all I know."

#: 404U09
msgctxt "404U09"
msgid "I know nothing else."
msgstr "I know nothing else."

#: 404U10
msgctxt "404U10"
msgid "The gardener is gone, mein Herr. A bell rang from within the old baron's tomb. It was a false alarm, of course. The old fool didn't realize it and ran off somewhere. And now I'm having difficulty replacing him. The villagers are so superstitious, you know."
msgstr "The gardener is gone, mein Herr. A bell rang from within the old baron's tomb. It was a false alarm, of course. The old fool didn't realize it and ran off somewhere. And now I'm having difficulty replacing him. The villagers are so superstitious, you know."

#: 404U11
msgctxt "404U11"
msgid "It is not your fault."
msgstr "It is not your fault."

#: 404U12
msgctxt "404U12"
msgid "Hey Ripley, I happened to look into the billiards room just now. I saw you take one of the balls. Pleased to leave the ball where you found it?"
msgstr "Hey Ripley, I happened to look into the billiards room just now. I saw you take one of the balls. Pleased to leave the ball where you found it?"

#: 404U13
msgctxt "404U13"
msgid "Hey Ripley, I cannot allow you to leave with Sir Barron's property. Please to put the ball back."
msgstr "Hey Ripley, I cannot allow you to leave with Sir Barron's property. Please to put the ball back."

#: 405B01
msgctxt "405B01"
msgid "Mr. Ripley, Von Seltsam."
msgstr "Mr. Ripley, Von Seltsam."

#: 405B01A
msgctxt "405B01A"
msgid "Please, forgive the tennis togs. The third set was more of a struggle than I expected."
msgstr "Please, forgive the tennis togs. The third set was more of a struggle than I expected."

#: 405B02
msgctxt "405B02"
msgid "You knew my father, I believe."
msgstr "You knew my father, I believe."

#: 405B03
msgctxt "405B03"
msgid "Indeed. This house alone is testament to that."
msgstr "Indeed. This house alone is testament to that."

#: 405B04
msgctxt "405B04"
msgid "Ah, you're that Mr. Ripley. I am also a fan."
msgstr "Ah, you're that Mr. Ripley. I am also a fan."

#: 405B05
msgctxt "405B05"
msgid "The first emperor of China, Master Lu."
msgstr "The first emperor of China, Master Lu."

#: 405B05A
msgctxt "405B05A"
msgid "As you might have gathered, my father was an orientalist of some note. It's a pity he died before he was able to pursue this line of research. It sounds fascinating."
msgstr "As you might have gathered, my father was an orientalist of some note. It's a pity he died before he was able to pursue this line of research. It sounds fascinating."

#: 405R01
msgctxt "405R01"
msgid "I never had the pleasure of meeting him, I'm afraid. By all accounts, he was quite a fellow."
msgstr "I never had the pleasure of meeting him, I'm afraid. By all accounts, he was quite a fellow."

#: 405R02
msgctxt "405R02"
msgid "He wrote me this shortly before he died."
msgstr "He wrote me this shortly before he died."

#: 405R03
msgctxt "405R03"
msgid "Thank you."
msgstr "Thank you."

#: 405R04
msgctxt "405R04"
msgid "Castles were designed to make you feel small."
msgstr "Castles were designed to make you feel small."

#: 405R05
msgctxt "405R05"
msgid "Shaped like the Ace of Spades. How quaint."
msgstr "Shaped like the Ace of Spades. How quaint."

#: 405R06
msgctxt "405R06"
msgid "If there wasn't an ace of spades in the windows, I would have been disappointed."
msgstr "If there wasn't an ace of spades in the windows, I would have been disappointed."

#: 405R07
msgctxt "405R07"
msgid "Even animals cooperate with the Baron's unique decorating scheme."
msgstr "Even animals cooperate with the Baron's unique decorating scheme."

#: 405R08
msgctxt "405R08"
msgid "What would the wall of a castle be without some poor decapitated beast hung on it?"
msgstr "What would the wall of a castle be without some poor decapitated beast hung on it?"

#: 405R09
msgctxt "405R09"
msgid "The Baron's coat of arms contains the Ace of Spades. Who would have guessed?"
msgstr "The Baron's coat of arms contains the Ace of Spades. Who would have guessed?"

#: 405R10
msgctxt "405R10"
msgid "They would need chandeliers that big to light this room at night."
msgstr "They would need chandeliers that big to light this room at night."

#: 405R11
msgctxt "405R11"
msgid "An impressive collection of books in many languages. Most of them appear to be science texts or about the Orient."
msgstr "An impressive collection of books in many languages. Most of them appear to be science texts or about the Orient."

#: 405R12
msgctxt "405R12"
msgid "The sofa looks comfortable enough to sleep on."
msgstr "The sofa looks comfortable enough to sleep on."

#: 405R13
msgctxt "405R13"
msgid "The chairs and sofa constitute an island of comfort in this cold room."
msgstr "The chairs and sofa constitute an island of comfort in this cold room."

#: 405R14
msgctxt "405R14"
msgid "A library table. There's a journal here written by the young baron."
msgstr "A library table. There's a journal here written by the young baron."

#: 405R14A
msgctxt "405R14A"
msgid "Hmm. Notes on the latest racing cars, clippings of the tennis tournament he won. Oh, nothing here concerning the old Baron, unfortunately."
msgstr "Hmm. Notes on the latest racing cars, clippings of the tennis tournament he won. Oh, nothing here concerning the old Baron, unfortunately."

#: 405R15
msgctxt "405R15"
msgid "The sofa looks comfortable enough to sleep on. There seems to be something sticking out from underneath it."
msgstr "The sofa looks comfortable enough to sleep on. There seems to be something sticking out from underneath it."

#: 405R16
msgctxt "405R16"
msgid "You need thick rugs like that to temper the cold of the castle's floors."
msgstr "You need thick rugs like that to temper the cold of the castle's floors."

#: 405R17
msgctxt "405R17"
msgid "It looks like money."
msgstr "It looks like money."

#: 405R18
msgctxt "405R18"
msgid "While it would make a nice companion for my cow with a spot shaped like Ireland, the Baron has explained it must remain in the castle. I'll respect his wishes."
msgstr "While it would make a nice companion for my cow with a spot shaped like Ireland, the Baron has explained it must remain in the castle. I'll respect his wishes."

#: 405R19
msgctxt "405R19"
msgid "I suppose you could say someone has already taken the deer's head. Unfortunately, that's not much of an oddity."
msgstr "I suppose you could say someone has already taken the deer's head. Unfortunately, that's not much of an oddity."

#: 405R20
msgctxt "405R20"
msgid "They're bolted to the wall. Medieval weapons don't do me much good anyway."
msgstr "They're bolted to the wall. Medieval weapons don't do me much good anyway."

#: 405R21
msgctxt "405R21"
msgid "I'd love to spend time browsing through the baron's library. Maybe when I have more time, I'll ask him if I might."
msgstr "I'd love to spend time browsing through the baron's library. Maybe when I have more time, I'll ask him if I might."

#: 405R22
msgctxt "405R22"
msgid "The furniture is more comfortable to sit on than to lug around."
msgstr "The furniture is more comfortable to sit on than to lug around."

#: 405R23
msgctxt "405R23"
msgid "The Baron needs his journal to recount his adventures in the world of sport."
msgstr "The Baron needs his journal to recount his adventures in the world of sport."

#: 405R24
msgctxt "405R24"
msgid "Goodness gracious, it's a fifty million mark note. Unfortunately, today it's as worthless as Confederate currency. I'm told doctors used these during the Great War as prescription blanks."
msgstr "Goodness gracious, it's a fifty million mark note. Unfortunately, today it's as worthless as Confederate currency. I'm told doctors used these during the Great War as prescription blanks."

#: 405R30
msgctxt "405R30"
msgid "The brass work on the door strikes a familiar note."
msgstr "The brass work on the door strikes a familiar note."

#: 405R31
msgctxt "405R31"
msgid "If the baron wants the door closed, I'm sure he'll have his butler do it."
msgstr "If the baron wants the door closed, I'm sure he'll have his butler do it."

#: 406R01
msgctxt "406R01"
msgid "So the Baron believes the curse of the Romanov Emerald taints this room. It all looks pretty harmless to me."
msgstr "So the Baron believes the curse of the Romanov Emerald taints this room. It all looks pretty harmless to me."

#: 406R02
msgctxt "406R02"
msgid "The billiard table is a beauty. I used to play a little 8 ball myself when I was a lad."
msgstr "The billiard table is a beauty. I used to play a little 8 ball myself when I was a lad."

#: 406R03
msgctxt "406R03"
msgid "A darkboard cabinet, just like the one at my favorite pub on Second Avenue."
msgstr "A darkboard cabinet, just like the one at my favorite pub on Second Avenue."

#: 406R04
msgctxt "406R04"
msgid "The lamp illuminates every corner of the billiard table."
msgstr "The lamp illuminates every corner of the billiard table."

#: 406R05
msgctxt "406R05"
msgid "Everything necessary for a challenging game of Billiards."
msgstr "Everything necessary for a challenging game of Billiards."

#: 406R06
msgctxt "406R06"
msgid "The cabinet is closed."
msgstr "The cabinet is closed."

#: 406R07
msgctxt "406R07"
msgid "Golly!"
msgstr "Golly!"

#: 406R07A
msgctxt "406R07A"
msgid "Maybe the room is unlucky after all."
msgstr "Maybe the room is unlucky after all."

#: 406R08
msgctxt "406R08"
msgid "That Ace of Spades looks slightly different than the rest of the wallpaper design."
msgstr "That Ace of Spades looks slightly different than the rest of the wallpaper design."

#: 406R09
msgctxt "406R09"
msgid "The old baron's writing desk. Some books, and a piece of paper. None of any use, I'm afraid."
msgstr "The old baron's writing desk. Some books, and a piece of paper. None of any use, I'm afraid."

#: 406R09A
msgctxt "406R09A"
msgid "The old baron's writing desk."
msgstr "The old baron's writing desk."

#: 406R10
msgctxt "406R10"
msgid "A red billiard ball. Luckily for anyone wanting to play, it is not shaped like the ace of spades."
msgstr "A red billiard ball. Luckily for anyone wanting to play, it is not shaped like the ace of spades."

#: 406R11
msgctxt "406R11"
msgid "A table with a lamp on it."
msgstr "A table with a lamp on it."

#: 406R12
msgctxt "406R12"
msgid "An uncomfortable looking chair of hard wood."
msgstr "An uncomfortable looking chair of hard wood."

#: 406R13
msgctxt "406R13"
msgid "The person in that portrait looks familiar."
msgstr "The person in that portrait looks familiar."

#: 406R14
msgctxt "406R14"
msgid "A few papers referring to household matters."
msgstr "A few papers referring to household matters."

#: 406R15
msgctxt "406R15"
msgid "Great Caesar's Ghost! It's addressed to me!"
msgstr "Great Caesar's Ghost! It's addressed to me!"

#: 406R16
msgctxt "406R16"
msgid "I wonder what those keys unlock."
msgstr "I wonder what those keys unlock."

#: 406R17
msgctxt "406R17"
msgid "The papers won't help me, I'm afraid."
msgstr "The papers won't help me, I'm afraid."

#: 406R18
msgctxt "406R18"
msgid "Mr. Ripley, this interesting item came into my possession quite by accident last year while I was in China. I thought it might amuse you. To the best of my knowledge, it is the cheapest stamp ever struck, worth but four thousandths of one of your American pennies. Please accept it with my compliments. I look forward to meeting you in person soon to plan our great adventure tackling the mysteries of the First Emperor's tomb. Signed Otto, 6 Baron von Seltzer."
msgstr "Mr. Ripley, this interesting item came into my possession quite by accident last year while I was in China. I thought it might amuse you. To the best of my knowledge, it is the cheapest stamp ever struck, worth but four thousandths of one of your American pennies. Please accept it with my compliments. I look forward to meeting you in person soon to plan our great adventure tackling the mysteries of the First Emperor's tomb. Signed Otto, 6 Baron von Seltzer."

#: 406R18A
msgctxt "406R18A"
msgid "To the best of my knowledge, it is the cheapest stamp ever struck, worth but four thousandths of one of your American pennies. Please accept it with my compliments."
msgstr "To the best of my knowledge, it is the cheapest stamp ever struck, worth but four thousandths of one of your American pennies. Please accept it with my compliments."

#: 406R18B
msgctxt "406R18B"
msgid "I look forward to meeting you in person soon to plan our great adventure tackling the mysteries of the First Emperor's tomb. Signed Otto, 6th Baron von Celtsam."
msgstr "I look forward to meeting you in person soon to plan our great adventure tackling the mysteries of the First Emperor's tomb. Signed Otto, 6th Baron von Celtsam."

#: 406R18C
msgctxt "406R18C"
msgid "Mr. Ripley, this interesting item came into my possession quite by accident last year while I was in China. I thought it might amuse you. To the best of my knowledge, it is the cheapest stamp ever struck, worth but four thousandths of one of your American pennies. Please accept it with my compliments. I look forward to meeting you in person soon to plan our great adventure tackling the mysteries of the First Emperor's tomb. Signed Otto, 6th Baron von Seltsam. I would have enjoyed seeing this thing through with you, Baron. I'm sorry it wasn't meant to be."
msgstr "Mr. Ripley, this interesting item came into my possession quite by accident last year while I was in China. I thought it might amuse you. To the best of my knowledge, it is the cheapest stamp ever struck, worth but four thousandths of one of your American pennies. Please accept it with my compliments. I look forward to meeting you in person soon to plan our great adventure tackling the mysteries of the First Emperor's tomb. Signed Otto, 6th Baron von Seltsam. I would have enjoyed seeing this thing through with you, Baron. I'm sorry it wasn't meant to be."

#: 406R19
msgctxt "406R19"
msgid "Worth only a fraction of a cent! How wonderful!"
msgstr "Worth only a fraction of a cent! How wonderful!"

#: 406R20
msgctxt "406R20"
msgid "LOCKED."
msgstr "LOCKED."

#: 406R21
msgctxt "406R21"
msgid "I wonder what's in there."
msgstr "I wonder what's in there."

#: 406R23
msgctxt "406R23"
msgid "The Ace of Spades is missing from this deck of cards."
msgstr "The Ace of Spades is missing from this deck of cards."

#: 406R23A
msgctxt "406R23A"
msgid "Must be where that card on the wall came from."
msgstr "Must be where that card on the wall came from."

#: 406R24
msgctxt "406R24"
msgid "The deck is incomplete, useless for playing games."
msgstr "The deck is incomplete, useless for playing games."

#: 406R25
msgctxt "406R25"
msgid "Parcheesi, Mahjong, Chinese checkers, and that new game, Monopoly."
msgstr "Parcheesi, Mahjong, Chinese checkers, and that new game, Monopoly."

#: 406R25A
msgctxt "406R25A"
msgid "It's rather fun. I wonder if it will catch on."
msgstr "It's rather fun. I wonder if it will catch on."

#: 406R26
msgctxt "406R26"
msgid "None of the keys fit. Well, I didn't have time for darts anyway."
msgstr "None of the keys fit. Well, I didn't have time for darts anyway."

#: 406R27
msgctxt "406R27"
msgid "None of the keys fit. I prefer pocket billiards myself."
msgstr "None of the keys fit. I prefer pocket billiards myself."

#: 406R28
msgctxt "406R28"
msgid "Curious. The table suddenly seems to be on an angle."
msgstr "Curious. The table suddenly seems to be on an angle."

#: 406R29
msgctxt "406R29"
msgid "I do believe a red ball has been added to the rack. That must be the ball I put into the slot."
msgstr "I do believe a red ball has been added to the rack. That must be the ball I put into the slot."

#: 406R30
msgctxt "406R30"
msgid "Stairs. Baron, you're a wily old coot, but I think I'm on to you."
msgstr "Stairs. Baron, you're a wily old coot, but I think I'm on to you."

#: 406R40
msgctxt "406R40"
msgid "The curse of the Romanov Emerald should no longer haunt this room. It should make playing games in here a bit more fun."
msgstr "The curse of the Romanov Emerald should no longer haunt this room. It should make playing games in here a bit more fun."

#: 406R41
msgctxt "406R41"
msgid "Your secret is safe with me, Baron."
msgstr "Your secret is safe with me, Baron."

#: 406R42
msgctxt "406R42"
msgid "So a ball dropped into the hole in the smoking hutch pops out there. Ingenious!"
msgstr "So a ball dropped into the hole in the smoking hutch pops out there. Ingenious!"

#: 406R43
msgctxt "406R43"
msgid "Seven years, bad luck!"
msgstr "Seven years, bad luck!"

#: 406R44
msgctxt "406R44"
msgid "That Ace of Spades conceals the switch to the old Baron's smoking hatch."
msgstr "That Ace of Spades conceals the switch to the old Baron's smoking hatch."

#: 406R44A
msgctxt "406R44A"
msgid "That Ace of Spades conceals the switch."
msgstr "That Ace of Spades conceals the switch."

#: 406R45
msgctxt "406R45"
msgid "I know I've seen that face somewhere before."
msgstr "I know I've seen that face somewhere before."

#: 406R46
msgctxt "406R46"
msgid "That useless deck of 51 cards is in there."
msgstr "That useless deck of 51 cards is in there."

#: 406R47
msgctxt "406R47"
msgid "There's a drawer in the games cabinet."
msgstr "There's a drawer in the games cabinet."

#: 406R48
msgctxt "406R48"
msgid "There's a drawer in the writing desk."
msgstr "There's a drawer in the writing desk."

#: 406R49
msgctxt "406R49"
msgid "A vertical rack of billiard balls with a hole at the top."
msgstr "A vertical rack of billiard balls with a hole at the top."

#: 406R50
msgctxt "406R50"
msgid "A two-button switch. Fascinating."
msgstr "A two-button switch. Fascinating."

#: 407R01
msgctxt "407R01"
msgid "The Baron's private laboratory. Other than the Baron, I may well be the only other living soul ever to enter this room."
msgstr "The Baron's private laboratory. Other than the Baron, I may well be the only other living soul ever to enter this room."

#: 407R02
msgctxt "407R02"
msgid "Shut tight. I have a sneaking suspicion it's not going to be as easy to get out of here as it was to get in."
msgstr "Shut tight. I have a sneaking suspicion it's not going to be as easy to get out of here as it was to get in."

#: 407R03
msgctxt "407R03"
msgid "I wonder what experiments that eccentric old gentleman conducted at this table."
msgstr "I wonder what experiments that eccentric old gentleman conducted at this table."

#: 407R04
msgctxt "407R04"
msgid "There's a drawer in the work table."
msgstr "There's a drawer in the work table."

#: 407R05
msgctxt "407R05"
msgid "The sink has been stained with countless chemicals."
msgstr "The sink has been stained with countless chemicals."

#: 407R06
msgctxt "407R06"
msgid "A rubber plug."
msgstr "A rubber plug."

#: 407R07
msgctxt "407R07"
msgid "A faucet."
msgstr "A faucet."

#: 407R08
msgctxt "407R08"
msgid "The Fawcett Handle."
msgstr "The Fawcett Handle."

#: 407R09
msgctxt "407R09"
msgid "It's some sort of pivot bolted to the tabletop."
msgstr "It's some sort of pivot bolted to the tabletop."

#: 407R10
msgctxt "407R10"
msgid "There are two brass nozzles protruding through the tabletop."
msgstr "There are two brass nozzles protruding through the tabletop."

#: 407R11
msgctxt "407R11"
msgid "A piston is set into the table. Beneath the table, tubing runs from the piston to one of two brass nozzles. A second tube runs up through the table to an axle of some sort. The axle is attached to a large gear."
msgstr "A piston is set into the table. Beneath the table, tubing runs from the piston to one of two brass nozzles. A second tube runs up through the table to an axle of some sort. The axle is attached to a large gear."

#: 407R12
msgctxt "407R12"
msgid "A pump with a plunger rod extending from it. The pump is connected to a compressed air tank."
msgstr "A pump with a plunger rod extending from it. The pump is connected to a compressed air tank."

#: 407R12A
msgctxt "407R12A"
msgid "The pump is connected to a compressed air tank."
msgstr "The pump is connected to a compressed air tank."

#: 407R13
