#: 407R99F
msgctxt "407R99F"
msgid "Uh-oh."
msgstr "Uh-oh."

#: 407R99G
msgctxt "407R99G"
msgid "A series of four number wheels with corresponding buttons beneath them."
msgstr "A series of four number wheels with corresponding buttons beneath them."

#: 407R99H
msgctxt "407R99H"
msgid "The garden hose doesn't fit on that end of the faucet pipe."
msgstr "The garden hose doesn't fit on that end of the faucet pipe."

#: 407R99I
msgctxt "407R99I"
msgid "The surgical tube doesn't fit on the faucet pipe."
msgstr "The surgical tube doesn't fit on the faucet pipe."

#: 407R99J
msgctxt "407R99J"
msgid "There's no need to do that anymore. The glass jar is empty."
msgstr "There's no need to do that anymore. The glass jar is empty."

#: 407R99K
msgctxt "407R99K"
msgid "A piston is attached to the wall."
msgstr "A piston is attached to the wall."

#: 407R99L
msgctxt "407R99L"
msgid "A faucet stem."
msgstr "A faucet stem."

#: 407R99M
msgctxt "407R99M"
msgid "Drain seems to work."
msgstr "Drain seems to work."

#: 407R99N
msgctxt "407R99N"
msgid "The water will undoubtedly geyser up, but I don't see how that will help me very much."
msgstr "The water will undoubtedly geyser up, but I don't see how that will help me very much."

#: 407R99O
msgctxt "407R99O"
msgid "I don't really want to reduce the periodic table to soggy pulp."
msgstr "I don't really want to reduce the periodic table to soggy pulp."

#: 407R99P
msgctxt "407R99P"
msgid "The garden hose and surgical tube won't reach."
msgstr "The garden hose and surgical tube won't reach."

#: 407R99Q
msgctxt "407R99Q"
msgid "There's not enough room for the horn to fit under the faucet pipe."
msgstr "There's not enough room for the horn to fit under the faucet pipe."

#: 407R99R
msgctxt "407R99R"
msgid "The piston is attached to a large gear."
msgstr "The piston is attached to a large gear."

#: 408R01
msgctxt "408R01"
msgid "The side of the castle continues the excessive architectural theme."
msgstr "The side of the castle continues the excessive architectural theme."

#: 408R02
msgctxt "408R02"
msgid "Shaped like the Ace of Spades."
msgstr "Shaped like the Ace of Spades."

#: 408R03
msgctxt "408R03"
msgid "The windows are shaped like the ace of spades. Imagine that!"
msgstr "The windows are shaped like the ace of spades. Imagine that!"

#: 408R04
msgctxt "408R04"
msgid "A sundial? Gosh, I didn't realize it was so late."
msgstr "A sundial? Gosh, I didn't realize it was so late."

#: 408R05
msgctxt "408R05"
msgid "An inexplicable oversight has left the bush looking relatively normal."
msgstr "An inexplicable oversight has left the bush looking relatively normal."

#: 408R06
msgctxt "408R06"
msgid "The topiary is firmly rooted in the ground."
msgstr "The topiary is firmly rooted in the ground."

#: 408R07
msgctxt "408R07"
msgid "I see no reason to fiddle with any of the topiaries right now."
msgstr "I see no reason to fiddle with any of the topiaries right now."

#: 408R08
msgctxt "408R08"
msgid "If I need to tell time, I'll get a watch."
msgstr "If I need to tell time, I'll get a watch."

#: 408R09
msgctxt "408R09"
msgid "The sundial seems to be keeping correct time. It doesn't need adjusting."
msgstr "The sundial seems to be keeping correct time. It doesn't need adjusting."

#: 408R10
msgctxt "408R10"
msgid "These windows don't open. And anyway, I expect I'd better use the door."
msgstr "These windows don't open. And anyway, I expect I'd better use the door."

#: 408R20
msgctxt "408R20"
msgid "A sturdy plank."
msgstr "A sturdy plank."

#: 408R21
msgctxt "408R21"
msgid "He must have nightmares about that shape."
msgstr "He must have nightmares about that shape."

#: 408R22
msgctxt "408R22"
msgid "Sorry to bother you."
msgstr "Sorry to bother you."

#: 408R23
msgctxt "408R23"
msgid "I don't mean to be a pest."
msgstr "I don't mean to be a pest."

#: 408R24
msgctxt "408R24"
msgid "Just one more thing..."
msgstr "Just one more thing..."

#: 408R25
msgctxt "408R25"
msgid "Excuse me, but I've noticed how meticulously you attend to your topiaries."
msgstr "Excuse me, but I've noticed how meticulously you attend to your topiaries."

#: 408R26
msgctxt "408R26"
msgid "Well, I hate to be the bearer of bad news, but the bush out front is a mess."
msgstr "Well, I hate to be the bearer of bad news, but the bush out front is a mess."

#: 408R27
msgctxt "408R27"
msgid "It's happened again. Utopiary out front is a mess."
msgstr "It's happened again. Utopiary out front is a mess."

#: 408R28
msgctxt "408R28"
msgid "I'd better not meddle with the topiary, especially while he's wielding those shears."
msgstr "I'd better not meddle with the topiary, especially while he's wielding those shears."

#: 408R29
msgctxt "408R29"
msgid "Wolf is using the plank to help trim the shrub."
msgstr "Wolf is using the plank to help trim the shrub."

#: 408R30
msgctxt "408R30"
msgid "I can't steal the man's edger right from under his nose."
msgstr "I can't steal the man's edger right from under his nose."

#: 408R31
msgctxt "408R31"
msgid "Eh... eh... Phew..."
msgstr "Eh... eh... Phew..."

#: 408R32
msgctxt "408R32"
msgid "The old baron sure had a few cards up his sleeve."
msgstr "The old baron sure had a few cards up his sleeve."

#: 408R34
msgctxt "408R34"
msgid "If there is a trick to entering the secret passage from out here, I don't have time to find it."
msgstr "If there is a trick to entering the secret passage from out here, I don't have time to find it."

#: 408R35
msgctxt "408R35"
msgid "The Gardener's Edger."
msgstr "The Gardener's Edger."

#: 408R36
msgctxt "408R36"
msgid "While a spot of gardening might be quite relaxing, I really don't have time right now."
msgstr "While a spot of gardening might be quite relaxing, I really don't have time right now."

#: 408W01
msgctxt "408W01"
msgid "I'm a busy man, please let me work."
msgstr "I'm a busy man, please let me work."

#: 408W02
msgctxt "408W02"
msgid "I have no time for endless conversation."
msgstr "I have no time for endless conversation."

#: 408W03
msgctxt "408W03"
msgid "Find someone else to answer your questions."
msgstr "Find someone else to answer your questions."

#: 408W04
msgctxt "408W04"
msgid "Yeah, each one must be precisely shaped."
msgstr "Yeah, each one must be precisely shaped."

#: 408W05
msgctxt "408W05"
msgid "I only just trimmed it. Ah, the plants. They hate me, you know."
msgstr "I only just trimmed it. Ah, the plants. They hate me, you know."

#: 408W06
msgctxt "408W06"
msgid "This job is a nightmare and there is no escape. I just keep doing the same things over and over again."
msgstr "This job is a nightmare and there is no escape. I just keep doing the same things over and over again."

#: 408W07
msgctxt "408W07"
msgid "Duncan, my hair. A man can never have too much small change."
msgstr "Duncan, my hair. A man can never have too much small change."

#: 409R01A
msgctxt "409R01A"
msgid "You thought he might have succeeded in his quest after all, eh Baron? If we could uncover a sample, or even the formula, you could duplicate it in your secret laboratory."
msgstr "You thought he might have succeeded in his quest after all, eh Baron? If we could uncover a sample, or even the formula, you could duplicate it in your secret laboratory."

#: 409R01B
msgctxt "409R01B"
msgid "It's the kind of dream every man flirts with when the road shortens and the end is near. But that's all it is. A dream. And a waste of time. Better to face our mortality, I think. To live the years we're granted as fully as we can."
msgstr "It's the kind of dream every man flirts with when the road shortens and the end is near. But that's all it is. A dream. And a waste of time. Better to face our mortality, I think. To live the years we're granted as fully as we can."

#: 409R01C
msgctxt "409R01C"
msgid "The Chinese symbol for long life on every wall. I think I finally understand the old baron's interest in Liu. Even with all his safeguards, how could the baron prevent his being buried alive? How could he outwit death? With Liu's elixir of life."
msgstr "The Chinese symbol for long life on every wall. I think I finally understand the old baron's interest in Liu. Even with all his safeguards, how could the baron prevent his being buried alive? How could he outwit death? With Liu's elixir of life."

#: 409R02A
msgctxt "409R02A"
msgid "If he has come to realize the true import of this key and how it relates to the tablet in the Hall of Classics, who knows whom he may tell? The Japanese imperialists would dearly love to get their hands on the emerald seal. I grow increasingly weak, I'm afraid. So you, the one reading this, may now understand the lengths I went to to take my knowledge to the grave with me."
msgstr "If he has come to realize the true import of this key and how it relates to the tablet in the Hall of Classics, who knows whom he may tell? The Japanese imperialists would dearly love to get their hands on the emerald seal. I grow increasingly weak, I'm afraid. So you, the one reading this, may now understand the lengths I went to to take my knowledge to the grave with me."

#: 409R02B
msgctxt "409R02B"
msgid "If you do acquire the Emerald Seal, I beg of you, don't turn its power to world domination. Find it in your heart to use the seal only in the name of good. Then I can sleep my long sleep in peace. Signed, Otto VI Baron von Seltsam."
msgstr "If you do acquire the Emerald Seal, I beg of you, don't turn its power to world domination. Find it in your heart to use the seal only in the name of good. Then I can sleep my long sleep in peace. Signed, Otto VI Baron von Seltsam."

#: 409R02C
msgctxt "409R02C"
msgid "I'll do my best, Baron. I promise you."
msgstr "I'll do my best, Baron. I promise you."

#: 409R02D
msgctxt "409R02D"
msgid "This ceramic mask is, I believe, to be placed over Liu's tablet to indicate what portion of the tablet must be deciphered. It was sent to me by a Japanese gentleman I employed in Shanghai to seek out any information on the First Emperor's tomb. He wrote that it was found in a curio shop and obtained quite cheaply. I've heard nothing further from him. His silence is troubling."
msgstr "This ceramic mask is, I believe, to be placed over Liu's tablet to indicate what portion of the tablet must be deciphered. It was sent to me by a Japanese gentleman I employed in Shanghai to seek out any information on the First Emperor's tomb. He wrote that it was found in a curio shop and obtained quite cheaply. I've heard nothing further from him. His silence is troubling."

#: 409R03A
msgctxt "409R03A"
msgid "So this is the key at last, an overlay for loose tablet."
msgstr "So this is the key at last, an overlay for loose tablet."

#: 409R04A
msgctxt "409R04A"
msgid "Now I need all the scripts necessary to translate the tablet."
msgstr "Now I need all the scripts necessary to translate the tablet."

#: 409R05A
msgctxt "409R05A"
msgid "With the three scripts in this key, I now have everything I need to learn the secret of Master Lu's tablet."
msgstr "With the three scripts in this key, I now have everything I need to learn the secret of Master Lu's tablet."

#: 409R06
msgctxt "409R06"
msgid "Now, how the heck do I get you down?"
msgstr "Now, how the heck do I get you down?"

#: 409W11A
msgctxt "409W11A"
msgid "The bear! The old barren! The old barren!"
msgstr "The bear! The old barren! The old barren!"

#: 410R01
msgctxt "410R01"
msgid "Gosh, what a peculiar looking place!"
msgstr "Gosh, what a peculiar looking place!"

#: 410R02
msgctxt "410R02"
msgid "What does that mean?"
msgstr "What does that mean?"

#: 410R03
msgctxt "410R03"
msgid "Somehow the name fits."
msgstr "Somehow the name fits."

#: 410R04
msgctxt "410R04"
msgid "The so-called Free City of Danzig, perched precariously between Poland and Nazi Germany. How much longer will it remain free?"
msgstr "The so-called Free City of Danzig, perched precariously between Poland and Nazi Germany. How much longer will it remain free?"

#: 410R05
msgctxt "410R05"
msgid "Ace of Spades Castle, home to generations of barons von Seltsam."
msgstr "Ace of Spades Castle, home to generations of barons von Seltsam."

#: 410T01
msgctxt "410T01"
msgid "That is SlashBegas."
msgstr "That is SlashBegas."

#: 410T02
msgctxt "410T02"
msgid "Castle of the Apes of Spades, my dear."
msgstr "Castle of the Apes of Spades, my dear."

#: 413R01
msgctxt "413R01"
msgid "Gosh, my whole life just seemed to pass before my eyes. Wait a minute. That was my life. I'd sure like another chance."
msgstr "Gosh, my whole life just seemed to pass before my eyes. Wait a minute. That was my life. I'd sure like another chance."

#: 413R02
msgctxt "413R02"
msgid "In the big house they stuck killer skelling in my cell. Three days later I was history. I'd sure like another chance."
msgstr "In the big house they stuck killer skelling in my cell. Three days later I was history. I'd sure like another chance."

#: 456R01
msgctxt "456R01"
msgid "Neptune on, you guessed it, a large ace of spades playing card."
msgstr "Neptune on, you guessed it, a large ace of spades playing card."

#: 456R02
msgctxt "456R02"
msgid "That Ace of Spades doesn't really match the others."
msgstr "That Ace of Spades doesn't really match the others."

#: 456R03
msgctxt "456R03"
msgid "A two-button switch."
msgstr "A two-button switch."

#: 456R04
msgctxt "456R04"
msgid "A box of fine Cubano cigars, judging by the ace of spades on the box, I'd bet they're the old baron's special blend."
msgstr "A box of fine Cubano cigars, judging by the ace of spades on the box, I'd bet they're the old baron's special blend."

#: 456R04A
msgctxt "456R04A"
msgid "Judging by the ace of spades on the box, I bet they're the old baron's special blend."
msgstr "Judging by the ace of spades on the box, I bet they're the old baron's special blend."

#: 456R04B
msgctxt "456R04B"
msgid "A box of fine Cubano cigars."
msgstr "A box of fine Cubano cigars."

#: 456R05
msgctxt "456R05"
msgid "I don't quite know what I'll need it for, especially being a non-smoker, but one is plenty."
msgstr "I don't quite know what I'll need it for, especially being a non-smoker, but one is plenty."

#: 456R06
msgctxt "456R06"
msgid "A built-in lighter."
msgstr "A built-in lighter."

#: 456R07
msgctxt "456R07"
msgid "A chain with a little spade is a handle."
msgstr "A chain with a little spade is a handle."

#: 456R08
msgctxt "456R08"
msgid "The lighter must be out of fluid."
msgstr "The lighter must be out of fluid."

#: 456R09
msgctxt "456R09"
msgid "A common two-button switch."
msgstr "A common two-button switch."

#: 456R10
msgctxt "456R10"
msgid "A vent, probably to draw off cigar smoke."
msgstr "A vent, probably to draw off cigar smoke."

#: 456R11
msgctxt "456R11"
msgid "An ashtray."
msgstr "An ashtray."

#: 456R12
msgctxt "456R12"
msgid "The ashtray is a permanent part of the smoking hunch."
msgstr "The ashtray is a permanent part of the smoking hunch."

#: 456R13
msgctxt "456R13"
msgid "Ripley, you don't put round balls in rectangular holes. It won't fit."
msgstr "Ripley, you don't put round balls in rectangular holes. It won't fit."

#: 456R14
msgctxt "456R14"
msgid "The lighter is a permanent part of the smoking hatch."
msgstr "The lighter is a permanent part of the smoking hatch."

#: 456R15
msgctxt "456R15"
msgid "The Barron Special Cigar Box is a permanent part of the smoking hatch."
msgstr "The Barron Special Cigar Box is a permanent part of the smoking hatch."

#: 456R16
msgctxt "456R16"
msgid "I know I don't smoke, but cigarettes certainly make you look sophisticated. I wonder if they're as good for your health as the scientists claim."
msgstr "I know I don't smoke, but cigarettes certainly make you look sophisticated. I wonder if they're as good for your health as the scientists claim."

#: 456R17
msgctxt "456R17"
msgid "The old baron's private smoking hatch. The old gent certainly was a secretive fellow."
msgstr "The old baron's private smoking hatch. The old gent certainly was a secretive fellow."

#: 456R26
msgctxt "456R26"
msgid "That Ace of Spades conceals the switch to the old Baron's smoking hatch."
msgstr "That Ace of Spades conceals the switch to the old Baron's smoking hatch."

#: 456R27
msgctxt "456R27"
msgid "A round hole."
msgstr "A round hole."

#: 456R28
msgctxt "456R28"
msgid "A rectangular hole."
msgstr "A rectangular hole."

#: 501R01
msgctxt "501R01"
msgid "Buenos dias, Mateo."
msgstr "Buenos dias, Mateo."

#: 501R02
msgctxt "501R02"
msgid "Dear Mr. Ripley, I regret to inform you that Professor Jorge Menendez was killed two weeks ago in an attempted robbery. Most of his papers are missing or destroyed. The perpetrator remains at large. We are all shocked, to say the least, and it will take us months to reconstruct the professor's work. But if I can be of assistance, please do not hesitate to contact me. Signed, Rafael Campos, Assistant Professor of Archaeology, National University of San Marcos, Lima."
msgstr "Dear Mr. Ripley, I regret to inform you that Professor Jorge Menendez was killed two weeks ago in an attempted robbery. Most of his papers are missing or destroyed. The perpetrator remains at large. We are all shocked, to say the least, and it will take us months to reconstruct the professor's work. But if I can be of assistance, please do not hesitate to contact me. Signed, Rafael Campos, Assistant Professor of Archaeology, National University of San Marcos, Lima."

#: 501R02A
msgctxt "501R02A"
msgid "We're all shocked to say the least and it will take us months to reconstruct the professor's work. But if I can be of assistance, please do not hesitate to contact me. Signed, Rafael Campos, Assistant Professor of Archaeology, National University of San Marcos, Lima."
msgstr "We're all shocked to say the least and it will take us months to reconstruct the professor's work. But if I can be of assistance, please do not hesitate to contact me. Signed, Rafael Campos, Assistant Professor of Archaeology, National University of San Marcos, Lima."

#: 501R02B
msgctxt "501R02B"
msgid "Dear Mr. Ripley, I regret to inform you that Professor Jorge Menendez was killed two weeks ago in an attempted robbery. Most of his papers are missing or destroyed. The perpetrator remains at large. We are all shocked to say the least and it will take us months to reconstruct the professor's work. But if I can be of assistance, please do not hesitate to contact me. Signed, Rafael Campos, Assistant Professor of Archaeology, National University of San Marcos, Lima. Months? I don't have months. The man Menendez mentioned in his letter, the one who was following him, I wonder who he was."
msgstr "Dear Mr. Ripley, I regret to inform you that Professor Jorge Menendez was killed two weeks ago in an attempted robbery. Most of his papers are missing or destroyed. The perpetrator remains at large. We are all shocked to say the least and it will take us months to reconstruct the professor's work. But if I can be of assistance, please do not hesitate to contact me. Signed, Rafael Campos, Assistant Professor of Archaeology, National University of San Marcos, Lima. Months? I don't have months. The man Menendez mentioned in his letter, the one who was following him, I wonder who he was."

#: 501R03
msgctxt "501R03"
msgid "Dear Mr. Ripley, I wanted to let you know that the identity of Professor Menendez's killer has been uncovered. Evidence of the scene points to a ne'er-do-well nephew of the professor named Emilio Menendez, a criminal with a history of looting historical sites. The motive was greed. The nephew had apparently broken into the professor's home in an attempt to steal papers that would lead him to archaeological treasures. Unfortunately, the man seems to have vanished, but police all over Latin America are on the lookout for him. I can only hope that Emilio Menendez will be brought to justice for his despicable crime. Signed, Rafael Campos, Assistant Professor of Archaeology, National University of San Marcos, Lima."
msgstr "Dear Mr. Ripley, I wanted to let you know that the identity of Professor Menendez's killer has been uncovered. Evidence of the scene points to a ne'er-do-well nephew of the professor named Emilio Menendez, a criminal with a history of looting historical sites. The motive was greed. The nephew had apparently broken into the professor's home in an attempt to steal papers that would lead him to archaeological treasures. Unfortunately, the man seems to have vanished, but police all over Latin America are on the lookout for him. I can only hope that Emilio Menendez will be brought to justice for his despicable crime. Signed, Rafael Campos, Assistant Professor of Archaeology, National University of San Marcos, Lima."

#: 501R03A
msgctxt "501R03A"
msgid "The motive was greed. The nephew had apparently broken into the professor's home in an attempt to steal papers that would lead him to archaeological treasures. Unfortunately, the man seems to have vanished, but police all over Latin America are on the lookout for him."
msgstr "The motive was greed. The nephew had apparently broken into the professor's home in an attempt to steal papers that would lead him to archaeological treasures. Unfortunately, the man seems to have vanished, but police all over Latin America are on the lookout for him."

#: 501R03B
msgctxt "501R03B"
msgid "I can only hope that Emilio Menendez will be brought to justice for his despicable crime. Signed, Rafael Campos, Assistant Professor of Archaeology, National University of San Marcos, Lima."
msgstr "I can only hope that Emilio Menendez will be brought to justice for his despicable crime. Signed, Rafael Campos, Assistant Professor of Archaeology, National University of San Marcos, Lima."

#: 501R03C
msgctxt "501R03C"
msgid "Dear Mr. Ripley, I wanted to let you know that the identity of Professor Menendez's killer has been uncovered. Evidence of the scene points to a ne'er-do-well nephew of the professor named Emilio Menendez, a criminal with a history of looting historical sites. The motive was greed. The nephew had apparently broken into the professor's home in an attempt to steal papers that would lead him to archaeological treasures. Unfortunately, the man seems to have vanished, but police all over Latin America are on the lookout for him. I can only hope that Emilio Menendez will be brought to justice for his despicable crime. Signed, Rafael Campos, Assistant Professor of Archaeology, National University of San Marcos, Lima. Justice has been served, Professor Campos. Greed was literally the downfall of Emilio Menendez."
msgstr "Dear Mr. Ripley, I wanted to let you know that the identity of Professor Menendez's killer has been uncovered. Evidence of the scene points to a ne'er-do-well nephew of the professor named Emilio Menendez, a criminal with a history of looting historical sites. The motive was greed. The nephew had apparently broken into the professor's home in an attempt to steal papers that would lead him to archaeological treasures. Unfortunately, the man seems to have vanished, but police all over Latin America are on the lookout for him. I can only hope that Emilio Menendez will be brought to justice for his despicable crime. Signed, Rafael Campos, Assistant Professor of Archaeology, National University of San Marcos, Lima. Justice has been served, Professor Campos. Greed was literally the downfall of Emilio Menendez."

#: 501R05
msgctxt "501R05"
msgid "An unusual looking clock."
msgstr "An unusual looking clock."

#: 501R05A
msgctxt "501R05A"
msgid "I wonder if there is a story behind it."
msgstr "I wonder if there is a story behind it."

#: 501R06
msgctxt "501R06"
msgid "Standard views of Lake Titicaca, El Misti, that magnificent extinct volcano with the evocative name, and of course the ancient cities like Machu Picchu."
msgstr "Standard views of Lake Titicaca, El Misti, that magnificent extinct volcano with the evocative name, and of course the ancient cities like Machu Picchu."

#: 501R07
msgctxt "501R07"
msgid "Puffins. Stuffed, carved, molded, painted..."
msgstr "Puffins. Stuffed, carved, molded, painted..."

#: 501R07A
msgctxt "501R07A"
msgid "A unique collection."
msgstr "A unique collection."

#: 501R08
msgctxt "501R08"
msgid "A magnificent stelae. One pictograph looks like a giant condor."
msgstr "A magnificent stelae. One pictograph looks like a giant condor."

#: 501R08A
msgctxt "501R08A"
msgid "It's a shame some of those blocks are broken off."
msgstr "It's a shame some of those blocks are broken off."

#: 501R10
msgctxt "501R10"
msgid "A simple brick wall atop an ancient Inca stone foundation. With stones fitted so tightly, a razor blade cannot be slit between them. I'll wager the Inca stones are here long after their modern counterparts have crumbled to dust."
msgstr "A simple brick wall atop an ancient Inca stone foundation. With stones fitted so tightly, a razor blade cannot be slit between them. I'll wager the Inca stones are here long after their modern counterparts have crumbled to dust."

#: 501R12
msgctxt "501R12"
msgid "Posh Express Man in Peru, efficient and friendly."
msgstr "Posh Express Man in Peru, efficient and friendly."

#: 501R14
msgctxt "501R14"
msgid "Did I remember to ask my landlady to water my plants?"
msgstr "Did I remember to ask my landlady to water my plants?"

#: 501R19
msgctxt "501R19"
msgid "The stele is far too heavy."
msgstr "The stele is far too heavy."

#: 501R20
msgctxt "501R20"
msgid "What am I thinking of? I don't want to steal the puffin!"
msgstr "What am I thinking of? I don't want to steal the puffin!"

#: 501R21
msgctxt "501R21"
msgid "I expect my tail would object if I tried to walk off with the clock."
msgstr "I expect my tail would object if I tried to walk off with the clock."

#: 501R34
msgctxt "501R34"
msgid "I already have a sketch of the stele."
msgstr "I already have a sketch of the stele."

#: 501R35
msgctxt "501R35"
msgid "Other than the stelae, there is nothing else of interest to sketch in here."
msgstr "Other than the stelae, there is nothing else of interest to sketch in here."

#: 501R36
msgctxt "501R36"
msgid "This Driftwood reminded me of a puffin when I first saw it."
msgstr "This Driftwood reminded me of a puffin when I first saw it."

#: 501R37
msgctxt "501R37"
msgid "Your son might like it, and that circular hole your clock might fit in there."
msgstr "Your son might like it, and that circular hole your clock might fit in there."

#: 501R38
msgctxt "501R38"
msgid "Could we trade?"
msgstr "Could we trade?"

#: 501R39
msgctxt "501R39"
msgid "Don't worry about me. This piece of coral is payment enough."
msgstr "Don't worry about me. This piece of coral is payment enough."

#: 501R40
msgctxt "501R40"
msgid "Ripley, where do you think you're going? You don't know your way around these parts. Getting lost won't help."
msgstr "Ripley, where do you think you're going? You don't know your way around these parts. Getting lost won't help."

#: 501X01
msgctxt "501X01"
msgid "Buenas dias señor Ripley. Welcome back to Lima."
msgstr "Buenas dias señor Ripley. Welcome back to Lima."

#: 501X02
msgctxt "501X02"
msgid "There is a message for you."
msgstr "There is a message for you."

#: 501X03
msgctxt "501X03"
msgid "There are messages for you."
msgstr "There are messages for you."

#: 501X05
msgctxt "501X05"
msgid "You're right! It is a remarkable likeness."
msgstr "You're right! It is a remarkable likeness."

#: 501X06
msgctxt "501X06"
msgid "It is possible, yes."
msgstr "It is possible, yes."

#: 501X07
msgctxt "501X07"
msgid "With the greatest of pleasure, Senor Ripley. Muchísimas gracias. My son will be so excited."
msgstr "With the greatest of pleasure, Senor Ripley. Muchísimas gracias. My son will be so excited."

#: 501X08
msgctxt "501X08"
msgid "But it is not much of a trade. I have gained so much and you... May I not pay you something?"
msgstr "But it is not much of a trade. I have gained so much and you... May I not pay you something?"

#: 504R01
msgctxt "504R01"
msgid "The guide must really be scared of ghosts, leaving me to climb the last five hundred feet on my own. But I'm going to need a rope to climb back down that last cliff."
msgstr "The guide must really be scared of ghosts, leaving me to climb the last five hundred feet on my own. But I'm going to need a rope to climb back down that last cliff."

#: 504R02
msgctxt "504R02"
msgid "The lost city of Moka Moche."
msgstr "The lost city of Moka Moche."

#: 504R02A
msgctxt "504R02A"
msgid "Built by a forgotten civilization that predates the Inca by centuries. A civilization Master Lu visited, and whose hieroglyphics are now a part of his tablet in the Hall of Classics. It took almost a week to get here from Lima. I hope it'll be worth it."
msgstr "Built by a forgotten civilization that predates the Inca by centuries. A civilization Master Lu visited, and whose hieroglyphics are now a part of his tablet in the Hall of Classics. It took almost a week to get here from Lima. I hope it'll be worth it."

#: 504R03
msgctxt "504R03"
msgid "The waterfall is breathtaking. It reminds me of the speed and power of a finely tuned Ferrari."
msgstr "The waterfall is breathtaking. It reminds me of the speed and power of a finely tuned Ferrari."

#: 504R04
msgctxt "504R04"
msgid "The tree toppled long ago, and has obviously been enlisted as a crude bridge across the chasm. Looks very slippery thanks to the mist from the waterfall."
msgstr "The tree toppled long ago, and has obviously been enlisted as a crude bridge across the chasm. Looks very slippery thanks to the mist from the waterfall."

#: 504R04A
msgctxt "504R04A"
msgid "The tree looks very slippery, thanks to the mist from the waterfall."
msgstr "The tree looks very slippery, thanks to the mist from the waterfall."

#: 504R05
msgctxt "504R05"
msgid "The rope is the only handhold for anyone crossing the chasm on that tree. And I'll also need it to climb back down that cliff."
msgstr "The rope is the only handhold for anyone crossing the chasm on that tree. And I'll also need it to climb back down that cliff."

#: 504R05A
msgctxt "504R05A"
msgid "The rope is the only handhold for anyone crossing the chasm on that tree."
msgstr "The rope is the only handhold for anyone crossing the chasm on that tree."

#: 504R05B
msgctxt "504R05B"
msgid "Good! The vines are still here."
msgstr "Good! The vines are still here."

#: 504R06
msgctxt "504R06"
msgid "The statue of a spider. Menendez was right. Mocha Moche was the city devoted to the spider god. There is a rope attached to an iron ring on the statue."
msgstr "The statue of a spider. Menendez was right. Mocha Moche was the city devoted to the spider god. There is a rope attached to an iron ring on the statue."

#: 504R06A
msgctxt "504R06A"
msgid "The statue of a spider. There is a rope attached to an iron ring on the statue."
msgstr "The statue of a spider. There is a rope attached to an iron ring on the statue."

#: 504R06B
msgctxt "504R06B"
msgid "The statue of a spider."
msgstr "The statue of a spider."

#: 504R07
msgctxt "504R07"
msgid "These thick vines are a common sight in these mountains."
msgstr "These thick vines are a common sight in these mountains."

#: 504R08
msgctxt "504R08"
msgid "It must be half a mile to the bottom of the chasm."
msgstr "It must be half a mile to the bottom of the chasm."

#: 504R09
msgctxt "504R09"
msgid "These stones are thousands of years old."
msgstr "These stones are thousands of years old."

#: 504R12
msgctxt "504R12"
msgid "Hmm... whoever that is, he can't be an archaeologist, burrowing away without quartering his sight or applying even the most rudimentary safeguards."
msgstr "Hmm... whoever that is, he can't be an archaeologist, burrowing away without quartering his sight or applying even the most rudimentary safeguards."

#: 504R13
msgctxt "504R13"
msgid "Would you take this?"
msgstr "Would you take this?"

#: 504R14
msgctxt "504R14"
msgid "Your ladder. Your shovel."
msgstr "Your ladder. Your shovel."

#: 504R15
msgctxt "504R15"
msgid "That's an emerald! It's worth thousands! Give it back!"
msgstr "That's an emerald! It's worth thousands! Give it back!"

#: 504R16
msgctxt "504R16"
msgid "What happened?"
msgstr "What happened?"

#: 504R17
msgctxt "504R17"
msgid "Cursed luck... Wait! The emerald!"
msgstr "Cursed luck... Wait! The emerald!"

#: 504R18
msgctxt "504R18"
msgid "Don't try crossing the AAAAAAAAAAAA-"
msgstr "Don't try crossing the AAAAAAAAAAAA-"

#: 504R18A
msgctxt "504R18A"
msgid "Chasm."
msgstr "Chasm."

#: 504R19
msgctxt "504R19"
msgid "Menendez has done enough damage to the site."
msgstr "Menendez has done enough damage to the site."

#: 504R20
msgctxt "504R20"
msgid "A pre-Columbian wheeled toy. This is remarkable. We know the Inca hadn't discovered any practical application for the wheel, yet here it is used as locomotion for a toy. And a little child shall lead them."
msgstr "A pre-Columbian wheeled toy. This is remarkable. We know the Inca hadn't discovered any practical application for the wheel, yet here it is used as locomotion for a toy. And a little child shall lead them."

#: 504R21
msgctxt "504R21"
msgid "There's nothing in the hole except for a couple of Menendez Toads."
msgstr "There's nothing in the hole except for a couple of Menendez Toads."

#: 504R22
msgctxt "504R22"
msgid "This stelae must refer to the city that worshiped the monkey god that Professor Menendez mentioned in his letter. Some of the blocks are missing."
msgstr "This stelae must refer to the city that worshiped the monkey god that Professor Menendez mentioned in his letter. Some of the blocks are missing."

#: 504R23
msgctxt "504R23"
msgid "I already have a sketch of the stele."
msgstr "I already have a sketch of the stele."

#: 504R24
msgctxt "504R24"
msgid "The Stella is far too heavy."
msgstr "The Stella is far too heavy."

#: 504R25
msgctxt "504R25"
msgid "It's hard not to think of the feet that trod this ancient staircase so many eons ago."
msgstr "It's hard not to think of the feet that trod this ancient staircase so many eons ago."

#: 504R33
msgctxt "504R33"
msgid "All that remains of Menendez are three severed toes."
msgstr "All that remains of Menendez are three severed toes."

#: 504R33A
msgctxt "504R33A"
msgid "I wonder if Menenda's toes are still down there."
msgstr "I wonder if Menenda's toes are still down there."

#: 504R34
msgctxt "504R34"
msgid "There's a coil of vine left on the ground."
msgstr "There's a coil of vine left on the ground."

#: 504R35
msgctxt "504R35"
msgid "There's a large coil of vine left on the ground."
msgstr "There's a large coil of vine left on the ground."

#: 504R36
msgctxt "504R36"
msgid "One end of the rope is untied."
msgstr "One end of the rope is untied."

#: 504R37
msgctxt "504R37"
msgid "The rope and the vine are now tied across the chasm."
msgstr "The rope and the vine are now tied across the chasm."

#: 504R38
msgctxt "504R38"
msgid "The rope and the vines are now tied across the chasm."
msgstr "The rope and the vines are now tied across the chasm."

#: 504R39
msgctxt "504R39"
msgid "It's tied to the spider statue."
msgstr "It's tied to the spider statue."

#: 504R40
msgctxt "504R40"
msgid "It's tied securely to the tree."
msgstr "It's tied securely to the tree."

#: 504R41
msgctxt "504R41"
msgid "The vine is tied across the chasm."
msgstr "The vine is tied across the chasm."

#: 504R42
msgctxt "504R42"
msgid "The vine is doubled across the chasm."
msgstr "The vine is doubled across the chasm."

#: 504R43
msgctxt "504R43"
msgid "Too bulky to cross that log with."
msgstr "Too bulky to cross that log with."

#: 504R44
msgctxt "504R44"
msgid "I'll need the rope to climb back down."
msgstr "I'll need the rope to climb back down."

#: 504R45
msgctxt "504R45"
msgid "If I'm going to cross the chasm on that tree trunk, I'd better travel light."
msgstr "If I'm going to cross the chasm on that tree trunk, I'd better travel light."

#: 504R46
msgctxt "504R46"
msgid "That isn't bulky enough to get in the way."
msgstr "That isn't bulky enough to get in the way."

#: 504R47
msgctxt "504R47"
msgid "Ripley, you already have two vines. That should be enough for any man."
msgstr "Ripley, you already have two vines. That should be enough for any man."

#: 504R48
msgctxt "504R48"
msgid "I'm no thief."
msgstr "I'm no thief."

#: 504R49
msgctxt "504R49"
msgid "If I threw it without securing it first, it could end up at the bottom of the chasm."
msgstr "If I threw it without securing it first, it could end up at the bottom of the chasm."

#: 504R50
msgctxt "504R50"
msgid "That looks like a child's toy."
msgstr "That looks like a child's toy."

#: 504R51
msgctxt "504R51"
msgid "Excuse me."
msgstr "Excuse me."

#: 504Z01
msgctxt "504Z01"
msgid "No, senor."
msgstr "No, senor."

#: 504Z02
msgctxt "504Z02"
msgid "Find your own ladder."
msgstr "Find your own ladder."

#: 504Z03
msgctxt "504Z03"
msgid "It's not for sale."
msgstr "It's not for sale."

#: 504Z04
msgctxt "504Z04"
msgid "Where do you want to climb anyway?"
msgstr "Where do you want to climb anyway?"

#: 504Z05
msgctxt "504Z05"
msgid "What do I want with that?"
msgstr "What do I want with that?"

#: 504Z06
msgctxt "504Z06"
msgid "NO!"
msgstr "NO!"

#: 504Z07
msgctxt "504Z07"
msgid "I need it."
msgstr "I need it."

#: 504Z08
msgctxt "504Z08"
msgid "I can't dig without a shovel."
msgstr "I can't dig without a shovel."

#: 504Z09
msgctxt "504Z09"
msgid "You're wasting my time!"
msgstr "You're wasting my time!"

#: 504Z10
msgctxt "504Z10"
msgid "Are you crazy, senor?"
msgstr "Are you crazy, senor?"

#: 504Z11
msgctxt "504Z11"
msgid "No, gracias."
msgstr "No, gracias."

#: 504Z12
msgctxt "504Z12"
msgid "Stupid foreigners."
msgstr "Stupid foreigners."

#: 504Z13
msgctxt "504Z13"
msgid "For what?"
msgstr "For what?"

#: 504Z14
msgctxt "504Z14"
msgid "I'll take it as a down payment."
msgstr "I'll take it as a down payment."

#: 504Z15
msgctxt "504Z15"
msgid "Do not provoke me further or they'll be digging up your remains in a century or two."
msgstr "Do not provoke me further or they'll be digging up your remains in a century or two."

#: 504Z16
msgctxt "504Z16"
msgid "Oh, what cursed luck!"
msgstr "Oh, what cursed luck!"

#: 504Z17
msgctxt "504Z17"
msgid "I've sliced up my foot with a shovel. It's never happened to me before. I'm a professional!"
msgstr "I've sliced up my foot with a shovel. It's never happened to me before. I'm a professional!"

#: 504Z18
msgctxt "504Z18"
msgid "It's mine now!"
msgstr "It's mine now!"

#: 506R01
msgctxt "506R01"
msgid "The lost city of Moka Moche."
msgstr "The lost city of Moka Moche."

#: 506R01A
msgctxt "506R01A"
msgid "It took almost a week to get here. I hope it will be worth it."
msgstr "It took almost a week to get here. I hope it will be worth it."

#: 506R02
msgctxt "506R02"
msgid "There's something about that tower, the stark lines of the crumbling walls, the keening of the wind as it whips at the stone."
msgstr "There's something about that tower, the stark lines of the crumbling walls, the keening of the wind as it whips at the stone."

#: 506R03
msgctxt "506R03"
msgid "A headless skeleton almost three stories high. A monument to death. There's a terrible finality in those open arms."
msgstr "A headless skeleton almost three stories high. A monument to death. There's a terrible finality in those open arms."

#: 506R04
msgctxt "506R04"
msgid "Something in that niche is catching the sunlight."
msgstr "Something in that niche is catching the sunlight."

#: 506R05
msgctxt "506R05"
msgid "This vast central terrace almost forces the attention of any who stand here to the tower."
msgstr "This vast central terrace almost forces the attention of any who stand here to the tower."

#: 506R06
msgctxt "506R06"
msgid "That building must be an observatory, like the one Menendez refers to in his letter."
msgstr "That building must be an observatory, like the one Menendez refers to in his letter."

#: 506R07
msgctxt "506R07"
msgid "The dome looks uncannily advanced for its time."
msgstr "The dome looks uncannily advanced for its time."

#: 506R08
msgctxt "506R08"
msgid "Statues of spiders with outstretched arms, as if welcoming their prey."
msgstr "Statues of spiders with outstretched arms, as if welcoming their prey."

#: 506R09
msgctxt "506R09"
msgid "These thick vines are a common sight in these mountains."
msgstr "These thick vines are a common sight in these mountains."

#: 506R19
msgctxt "506R19"
msgid "Vines cling to the stone wall of the tower."
msgstr "Vines cling to the stone wall of the tower."

#: 507R01
msgctxt "507R01"
msgid "A door of solid copper, yet it lacks a handle or a doorknob. And those symbols inset into the frame, they're similar to the ones on the stelae I've sketched. It's some sort of mechanism requiring a combination."
msgstr "A door of solid copper, yet it lacks a handle or a doorknob. And those symbols inset into the frame, they're similar to the ones on the stelae I've sketched. It's some sort of mechanism requiring a combination."

#: 507R02
msgctxt "507R02"
msgid "I'll have to figure out the combination if I want to get through the door."
msgstr "I'll have to figure out the combination if I want to get through the door."

#: 507R03
msgctxt "507R03"
msgid "A copper door."
msgstr "A copper door."

#: 507R04
msgctxt "507R04"
msgid "The block the glyph is on looks movable."
msgstr "The block the glyph is on looks movable."

#: 507R05
msgctxt "507R05"
msgid "According to the Menendez letter, somewhere in another lost city is the stelae that holds the combination to this door."
msgstr "According to the Menendez letter, somewhere in another lost city is the stelae that holds the combination to this door."

#: 507R07
msgctxt "507R07"
msgid "The door is far too solidly constructed to be forced open."
msgstr "The door is far too solidly constructed to be forced open."

#: 507R15
msgctxt "507R15"
msgid "These are the same glyphs I saw in the spelling."
msgstr "These are the same glyphs I saw in the spelling."

#: 508R01
msgctxt "508R01"
msgid "Observatory or something more?"
msgstr "Observatory or something more?"

#: 508R01A
msgctxt "508R01A"
msgid "Menendez was right. These buildings were constructed to observe the heavens and to play some active part in this forgotten race's rituals."
msgstr "Menendez was right. These buildings were constructed to observe the heavens and to play some active part in this forgotten race's rituals."

#: 508R02
msgctxt "508R02"
msgid "The craftsmanship that built the dome would be remarkable even today."
msgstr "The craftsmanship that built the dome would be remarkable even today."

#: 508R03
msgctxt "508R03"
msgid "That slid is too narrow for viewing stars."
msgstr "That slid is too narrow for viewing stars."

#: 508R04
msgctxt "508R04"
msgid "These are the same glyphs I saw in the spelling."
msgstr "These are the same glyphs I saw in the spelling."

#: 508R05
msgctxt "508R05"
msgid "A skeleton carved from unblemished jade. Where's its head, I wonder?"
msgstr "A skeleton carved from unblemished jade. Where's its head, I wonder?"

#: 508R05A
msgctxt "508R05A"
msgid "A headless skeleton carved from unblemished jade."
msgstr "A headless skeleton carved from unblemished jade."

#: 508R05B
msgctxt "508R05B"
msgid "The Crystal Skull was obviously meant to sit on the Jade Skeleton."
msgstr "The Crystal Skull was obviously meant to sit on the Jade Skeleton."

#: 508R06
msgctxt "508R06"
msgid "This chain circles the whole dome, then disappears into the floor."
msgstr "This chain circles the whole dome, then disappears into the floor."

#: 508R07
msgctxt "508R07"
msgid "A stone floor inlaid with a striking blue mosaic."
msgstr "A stone floor inlaid with a striking blue mosaic."

#: 508R08
msgctxt "508R08"
msgid "Carved from stone."
msgstr "Carved from stone."

#: 508R09
msgctxt "508R09"
msgid "Holes dot the circumference of the base. I wonder what they're for?"
msgstr "Holes dot the circumference of the base. I wonder what they're for?"

#: 508R09A
msgctxt "508R09A"
msgid "Holes dot the circumference of the base."
msgstr "Holes dot the circumference of the base."

#: 508R10
msgctxt "508R10"
msgid "A bas relief design of some kind. No doubt an ancient god."
msgstr "A bas relief design of some kind. No doubt an ancient god."

#: 508R11
msgctxt "508R11"
msgid "I could have sworn it would turn. What am I missing?"
msgstr "I could have sworn it would turn. What am I missing?"

#: 508R12
msgctxt "508R12"
msgid "The colors striking each glyph. It must be significant."
msgstr "The colors striking each glyph. It must be significant."

#: 508R13
msgctxt "508R13"
msgid "Green, blue, purple, no color. Yellow, red, orange..."
msgstr "Green, blue, purple, no color. Yellow, red, orange..."

#: 508R14
msgctxt "508R14"
msgid "Got it! I hope it helps!"
msgstr "Got it! I hope it helps!"

#: 508R15
msgctxt "508R15"
msgid "The chain is broken."
msgstr "The chain is broken."

#: 508R16
msgctxt "508R16"
msgid "The shovel is tightly wedged in the capstan. I can't budget it."
msgstr "The shovel is tightly wedged in the capstan. I can't budget it."

#: 508R17
msgctxt "508R17"
msgid "The chain is broken. The dome won't rotate."
msgstr "The chain is broken. The dome won't rotate."

#: 508R25
msgctxt "508R25"
msgid "A skull fashioned from some fabulous crystal."
msgstr "A skull fashioned from some fabulous crystal."

#: 509R01
msgctxt "509R01"
msgid "Gosh, the wind. It erupts from below, its fingers plucking at me, insistent, caressing, pushing me up the steps to... what? And the sound... like a choir of the damned."
msgstr "Gosh, the wind. It erupts from below, its fingers plucking at me, insistent, caressing, pushing me up the steps to... what? And the sound... like a choir of the damned."

#: 509R02
msgctxt "509R02"
msgid "The belly of this fearsome tower."
msgstr "The belly of this fearsome tower."

#: 509R03
msgctxt "509R03"
msgid "The tightly fitted stonework of this lost race rivals that of the Inca. But the walls feel almost alive. I'm sure it's only the wind in my imagination."
msgstr "The tightly fitted stonework of this lost race rivals that of the Inca. But the walls feel almost alive. I'm sure it's only the wind in my imagination."

#: 509R04
msgctxt "509R04"
msgid "The niche that forms the head of the skeleton would be just about here."
msgstr "The niche that forms the head of the skeleton would be just about here."

#: 509R04A
msgctxt "509R04A"
msgid "The niche that contained the crystal skull is behind there."
msgstr "The niche that contained the crystal skull is behind there."

#: 509R05
msgctxt "509R05"
msgid "The stairs lead further up the tower."
msgstr "The stairs lead further up the tower."

#: 509R06
msgctxt "509R06"
msgid "The stairs lead down to the base of the tower."
msgstr "The stairs lead down to the base of the tower."

#: 509R07
msgctxt "509R07"
msgid "It's locked or jammed."
msgstr "It's locked or jammed."

#: 509R08
msgctxt "509R08"
msgid "The door looks like it's been fused by the centuries. Would probably take a stick of dynamite to budge it."
msgstr "The door looks like it's been fused by the centuries. Would probably take a stick of dynamite to budge it."

#: 510R01
msgctxt "510R01"
msgid "The guide was right. There are ghosts here. And now I know why."
msgstr "The guide was right. There are ghosts here. And now I know why."

#: 510R02
msgctxt "510R02"
msgid "A city built on top of the world, a place of ancient science and even older rituals."
msgstr "A city built on top of the world, a place of ancient science and even older rituals."

#: 510R03
msgctxt "510R03"
msgid "The remains of an altar... the significance of that skeleton becomes obvious now."
msgstr "The remains of an altar... the significance of that skeleton becomes obvious now."

#: 510R03A
msgctxt "510R03A"
msgid "The remains of an altar."
msgstr "The remains of an altar."

#: 510R04
msgctxt "510R04"
msgid "A trough to carry away sacrificial blood. Human blood, I'm afraid. If stones could speak, these would scream."
msgstr "A trough to carry away sacrificial blood. Human blood, I'm afraid. If stones could speak, these would scream."

#: 510R04A
msgctxt "510R04A"
msgid "A trough to carry away sacrificial blood... human blood, I'm afraid."
msgstr "A trough to carry away sacrificial blood... human blood, I'm afraid."

#: 510R05
msgctxt "510R05"
msgid "They are screaming."
msgstr "They are screaming."

#: 510R06
msgctxt "510R06"
msgid "I can't see inside the niche from here."
msgstr "I can't see inside the niche from here."

#: 510R09
msgctxt "510R09"
msgid "While it might make a grisly addition to the auditorium, I could never get it down the mountain. In a way, I'm glad."
msgstr "While it might make a grisly addition to the auditorium, I could never get it down the mountain. In a way, I'm glad."

#: 510R10
msgctxt "510R10"
msgid "I'd better secure this ladder first. It's a long way to Lima from here. Straight down."
msgstr "I'd better secure this ladder first. It's a long way to Lima from here. Straight down."

#: 510R11
msgctxt "510R11"
msgid "A skull fashioned from some fabulous crystal."
msgstr "A skull fashioned from some fabulous crystal."

#: 510R19
msgctxt "510R19"
msgid "I'd have to shift the Altar."
msgstr "I'd have to shift the Altar."

#: 510R20
msgctxt "510R20"
msgid "The dome looks uncannily advanced for its time."
msgstr "The dome looks uncannily advanced for its time."

#: 603R01
msgctxt "603R01"
msgid "Easter Island, a living enigma in the midst of the vast Pacific Ocean. Who were the people that lived here? Where did they come from?"
msgstr "Easter Island, a living enigma in the midst of the vast Pacific Ocean. Who were the people that lived here? Where did they come from?"

#: 603R01A
msgctxt "603R01A"
msgid "Dr. Twelve Trees Archaeological Dig."
msgstr "Dr. Twelve Trees Archaeological Dig."

#: 603R02
msgctxt "603R02"
msgid "Looks like a comfortable enough place to live."
msgstr "Looks like a comfortable enough place to live."

#: 603R03
msgctxt "603R03"
msgid "A rundown storage shed."
msgstr "A rundown storage shed."

#: 603R04
msgctxt "603R04"
msgid "The door to the shed is held open with a length of wire."
msgstr "The door to the shed is held open with a length of wire."

#: 603R05
msgctxt "603R05"
msgid "An electrical power cable runs from the shed to the hut."
msgstr "An electrical power cable runs from the shed to the hut."

#: 603R06
msgctxt "603R06"
msgid "Looks like an ancient altar."
msgstr "Looks like an ancient altar."

#: 603R06A
msgctxt "603R06A"
msgid "An ancient altar."
msgstr "An ancient altar."

#: 603R07
msgctxt "603R07"
msgid "I'd have my shirt off too if I had to work in this heat for very long."
msgstr "I'd have my shirt off too if I had to work in this heat for very long."

#: 603R08
msgctxt "603R08"
msgid "Tearing her shirt was not the best introduction I could have made."
msgstr "Tearing her shirt was not the best introduction I could have made."

#: 603R09
msgctxt "603R09"
msgid "A sturdy looking pole."
msgstr "A sturdy looking pole."

#: 603R10
msgctxt "603R10"
msgid "The cliff rises over thirty feet above the sea."
msgstr "The cliff rises over thirty feet above the sea."

#: 603R11
msgctxt "603R11"
msgid "This must be a portion of the Twelve Trees Dig."
msgstr "This must be a portion of the Twelve Trees Dig."

#: 603R12
msgctxt "603R12"
msgid "Oh, uh, excuse me."
msgstr "Oh, uh, excuse me."

#: 603R13
msgctxt "603R13"
msgid "Not in the slightest."
msgstr "Not in the slightest."

#: 603R14
msgctxt "603R14"
msgid "Could I have the sleeve?"
msgstr "Could I have the sleeve?"

#: 603R14A
msgctxt "603R14A"
msgid "A memento of our first meeting."
msgstr "A memento of our first meeting."

#: 603R22
msgctxt "603R22"
msgid "Nothing much of interest to sketch here."
msgstr "Nothing much of interest to sketch here."

#: 603R23
msgctxt "603R23"
msgid "Sorry."
msgstr "Sorry."

#: 603R24
msgctxt "603R24"
msgid "I might damage precious artifacts if I went rooting about down there."
msgstr "I might damage precious artifacts if I went rooting about down there."

#: 603R25
msgctxt "603R25"
msgid "Dr. Twelve Trees is not about to let me trample all over her dick."
msgstr "Dr. Twelve Trees is not about to let me trample all over her dick."

#: 603R26
msgctxt "603R26"
msgid "There appears to be a note on the hut."
msgstr "There appears to be a note on the hut."

#: 603R27
msgctxt "603R27"
msgid "Dr. Twelve Trees is excavating the base of that ancient altar."
msgstr "Dr. Twelve Trees is excavating the base of that ancient altar."

#: 603R28
msgctxt "603R28"
msgid "Mr. Ripley, gone to the settlement for supplies. Be back shortly. Twelve trees."
msgstr "Mr. Ripley, gone to the settlement for supplies. Be back shortly. Twelve trees."

#: 603R29
msgctxt "603R29"
msgid "That poll could come in handy, but it's not really mine to take. Oh, she'll never miss it. I can bring it back later."
msgstr "That poll could come in handy, but it's not really mine to take. Oh, she'll never miss it. I can bring it back later."

#: 603R30
msgctxt "603R30"
msgid "Dr. Twelve Trees apparently tried to map the quarry."
msgstr "Dr. Twelve Trees apparently tried to map the quarry."

#: 603R31
msgctxt "603R31"
msgid "It's a rough map. If those are stones, it might be some place on the island."
msgstr "It's a rough map. If those are stones, it might be some place on the island."

#: 603R32
msgctxt "603R32"
msgid "The door to the hut has a padlock on it."
msgstr "The door to the hut has a padlock on it."

#: 603R34
msgctxt "603R34"
msgid "I'd better not disturb Dr. TwelveTreesDig."
msgstr "I'd better not disturb Dr. TwelveTreesDig."

#: 603R35
msgctxt "603R35"
msgid "Doctor Twelve Trees Living Quarters"
msgstr "Doctor Twelve Trees Living Quarters"

#: 603R36
msgctxt "603R36"
msgid "Quite a woman."
msgstr "Quite a woman."

#: 603R37
msgctxt "603R37"
msgid "Beauty, brains, and married to science."
msgstr "Beauty, brains, and married to science."

#: 603R38
msgctxt "603R38"
msgid "Keep your mind on the quest, Ripley."
msgstr "Keep your mind on the quest, Ripley."

#: 603R39
msgctxt "603R39"
msgid "Remember, Mei is in China right now risking her life for you."
msgstr "Remember, Mei is in China right now risking her life for you."

#: 603R40
msgctxt "603R40"
msgid "How's the dig going?"
msgstr "How's the dig going?"

#: 603R41
msgctxt "603R41"
msgid "You sure spend a lot of time down in that pit."
msgstr "You sure spend a lot of time down in that pit."

#: 603R42
msgctxt "603R42"
msgid "Any luck so far?"
msgstr "Any luck so far?"

#: 603R43
msgctxt "603R43"
msgid "You're very dedicated."
msgstr "You're very dedicated."

#: 603R44
msgctxt "603R44"
msgid "Gone to Mackenzie Institute in Ireland to match Rongo-Rongo tablets there with recent discovery. Be back in two to three months. Please do not disturb the dig site. Signed, Dr. Samantha Twelve Trees."
msgstr "Gone to Mackenzie Institute in Ireland to match Rongo-Rongo tablets there with recent discovery. Be back in two to three months. Please do not disturb the dig site. Signed, Dr. Samantha Twelve Trees."

#: 603R45
msgctxt "603R45"
msgid "The note was not only meant for me, I think I'll leave it right where it is."
msgstr "The note was not only meant for me, I think I'll leave it right where it is."

#: 603R46
msgctxt "603R46"
msgid "She might not help me if she knew I borrowed her pole."
msgstr "She might not help me if she knew I borrowed her pole."

#: 603R47
msgctxt "603R47"
msgid "I'd better leave the digging to Dr. 12trees. She's a professional."
msgstr "I'd better leave the digging to Dr. 12trees. She's a professional."

#: 603T01
msgctxt "603T01"
msgid "Hey!"
msgstr "Hey!"

#: 603T02
msgctxt "603T02"
msgid "Do you mind?"
msgstr "Do you mind?"

#: 603T03
msgctxt "603T03"
msgid "Leave the pole alone. I hang a tarp over it so I can work in the rain."
msgstr "Leave the pole alone. I hang a tarp over it so I can work in the rain."

#: 603T04
msgctxt "603T04"
msgid "Whatever for?"
msgstr "Whatever for?"

#: 603T05
msgctxt "603T05"
msgid "You're a very strange man, Mr. Ripley. Help yourself. I certainly have no further use for it."
msgstr "You're a very strange man, Mr. Ripley. Help yourself. I certainly have no further use for it."

#: 603T06
msgctxt "603T06"
msgid "That's my private living quarters. I keep the door locked."
msgstr "That's my private living quarters. I keep the door locked."

#: 603T07
msgctxt "603T07"
msgid "Please stay out of the shed!"
msgstr "Please stay out of the shed!"

#: 603T08
msgctxt "603T08"
msgid "Archaeology requires infinite patience."
msgstr "Archaeology requires infinite patience."

#: 603T09
msgctxt "603T09"
msgid "You never know when you'll find something important."
msgstr "You never know when you'll find something important."

#: 603T10
msgctxt "603T10"
msgid "I could be inches away from the next Rosetta Stone."
msgstr "I could be inches away from the next Rosetta Stone."

#: 603T11
msgctxt "603T11"
msgid "The trick is just to keep at it."
msgstr "The trick is just to keep at it."

#: 604K01
msgctxt "604K01"
msgid "Shen Gao, see who's in the shed."
msgstr "Shen Gao, see who's in the shed."

#: 604R01
msgctxt "604R01"
msgid "Dr. Twelve Trees uses that wire to hook the door open."
msgstr "Dr. Twelve Trees uses that wire to hook the door open."

#: 604R02
msgctxt "604R02"
msgid "The latest in portable generators. It obviously provides power to Dr. Twelve Trees Hut."
msgstr "The latest in portable generators. It obviously provides power to Dr. Twelve Trees Hut."

#: 604R03
msgctxt "604R03"
msgid "Gas gauge reads nearly full."
msgstr "Gas gauge reads nearly full."

#: 604R04
msgctxt "604R04"
msgid "The gas tank cap."
msgstr "The gas tank cap."

#: 604R05
msgctxt "604R05"
msgid "A drain for the gas tank with a half inch bolt on the end."
msgstr "A drain for the gas tank with a half inch bolt on the end."

#: 604R06
msgctxt "604R06"
msgid "The pull cord has a wooden handle attached to a short length of rope."
msgstr "The pull cord has a wooden handle attached to a short length of rope."

#: 604R07
msgctxt "604R07"
msgid "That wire must connect to the power cable that runs to the hut."
msgstr "That wire must connect to the power cable that runs to the hut."

#: 604R08
msgctxt "604R08"
msgid "A rundown shed of uncertain vintage."
msgstr "A rundown shed of uncertain vintage."

#: 604R09
msgctxt "604R09"
msgid "A wooden door."
msgstr "A wooden door."

#: 604R10
msgctxt "604R10"
msgid "A shed with a view."
msgstr "A shed with a view."

#: 604R11
msgctxt "604R11"
msgid "Spike to the ground... might be a tad heavy too."
msgstr "Spike to the ground... might be a tad heavy too."

#: 604R12
msgctxt "604R12"
msgid "I can't remove that bolt by hand."
msgstr "I can't remove that bolt by hand."

#: 604R13
msgctxt "604R13"
msgid "Should I disconnect Dr. Twelve Tree's power? No, probably not a very good idea."
msgstr "Should I disconnect Dr. Twelve Tree's power? No, probably not a very good idea."

#: 604R14
msgctxt "604R14"
msgid "I'd need wire cutters to remove that."
msgstr "I'd need wire cutters to remove that."

#: 604R15
msgctxt "604R15"
msgid "If Dr. Twelve Trees had wanted the door open, she would have hooked the wire up herself."
msgstr "If Dr. Twelve Trees had wanted the door open, she would have hooked the wire up herself."

#: 604R24
msgctxt "604R24"
msgid "I have to do something to help Dr. Twelve Trees."
msgstr "I have to do something to help Dr. Twelve Trees."

#: 604R25
msgctxt "604R25"
msgid "The wire used to hook the door open."
msgstr "The wire used to hook the door open."

#: 604R26
msgctxt "604R26"
msgid "The portable generator."
msgstr "The portable generator."

#: 604R27
msgctxt "604R27"
msgid "A tool for unscrewing the spark plug."
msgstr "A tool for unscrewing the spark plug."

#: 604R27A
msgctxt "604R27A"
msgid "That wasn't there before."
msgstr "That wasn't there before."

#: 604R28
msgctxt "604R28"
msgid "Lucky that door was closed."
msgstr "Lucky that door was closed."

#: 604R29
msgctxt "604R29"
msgid "My one chance of coming and going undetected."
msgstr "My one chance of coming and going undetected."

#: 604R30
msgctxt "604R30"
msgid "I better not close it. I may need to make a quick getaway."
msgstr "I better not close it. I may need to make a quick getaway."

#: 604R31
msgctxt "604R31"
msgid "Spike to the ground, and far too heavy to throw at those villains."
msgstr "Spike to the ground, and far too heavy to throw at those villains."

#: 604R32
msgctxt "604R32"
msgid "Now the plug is loose. If I turn it anymore and don't have a stopper handy, I'll have gas all over the place."
msgstr "Now the plug is loose. If I turn it anymore and don't have a stopper handy, I'll have gas all over the place."

#: 604R32A
msgctxt "604R32A"
msgid "If I do that, I'll have gas all over the place."
msgstr "If I do that, I'll have gas all over the place."

#: 604R33
msgctxt "604R33"
msgid "Ripley, for heaven's sake! Getting yourself killed won't help Dr. Twelve Trees!"
msgstr "Ripley, for heaven's sake! Getting yourself killed won't help Dr. Twelve Trees!"

#: 604R34
msgctxt "604R34"
msgid "Now is not the time for drawing pictures."
msgstr "Now is not the time for drawing pictures."

#: 604R35
msgctxt "604R35"
msgid "How would that help?"
msgstr "How would that help?"

#: 604R36
msgctxt "604R36"
msgid "The pull cord handle is now plugging the drain opening."
msgstr "The pull cord handle is now plugging the drain opening."

#: 604R37
msgctxt "604R37"
msgid "We are back. And we are back. And we are back."
msgstr "We are back. And we are back. And we are back."

#: 604R38
msgctxt "604R38"
msgid "The pull cord is attached to the wire."
msgstr "The pull cord is attached to the wire."

#: 604R39
msgctxt "604R39"
msgid "There. With any luck, opening the door should yank the pull cord from the gas tank."
msgstr "There. With any luck, opening the door should yank the pull cord from the gas tank."

#: 604R40
msgctxt "604R40"
msgid "I don't know what I'm saying."
msgstr "I don't know what I'm saying."

#: 604R41
msgctxt "604R41"
msgid "Anybody entering the shed is in for a nasty surprise."
msgstr "Anybody entering the shed is in for a nasty surprise."

#: 604R41A
msgctxt "604R41A"
msgid "If I can just think this through, I may be able to help Dr. Twelve Trees."
msgstr "If I can just think this through, I may be able to help Dr. Twelve Trees."

#: 604R42
msgctxt "604R42"
msgid "A little pause... and we are back."
msgstr "A little pause... and we are back."

#: 604R43
msgctxt "604R43"
msgid "I'll need the pull cord to start it up."
msgstr "I'll need the pull cord to start it up."

#: 604R44
msgctxt "604R44"
msgid "The lighter's flame is now directly under the gas tank drain."
msgstr "The lighter's flame is now directly under the gas tank drain."

#: 604R45
msgctxt "604R45"
msgid "I don't know what to say."
msgstr "I don't know what to say."

#: 604R46
msgctxt "604R46"
msgid "Well, I could tie the pull cord to the wire, but I don't see any reason to do that right now."
msgstr "Well, I could tie the pull cord to the wire, but I don't see any reason to do that right now."

#: 604R47
msgctxt "604R47"
msgid "This is no time for sightseeing, Ripley."
msgstr "This is no time for sightseeing, Ripley."

#: 604R48
msgctxt "604R48"
msgid "The pull cord stretches from the wire to where it plugs the gas tank drain."
msgstr "The pull cord stretches from the wire to where it plugs the gas tank drain."

#: 604R49
msgctxt "604R49"
msgid "The drain bolt is too large for the faucet handle."
msgstr "The drain bolt is too large for the faucet handle."

#: 605R01
msgctxt "605R01"
msgid "Can you translate any of it?"
msgstr "Can you translate any of it?"

#: 605R02
msgctxt "605R02"
msgid "A sun-baked hilltop with a view that can only be found on Easter Island."
msgstr "A sun-baked hilltop with a view that can only be found on Easter Island."

#: 605R03
msgctxt "605R03"
msgid "These stone monoliths are awe-inspiring, seen this close-up."
msgstr "These stone monoliths are awe-inspiring, seen this close-up."

#: 605R04
msgctxt "605R04"
msgid "What's that?"
msgstr "What's that?"

#: 605R05
msgctxt "605R05"
msgid "Hmm, quite a woman."
msgstr "Hmm, quite a woman."

#: 605R06
msgctxt "605R06"
msgid "Beauty, brains, and married to science."
msgstr "Beauty, brains, and married to science."

#: 605R07
msgctxt "605R07"
msgid "Keep your mind on the quest, Ripley."
msgstr "Keep your mind on the quest, Ripley."

#: 605R08
msgctxt "605R08"
msgid "Remember, Mei is in China right now risking her life for you."
msgstr "Remember, Mei is in China right now risking her life for you."

#: 605R09
msgctxt "605R09"
msgid "That statue appears to be looking at Dr. Twelftree's. I don't blame it."
msgstr "That statue appears to be looking at Dr. Twelftree's. I don't blame it."

#: 605R10
msgctxt "605R10"
msgid "Where does that path lead?"
msgstr "Where does that path lead?"

#: 605R11
msgctxt "605R11"
msgid "Where does that go?"
msgstr "Where does that go?"

#: 605R12
msgctxt "605R12"
msgid "The magnificent statues look as if they were scattered about the island by giant children at play."
msgstr "The magnificent statues look as if they were scattered about the island by giant children at play."

#: 605R13
msgctxt "605R13"
msgid "I can use Easter Island as the subject of one of my cartoons."
msgstr "I can use Easter Island as the subject of one of my cartoons."

#: 605R14
msgctxt "605R14"
msgid "I already have a sketch of Easter Island."
msgstr "I already have a sketch of Easter Island."

#: 605R15
msgctxt "605R15"
msgid "Ouch!"
msgstr "Ouch!"

#: 605R16
msgctxt "605R16"
msgid "That torn sleeve came in handy after all."
msgstr "That torn sleeve came in handy after all."

#: 605R17
msgctxt "605R17"
msgid "Sorry."
msgstr "Sorry."

#: 605R26
msgctxt "605R26"
msgid "The top knot to the fallen statue."
msgstr "The top knot to the fallen statue."

#: 605R27
msgctxt "605R27"
msgid "The statue appears to be looking at the ground."
msgstr "The statue appears to be looking at the ground."

#: 605R28
msgctxt "605R28"
msgid "I burned my fingers on that pupil."
msgstr "I burned my fingers on that pupil."

#: 605R29
msgctxt "605R29"
msgid "The path to the quarry."
msgstr "The path to the quarry."

#: 605R30
msgctxt "605R30"
msgid "I wonder where that path leads."
msgstr "I wonder where that path leads."

#: 605R31
msgctxt "605R31"
msgid "The path to Watcher's Cove."
msgstr "The path to Watcher's Cove."

#: 605R32
msgctxt "605R32"
msgid "It's been roasting in the sun."
msgstr "It's been roasting in the sun."

#: 605R33
msgctxt "605R33"
msgid "Dr. Twelve Trees warned me obsidian can get mighty warm in the sun."
msgstr "Dr. Twelve Trees warned me obsidian can get mighty warm in the sun."

#: 605R34
msgctxt "605R34"
msgid "The path to that cove where I saw the old woman."
msgstr "The path to that cove where I saw the old woman."

#: 605R35
msgctxt "605R35"
msgid "Ancient glyphs."
msgstr "Ancient glyphs."

#: 605T01
msgctxt "605T01"
msgid "Here's a good example of Easter Island script."
msgstr "Here's a good example of Easter Island script."

#: 605T02
msgctxt "605T02"
msgid "No. No one can. That's why I went to see Master Lu's tablet in China. It wasn't much help, I'm afraid."
msgstr "No. No one can. That's why I went to see Master Lu's tablet in China. It wasn't much help, I'm afraid."

#: 605T03
msgctxt "605T03"
msgid "A top knot. Most of the completed statues used to have them."
msgstr "A top knot. Most of the completed statues used to have them."

#: 605T04
msgctxt "605T04"
msgid "The old quarry where they made the heads."
msgstr "The old quarry where they made the heads."

#: 605T05
msgctxt "605T05"
msgid "Watchers Cove."
msgstr "Watchers Cove."

#: 605T06
msgctxt "605T06"
msgid "The pupils are made of obsidian, Mr. Ripley. Black volcanic glass? It can get very hot on this island."
msgstr "The pupils are made of obsidian, Mr. Ripley. Black volcanic glass? It can get very hot on this island."

#: 605T07
msgctxt "605T07"
msgid "Mr. Ripley, there's enough theft on this island already without you adding to it."
msgstr "Mr. Ripley, there's enough theft on this island already without you adding to it."

#: 607R01
msgctxt "607R01"
msgid "The quarry stretches in all directions."
msgstr "The quarry stretches in all directions."

#: 607R02
msgctxt "607R02"
msgid "That massive boulder was obviously destined to become a top-knock."
msgstr "That massive boulder was obviously destined to become a top-knock."

#: 607R03
msgctxt "607R03"
msgid "A chunk of small rock not used to make the statues."
msgstr "A chunk of small rock not used to make the statues."

#: 607R04
msgctxt "607R04"
msgid "The ground is sun-baked clay."
msgstr "The ground is sun-baked clay."

#: 607R05
msgctxt "607R05"
msgid "A natural fissure in the rock. There's something in there."
msgstr "A natural fissure in the rock. There's something in there."

#: 607R05A
msgctxt "607R05A"
msgid "A natural fisher in the rock."
msgstr "A natural fisher in the rock."

#: 607R06
msgctxt "607R06"
msgid "The boulder is far too massive to take."
msgstr "The boulder is far too massive to take."

#: 607R07
msgctxt "607R07"
msgid "I could never lift a gray rock."
msgstr "I could never lift a gray rock."

#: 607R08
msgctxt "607R08"
msgid "The clay is as hard as rock."
msgstr "The clay is as hard as rock."

#: 607R09
msgctxt "607R09"
msgid "Considering how much trouble the old woman's ancestor went to concealing this, it must be important."
msgstr "Considering how much trouble the old woman's ancestor went to concealing this, it must be important."

#: 607R10
msgctxt "607R10"
msgid "I'll never be able to do anything worthwhile with a boulder that large."
msgstr "I'll never be able to do anything worthwhile with a boulder that large."

#: 607R11
msgctxt "607R11"
msgid "The clay is not very wet."
msgstr "The clay is not very wet."

#: 607R12
msgctxt "607R12"
msgid "The clay is slightly damp."
msgstr "The clay is slightly damp."

#: 607R13
msgctxt "607R13"
msgid "The clay is beginning to look a lot less parched."
msgstr "The clay is beginning to look a lot less parched."

#: 607R14
msgctxt "607R14"
msgid "The clay has a wet sheen to it."
msgstr "The clay has a wet sheen to it."

#: 607R15
msgctxt "607R15"
msgid "I'm a better cartoonist than I am a sculptor."
msgstr "I'm a better cartoonist than I am a sculptor."

#: 608O01
msgctxt "608O01"
msgid "One eye is missing."
msgstr "One eye is missing."

#: 608O02
msgctxt "608O02"
msgid "There is only one watching God, and it must have two eyes before it can see."
msgstr "There is only one watching God, and it must have two eyes before it can see."

#: 608O03
msgctxt "608O03"
msgid "If you have something to say to me..."
msgstr "If you have something to say to me..."

#: 608O04
msgctxt "608O04"
msgid "I pray..."
msgstr "I pray..."

#: 608O05
msgctxt "608O05"
msgid "Privacy."
msgstr "Privacy."

#: 608O06
msgctxt "608O06"
msgid "Is this all?"
msgstr "Is this all?"

#: 608O07
msgctxt "608O07"
msgid "This I is not complete."
msgstr "This I is not complete."

#: 608O08
msgctxt "608O08"
msgid "Find the missing part. Then the watching god will see again."
msgstr "Find the missing part. Then the watching god will see again."

#: 608O09
msgctxt "608O09"
msgid "Yes! Yes! Now the watching god will see again!"
msgstr "Yes! Yes! Now the watching god will see again!"

#: 608O09A
msgctxt "608O09A"
msgid "You are taller. Your deeds make you so."
msgstr "You are taller. Your deeds make you so."

#: 608O10
msgctxt "608O10"
msgid "Place your hands on the watching god."
msgstr "Place your hands on the watching god."

#: 608O11
msgctxt "608O11"
msgid "Spread your legs!"
msgstr "Spread your legs!"

#: 608O12
msgctxt "608O12"
msgid "Come here."
msgstr "Come here."

#: 608O13
msgctxt "608O13"
msgid "Place your hands on the hill."
msgstr "Place your hands on the hill."

#: 608O14
msgctxt "608O14"
msgid "There is something up there. I saw it when I replaced the eye."
msgstr "There is something up there. I saw it when I replaced the eye."

#: 608O15
msgctxt "608O15"
msgid "The bones of the grandfather of my grandfathers. He did not run away in fear. The short ears pushed the watching god on top of him. I will give his bones the rest they deserve, and all will honor him."
msgstr "The bones of the grandfather of my grandfathers. He did not run away in fear. The short ears pushed the watching god on top of him. I will give his bones the rest they deserve, and all will honor him."

#: 608O15A
msgctxt "608O15A"
msgid "The watching gods cease again, and my family's honor is restored. You are the one from my vision. May you find what you seek on Easter Island."
msgstr "The watching gods cease again, and my family's honor is restored. You are the one from my vision. May you find what you seek on Easter Island."

#: 608O16
msgctxt "608O16"
msgid "The grandfather of my grandfathers was the keeper of a great secret."
msgstr "The grandfather of my grandfathers was the keeper of a great secret."

#: 608O17
msgctxt "608O17"
msgid "You again."
msgstr "You again."

#: 608O18
msgctxt "608O18"
msgid "You can make the watching gods see again?"
msgstr "You can make the watching gods see again?"

#: 608O19
msgctxt "608O19"
msgid "Huuh!"
msgstr "Huuh!"

#: 608R01
msgctxt "608R01"
msgid "What happened to him?"
msgstr "What happened to him?"

#: 608R02
msgctxt "608R02"
msgid "Fascinating!"
msgstr "Fascinating!"

#: 608R03
msgctxt "608R03"
msgid "Thanks, doctor."
msgstr "Thanks, doctor."

#: 608R04
msgctxt "608R04"
msgid "I won't disturb her prayers again unless I find a way to help her."
msgstr "I won't disturb her prayers again unless I find a way to help her."

#: 608R04A
msgctxt "608R04A"
msgid "I won't disturb her prayers unless I find a way to help her."
msgstr "I won't disturb her prayers unless I find a way to help her."

#: 608R05
msgctxt "608R05"
msgid "Hard for the watching God to see with its face buried in the hillside like that."
msgstr "Hard for the watching God to see with its face buried in the hillside like that."

#: 608R06
msgctxt "608R06"
msgid "That stone looks like it's been wedged under the base of the statue."
msgstr "That stone looks like it's been wedged under the base of the statue."

#: 608R07
msgctxt "608R07"
msgid "The statue obviously stood on that base, facing the sea."
msgstr "The statue obviously stood on that base, facing the sea."

#: 608R08
msgctxt "608R08"
msgid "Lava. Long ago this mountain must have been an active volcano."
msgstr "Lava. Long ago this mountain must have been an active volcano."

#: 608R09
msgctxt "608R09"
msgid "Lots of crevices and holes in the lava."
msgstr "Lots of crevices and holes in the lava."

#: 608R10
msgctxt "608R10"
msgid "That hole is much larger than the others."
msgstr "That hole is much larger than the others."

#: 608R11
msgctxt "608R11"
msgid "Eons ago, this ravine provided a natural path for lava flowing to the sea."
msgstr "Eons ago, this ravine provided a natural path for lava flowing to the sea."

#: 608R12
msgctxt "608R12"
msgid "Reminds me of one of those comical birds, puffins."
msgstr "Reminds me of one of those comical birds, puffins."

#: 608R12A
msgctxt "608R12A"
msgid "Shame there's a piece missing. It might make an interesting exhibit in the auditorium."
msgstr "Shame there's a piece missing. It might make an interesting exhibit in the auditorium."

#: 608R13
msgctxt "608R13"
msgid "That stump is practically petrified."
msgstr "That stump is practically petrified."

#: 608R14
msgctxt "608R14"
msgid "She looks as if she's squatted here all her life, buffeted by the elements, growing old, but never swerving from her vigilant faith in her ancestor."
msgstr "She looks as if she's squatted here all her life, buffeted by the elements, growing old, but never swerving from her vigilant faith in her ancestor."

#: 608R14A
msgctxt "608R14A"
msgid "Even if she can't help me, it would give me a great deal of satisfaction to end her vigil."
msgstr "Even if she can't help me, it would give me a great deal of satisfaction to end her vigil."

#: 608R14B
msgctxt "608R14B"
msgid "The old woman has never lost her faith."
msgstr "The old woman has never lost her faith."

#: 608R15
msgctxt "608R15"
msgid "The watching god can see again."
msgstr "The watching god can see again."

#: 608R16
msgctxt "608R16"
msgid "Lots of people can see with one eye."
msgstr "Lots of people can see with one eye."

#: 608R17
msgctxt "608R17"
msgid "Oh, this is going to be harder than I thought."
msgstr "Oh, this is going to be harder than I thought."

#: 608R18
msgctxt "608R18"
msgid "It's now wedged beneath several tons of statues."
msgstr "It's now wedged beneath several tons of statues."

#: 608R19
msgctxt "608R19"
msgid "Without a block and tackle to move the statue, that stump is staying where it is."
msgstr "Without a block and tackle to move the statue, that stump is staying where it is."

#: 608R20
msgctxt "608R20"
msgid "I can use Easter Island as the subject of one of my cartoons."
msgstr "I can use Easter Island as the subject of one of my cartoons."

#: 608R21
msgctxt "608R21"
msgid "I already have a sketch of Easter Island."
msgstr "I already have a sketch of Easter Island."

#: 608R22
msgctxt "608R22"
msgid "I don't know how the Easter Islanders toted these statues around, but I have no way of transporting the head."
msgstr "I don't know how the Easter Islanders toted these statues around, but I have no way of transporting the head."

#: 608R31
msgctxt "608R31"
msgid "May I talk to you for a moment?"
msgstr "May I talk to you for a moment?"

#: 608R32
msgctxt "608R32"
msgid "Tell me about yourself."
msgstr "Tell me about yourself."

#: 608R33
msgctxt "608R33"
msgid "What do you pray for?"
msgstr "What do you pray for?"

#: 608R34
msgctxt "608R34"
msgid "I wonder who she is."
msgstr "I wonder who she is."

#: 608R35
msgctxt "608R35"
msgid "I'd better not disturb her prayers again until I learn more about her."
msgstr "I'd better not disturb her prayers again until I learn more about her."

#: 608R35A
msgctxt "608R35A"
msgid "I'd better not disturb her prayers until I learn more about her."
msgstr "I'd better not disturb her prayers until I learn more about her."

#: 608R36
msgctxt "608R36"
msgid "The statue's face is buried in the hillside."
msgstr "The statue's face is buried in the hillside."

#: 608R37
msgctxt "608R37"
msgid "I suspect there is an interesting story behind her being here."
msgstr "I suspect there is an interesting story behind her being here."

#: 608R38
msgctxt "608R38"
msgid "The watching god is facing the ocean, but according to the old woman, it still needs a second eye to see."
msgstr "The watching god is facing the ocean, but according to the old woman, it still needs a second eye to see."

#: 608R39
msgctxt "608R39"
msgid "That stone was used to keep the statue's face lodged against the hillside."
msgstr "That stone was used to keep the statue's face lodged against the hillside."

#: 608R40
msgctxt "608R40"
msgid "The stump fills the hole."
msgstr "The stump fills the hole."

#: 608R41
msgctxt "608R41"
msgid "That petrified stump is pinned by the pole."
msgstr "That petrified stump is pinned by the pole."

#: 608R42
msgctxt "608R42"
msgid "I'm afraid Dr. Twelve Trees won't be getting her pull back."
msgstr "I'm afraid Dr. Twelve Trees won't be getting her pull back."

#: 608R43
msgctxt "608R43"
msgid "Well, yes."
msgstr "Well, yes."

#: 608R44
msgctxt "608R44"
msgid "I'm an adventurer, not an optician."
msgstr "I'm an adventurer, not an optician."

#: 608R45
msgctxt "608R45"
msgid "At long last, I may be able to help her."
msgstr "At long last, I may be able to help her."

#: 608R46
msgctxt "608R46"
msgid "Why? Thank you!"
msgstr "Why? Thank you!"

#: 608R47
msgctxt "608R47"
msgid "Ah, some sort of arcane ritual. Dr. Twelve-Tree should see this."
msgstr "Ah, some sort of arcane ritual. Dr. Twelve-Tree should see this."

#: 608R48
msgctxt "608R48"
msgid "Madame, I must be out of shape. Your feather-like form is beginning to tell on me, I'm afraid."
msgstr "Madame, I must be out of shape. Your feather-like form is beginning to tell on me, I'm afraid."

#: 608R49
msgctxt "608R49"
msgid "And spread my legs."
msgstr "And spread my legs."

#: 608R50
msgctxt "608R50"
msgid "Can you help me? I'm looking for Easter Island artifacts."
msgstr "Can you help me? I'm looking for Easter Island artifacts."

#: 608R51
msgctxt "608R51"
msgid "A great secret, eh? I wonder what you meant by that."
msgstr "A great secret, eh? I wonder what you meant by that."

#: 608R51A
msgctxt "608R51A"
msgid "A great secret, eh?"
msgstr "A great secret, eh?"

#: 608R52
msgctxt "608R52"
msgid "The watching God can see once more."
msgstr "The watching God can see once more."

#: 608R53
msgctxt "608R53"
msgid "Oh, does it?"
msgstr "Oh, does it?"

#: 608R53A
msgctxt "608R53A"
msgid "The watcher's body was in a hole up there."
msgstr "The watcher's body was in a hole up there."

#: 608R54
msgctxt "608R54"
msgid "Now, why didn't I think of that?"
msgstr "Now, why didn't I think of that?"

#: 608R55
msgctxt "608R55"
msgid "See anything, doctor?"
msgstr "See anything, doctor?"

#: 608R56
msgctxt "608R56"
msgid "Uh, sorry!"
msgstr "Uh, sorry!"

#: 608R57
msgctxt "608R57"
msgid "Well, not usually, doctor. Uh, uh, no."
msgstr "Well, not usually, doctor. Uh, uh, no."

#: 608R58
msgctxt "608R58"
msgid "What are they?"
msgstr "What are they?"

#: 608R59
msgctxt "608R59"
msgid "Gosh, what a find."
msgstr "Gosh, what a find."

#: 608R60
msgctxt "608R60"
msgid "I'm not sure why."
msgstr "I'm not sure why."

#: 608R61
msgctxt "608R61"
msgid "The good doctor dropped her lighter."
msgstr "The good doctor dropped her lighter."

#: 608R62
msgctxt "608R62"
msgid "The old woman's ancestor took several secrets to his grave. A horn, and some sort of navigation chart, or maybe simply a map."
msgstr "The old woman's ancestor took several secrets to his grave. A horn, and some sort of navigation chart, or maybe simply a map."

#: 608R62A
msgctxt "608R62A"
msgid "The old woman's ancestor took several secrets to his grave."
msgstr "The old woman's ancestor took several secrets to his grave."

#: 608R63
msgctxt "608R63"
msgid "The stone is far too heavy to shift."
msgstr "The stone is far too heavy to shift."

#: 608R64
msgctxt "608R64"
msgid "I could fill the horn with water, but it would run right out again."
msgstr "I could fill the horn with water, but it would run right out again."

#: 608R65
msgctxt "608R65"
msgid "I now have a horn full of water."
msgstr "I now have a horn full of water."

#: 608R66
msgctxt "608R66"
msgid "Doctor, twelve trees lighter. She dropped it during our unfortunate tumble."
msgstr "Doctor, twelve trees lighter. She dropped it during our unfortunate tumble."

#: 608R67
msgctxt "608R67"
msgid "Madam, excuse me."
msgstr "Madam, excuse me."

#: 608R68
msgctxt "608R68"
msgid "I'm pretty sure I have what you need."
msgstr "I'm pretty sure I have what you need."

#: 608R69
msgctxt "608R69"
msgid "I won't disturb her prayers again unless I find a way to help her."
msgstr "I won't disturb her prayers again unless I find a way to help her."

#: 608R70
msgctxt "608R70"
msgid "Madam, I have what you need."
msgstr "Madam, I have what you need."

#: 608R71
msgctxt "608R71"
msgid "Yes!"
msgstr "Yes!"

#: 608R72
msgctxt "608R72"
msgid "It's full to the brim."
msgstr "It's full to the brim."

#: 608R73
msgctxt "608R73"
msgid "The sea is quite calm in this protected cove."
msgstr "The sea is quite calm in this protected cove."

#: 608R74
msgctxt "608R74"
msgid "I'll have to move the pole first."
msgstr "I'll have to move the pole first."

#: 608R75
msgctxt "608R75"
msgid "The pole is resting on the stone."
msgstr "The pole is resting on the stone."

#: 608R76
msgctxt "608R76"
msgid "The driftwood stump is wedged into the hole."
msgstr "The driftwood stump is wedged into the hole."

#: 608R77
msgctxt "608R77"
msgid "Hitting the statue with the pole won't accomplish anything."
msgstr "Hitting the statue with the pole won't accomplish anything."

#: 608T01
msgctxt "608T01"
msgid "The night of the attack, the short ears toppled the statue face down so that they could pass without the gods seeing them."
msgstr "The night of the attack, the short ears toppled the statue face down so that they could pass without the gods seeing them."

#: 608T01A
msgctxt "608T01A"
msgid "There she is. Supposedly a descendant of the original Watcher."
msgstr "There she is. Supposedly a descendant of the original Watcher."

#: 608T02
msgctxt "608T02"
msgid "He vanished. Some say he ran away in fear when the short ears approached. But the old woman refuses to believe her ancestor was a coward. She comes here every day to pray to the watching God. She believes, if it can be made to see again, all will know the truth of that night."
msgstr "He vanished. Some say he ran away in fear when the short ears approached. But the old woman refuses to believe her ancestor was a coward. She comes here every day to pray to the watching God. She believes, if it can be made to see again, all will know the truth of that night."

#: 608T03
msgctxt "608T03"
msgid "I have long suspected that she knows more than she'll say. Some family tradition, perhaps, that could help both of us in our quests. Good luck, Mr. Ripley. I have to get back to my dig."
msgstr "I have long suspected that she knows more than she'll say. Some family tradition, perhaps, that could help both of us in our quests. Good luck, Mr. Ripley. I have to get back to my dig."

#: 608T04
msgctxt "608T04"
msgid "How did you ever manage to shift that statue?"
msgstr "How did you ever manage to shift that statue?"

#: 608T05
msgctxt "608T05"
msgid "Hey, that looks like my pole!"
msgstr "Hey, that looks like my pole!"

#: 608T06
msgctxt "608T06"
msgid "I have a great idea. You stand against the hill and give me a boost up."
msgstr "I have a great idea. You stand against the hill and give me a boost up."

#: 608T07
msgctxt "608T07"
msgid "Wait a second!"
msgstr "Wait a second!"

#: 608T08
msgctxt "608T08"
msgid "There... there's something here, all right."
msgstr "There... there's something here, all right."

#: 608T09
msgctxt "608T09"
msgid "Mr. Ripley, do you continually tear off the clothes of every woman you meet?"
msgstr "Mr. Ripley, do you continually tear off the clothes of every woman you meet?"

#: 608T10
msgctxt "608T10"
msgid "Sticks, a red stone, a scallop shell, a starfish, a shark's tooth and a seahorse all tied with grass, and a horn made from wheelbone."
msgstr "Sticks, a red stone, a scallop shell, a starfish, a shark's tooth and a seahorse all tied with grass, and a horn made from wheelbone."

#: 608T11
msgctxt "608T11"
msgid "The horn might be of interest to you, but it's too recent for me. Not more than four or five hundred years old. As for the other, I've seen something like it before. The islanders used them as navigation charts. That redstone in the center comes from the quarry. Not of much archaeological significance, unfortunately."
msgstr "The horn might be of interest to you, but it's too recent for me. Not more than four or five hundred years old. As for the other, I've seen something like it before. The islanders used them as navigation charts. That redstone in the center comes from the quarry. Not of much archaeological significance, unfortunately."

#: 608T11A
msgctxt "608T11A"
msgid "Hmm, looks like a dead end. I have to get back to my dig."
msgstr "Hmm, looks like a dead end. I have to get back to my dig."

#: 608T12
msgctxt "608T12"
msgid "Will you be staying on Easter Island much longer, Mr. Ripley?"
msgstr "Will you be staying on Easter Island much longer, Mr. Ripley?"

#: 608T13
msgctxt "608T13"
msgid "If you are, I'd better send for a trunk of new clothes."
msgstr "If you are, I'd better send for a trunk of new clothes."

#: 610K01
msgctxt "610K01"
msgid "It's hot here. I can't stand heat."
msgstr "It's hot here. I can't stand heat."

#: 610K02
msgctxt "610K02"
msgid "I don't like to sweat. Peasants sweat. I am not a peasant."
msgstr "I don't like to sweat. Peasants sweat. I am not a peasant."

#: 610K03
msgctxt "610K03"
msgid "She's not paying attention, Shen Gao. I'm insulted."
msgstr "She's not paying attention, Shen Gao. I'm insulted."

#: 610K04
msgctxt "610K04"
msgid "This could be so simple. You tell us where Mr. Ripley is, you tell us what he has learned, you win a prize. We give you your life. What could be simpler than that?"
msgstr "This could be so simple. You tell us where Mr. Ripley is, you tell us what he has learned, you win a prize. We give you your life. What could be simpler than that?"

#: 610K05
msgctxt "610K05"
msgid "You may hit her, yes."
msgstr "You may hit her, yes."

#: 610K06
msgctxt "610K06"
msgid "You will answer my questions, doctor. The only uncertainty in the entire process is how much pain you must endure first."
msgstr "You will answer my questions, doctor. The only uncertainty in the entire process is how much pain you must endure first."

#: 610K07
msgctxt "610K07"
msgid "Where is Mr. Ripley?"
msgstr "Where is Mr. Ripley?"

#: 610K08
msgctxt "610K08"
msgid "Why did Mr. Ripley come to Easter Island?"
msgstr "Why did Mr. Ripley come to Easter Island?"

#: 610K09
msgctxt "610K09"
msgid "What has Mr. Ripley learned?"
msgstr "What has Mr. Ripley learned?"

#: 610K10
msgctxt "610K10"
msgid "Does Mr. Ripley know Master Lu visited here?"
msgstr "Does Mr. Ripley know Master Lu visited here?"

#: 610K11
msgctxt "610K11"
msgid "Did you find anything that might help decipher Lou's tablet?"
msgstr "Did you find anything that might help decipher Lou's tablet?"

#: 610K12
msgctxt "610K12"
msgid "You may hit her, Shen Gao."
msgstr "You may hit her, Shen Gao."

#: 610K13
msgctxt "610K13"
msgid "Now, we begin again."
msgstr "Now, we begin again."

#: 610K14
msgctxt "610K14"
msgid "Mr. Ripley, how nice of you to join us. Now we will learn what we need to know."
msgstr "Mr. Ripley, how nice of you to join us. Now we will learn what we need to know."

#: 610R01
msgctxt "610R01"
msgid "Looks like the beasts have roughed her up pretty good."
msgstr "Looks like the beasts have roughed her up pretty good."

#: 610R02
msgctxt "610R02"
msgid "Nasty piece of work."
msgstr "Nasty piece of work."

#: 610R03
msgctxt "610R03"
msgid "From the looks of them, wrestling those ruffians into submission is not an option."
msgstr "From the looks of them, wrestling those ruffians into submission is not an option."

#: 610R04
msgctxt "610R04"
msgid "Dr. Twelve Trees Hut"
msgstr "Dr. Twelve Trees Hut"

#: 610R05
msgctxt "610R05"
msgid "The excavation."
msgstr "The excavation."

#: 610R06
msgctxt "610R06"
msgid "The generator shed."
msgstr "The generator shed."

#: 610R07
msgctxt "610R07"
msgid "I wonder if that window is locked."
msgstr "I wonder if that window is locked."

#: 610R08
msgctxt "610R08"
msgid "The electrical power cable."
msgstr "The electrical power cable."

#: 610R09
msgctxt "610R09"
msgid "The cliff rises over thirty feet above the sea."
msgstr "The cliff rises over thirty feet above the sea."

#: 610R10
msgctxt "610R10"
msgid "Just walking up to them may not have been an idea worthy of Tom Swift."
msgstr "Just walking up to them may not have been an idea worthy of Tom Swift."

#: 610R11
msgctxt "610R11"
msgid "Somehow, I don't think they are in the mood for musical accompaniment."
msgstr "Somehow, I don't think they are in the mood for musical accompaniment."

#: 610R12
msgctxt "610R12"
msgid "Beating up a defenseless woman? So that's your game, is it?"
msgstr "Beating up a defenseless woman? So that's your game, is it?"

#: 610R13
msgctxt "610R13"
msgid "Sometimes the truth hurts."
msgstr "Sometimes the truth hurts."

#: 610R14
msgctxt "610R14"
msgid "Doctor Twelve Trees, may I be of any assistance?"
msgstr "Doctor Twelve Trees, may I be of any assistance?"

#: 610R15
msgctxt "610R15"
msgid "Maybe I could have been of more assistance alive."
msgstr "Maybe I could have been of more assistance alive."

#: 610R16
msgctxt "610R16"
msgid "Ripley, for heaven's sakes, getting yourself killed won't help Dr. Twelve Trees."
msgstr "Ripley, for heaven's sakes, getting yourself killed won't help Dr. Twelve Trees."

#: 610R17
msgctxt "610R17"
msgid "Looks like I'm out of time... and out of luck."
msgstr "Looks like I'm out of time... and out of luck."

#: 610R18
msgctxt "610R18"
msgid "Now is not the time for drawing pictures."
msgstr "Now is not the time for drawing pictures."

#: 610R20
msgctxt "610R20"
msgid "How would that help?"
msgstr "How would that help?"

#: 610S01
msgctxt "610S01"
msgid "Now..."
msgstr "Now..."

#: 610T01
msgctxt "610T01"
msgid "You. If you think I'm going to tell you anything."
msgstr "You. If you think I'm going to tell you anything."

#: 615R01
msgctxt "615R01"
msgid "Doctor, are you okay?"
msgstr "Doctor, are you okay?"

#: 615R02
msgctxt "615R02"
msgid "Oh, uh, fine, uh..."
msgstr "Oh, uh, fine, uh..."

#: 615R02A
msgctxt "615R02A"
msgid "I'm Robert."
msgstr "I'm Robert."

#: 615R03
msgctxt "615R03"
msgid "I've crossed paths with them before. They're working for whoever is after the seal. I'm very sorry you got stuck in the middle of this."
msgstr "I've crossed paths with them before. They're working for whoever is after the seal. I'm very sorry you got stuck in the middle of this."

#: 615R04
msgctxt "615R04"
msgid "Maybe you can. I think I've found something. What do you make of it?"
msgstr "Maybe you can. I think I've found something. What do you make of it?"

#: 615R05
msgctxt "615R05"
msgid "Uh, no, that's what I was asking."
msgstr "Uh, no, that's what I was asking."

#: 615R06
msgctxt "615R06"
msgid "And that stick?"
msgstr "And that stick?"

#: 615R07
msgctxt "615R07"
msgid "Uh, what is Samantha?"
msgstr "Uh, what is Samantha?"

#: 615R08
msgctxt "615R08"
msgid "Ah, well, gosh, good!"
msgstr "Ah, well, gosh, good!"

#: 615R09
msgctxt "615R09"
msgid "The symbols you recognize, where did you see them before?"
msgstr "The symbols you recognize, where did you see them before?"

#: 615R10
msgctxt "615R10"
msgid "Doctor, uh, Samantha, thank you."
msgstr "Doctor, uh, Samantha, thank you."

#: 615R11
msgctxt "615R11"
msgid "You may have the stick to aid your research."
msgstr "You may have the stick to aid your research."

#: 615R12
msgctxt "615R12"
msgid "I'd better make a sketch of these glyphs. You may have the stick to aid your research."
msgstr "I'd better make a sketch of these glyphs. You may have the stick to aid your research."

#: 615R13
msgctxt "615R13"
msgid "Oh, here is your spark plug tool. I, uh, borrowed it."
msgstr "Oh, here is your spark plug tool. I, uh, borrowed it."

#: 615R14
msgctxt "615R14"
msgid "Yes, with these glyphs I'm one step farther on my quest, but the end isn't in sight yet."
msgstr "Yes, with these glyphs I'm one step farther on my quest, but the end isn't in sight yet."

#: 615R15
msgctxt "615R15"
msgid "Maybe we will."
msgstr "Maybe we will."

#: 615T01
msgctxt "615T01"
msgid "Mr. Ripley, after saving my life, you've earned the right to call me Samantha."
msgstr "Mr. Ripley, after saving my life, you've earned the right to call me Samantha."

#: 615T02
msgctxt "615T02"
msgid "Yes, you are."
msgstr "Yes, you are."

#: 615T03
msgctxt "615T03"
msgid "But who were they?"
msgstr "But who were they?"

#: 615T04
msgctxt "615T04"
msgid "I misjudged you, Robert. The fate of the world may rest in your hands. I wish I could do more to help."
msgstr "I misjudged you, Robert. The fate of the world may rest in your hands. I wish I could do more to help."

#: 615T05
msgctxt "615T05"
msgid "Huh, a rongo-rongo, definitely, but... Robert, do you know what this is?"
msgstr "Huh, a rongo-rongo, definitely, but... Robert, do you know what this is?"

#: 615T06
msgctxt "615T06"
msgid "Centuries ago, Dutch slavers carried off the last of the islanders who could read and write. Before they did, one of the islanders must have tried to record the language so that later generations could relearn it."
msgstr "Centuries ago, Dutch slavers carried off the last of the islanders who could read and write. Before they did, one of the islanders must have tried to record the language so that later generations could relearn it."

#: 615T07
msgctxt "615T07"
msgid "These pictures are not writing. They are all the same, but each set contains one more picture than the last. It's obvious, Robert!"
msgstr "These pictures are not writing. They are all the same, but each set contains one more picture than the last. It's obvious, Robert!"

#: 615T08
msgctxt "615T08"
msgid "They are numbers. One or first, two or second, and so on."
msgstr "They are numbers. One or first, two or second, and so on."

#: 615T08A
msgctxt "615T08A"
msgid "The stick you found, we can at last begin a translation."
msgstr "The stick you found, we can at last begin a translation."

#: 615T09
msgctxt "615T09"
msgid "On Master Lu's tablet."
msgstr "On Master Lu's tablet."

#: 615T10
msgctxt "615T10"
msgid "Under the circumstances, I won't complain."
msgstr "Under the circumstances, I won't complain."

#: 615T10A
msgctxt "615T10A"
msgid "You... you have to go now, don't you?"
msgstr "You... you have to go now, don't you?"

#: 615T11
msgctxt "615T11"
msgid "Well, good luck. Maybe we'll run into each other again in some forgotten corner of the world someday."
msgstr "Well, good luck. Maybe we'll run into each other again in some forgotten corner of the world someday."

#: 623R01
msgctxt "623R01"
msgid "The stone used to fashion the top knots of the statues."
msgstr "The stone used to fashion the top knots of the statues."

#: 623R02
msgctxt "623R02"
msgid "One of Easter Island's famed statues."
msgstr "One of Easter Island's famed statues."

#: 623R03
msgctxt "623R03"
msgid "The quarry is littered with great chunks of stone."
msgstr "The quarry is littered with great chunks of stone."

#: 623R04
msgctxt "623R04"
msgid "A patch of clay."
msgstr "A patch of clay."

#: 623R05
msgctxt "623R05"
msgid "Mist clings to the cool walls of the quarry, resisting the hot sun overhead."
msgstr "Mist clings to the cool walls of the quarry, resisting the hot sun overhead."

#: 625R01
msgctxt "625R01"
msgid "There's a starfish carved into the rock."
msgstr "There's a starfish carved into the rock."

#: 626R01
msgctxt "626R01"
msgid "There's a seahorse carved into the rock."
msgstr "There's a seahorse carved into the rock."

#: 644R01
msgctxt "644R01"
msgid "There's a scallop carved into the rock."
msgstr "There's a scallop carved into the rock."

#: 651R01
msgctxt "651R01"
msgid "There's a shark's tooth carved into the rock."
msgstr "There's a shark's tooth carved into the rock."

#: 701R01
msgctxt "701R01"
msgid "Good day!"
msgstr "Good day!"

#: 701R02
msgctxt "701R02"
msgid "My name is Robert Ripley."
msgstr "My name is Robert Ripley."

#: 701R03
msgctxt "701R03"
msgid "I'm on the trail of a very elusive Chinese gentleman called Master Lu."
msgstr "I'm on the trail of a very elusive Chinese gentleman called Master Lu."

#: 701R04
msgctxt "701R04"
msgid "No, but I believe he passed through here some 21 centuries ago."
msgstr "No, but I believe he passed through here some 21 centuries ago."

#: 701R05
msgctxt "701R05"
msgid "Is there anyone here I can talk to who knows the history of this place?"
msgstr "Is there anyone here I can talk to who knows the history of this place?"

#: 701R06
msgctxt "701R06"
msgid "Can you direct me to the temple?"
msgstr "Can you direct me to the temple?"

#: 701R07
msgctxt "701R07"
msgid "Many thanks, uh..."
msgstr "Many thanks, uh..."

#: 701R08
msgctxt "701R08"
msgid "Thanks, Terenjit."
msgstr "Thanks, Terenjit."

#: 701R10
msgctxt "701R10"
msgid "That's an unusual looking skin. Polar bear?"
msgstr "That's an unusual looking skin. Polar bear?"

#: 701R11
msgctxt "701R11"
msgid "Yeti? The abominable snowman of the Himalayas? Would you be interested in selling it?"
msgstr "Yeti? The abominable snowman of the Himalayas? Would you be interested in selling it?"

#: 701R12
msgctxt "701R12"
msgid "No kidding."
msgstr "No kidding."

#: 701R13
msgctxt "701R13"
msgid "A genuine Yeti skin hanging in a travel office. Unlikely."
msgstr "A genuine Yeti skin hanging in a travel office. Unlikely."

#: 701R14
msgctxt "701R14"
msgid "Scenes from the top of the world. The Chumbi Valley. Mount Kachinjunga, nearly as tall as Everest. Sherpas. Monasteries perched on the sides of cliffs. Even tropical scenes from the south. A fascinating region."
msgstr "Scenes from the top of the world. The Chumbi Valley. Mount Kachinjunga, nearly as tall as Everest. Sherpas. Monasteries perched on the sides of cliffs. Even tropical scenes from the south. A fascinating region."

#: 701R15
msgctxt "701R15"
msgid "Authentic prayer wheels of the Himalayas."
msgstr "Authentic prayer wheels of the Himalayas."

#: 701R17
msgctxt "701R17"
msgid "The Himalayas. Is there a more majestic and mysterious mountain range on this planet?"
msgstr "The Himalayas. Is there a more majestic and mysterious mountain range on this planet?"

#: 701R19
msgctxt "701R19"
msgid "A genuine Sikkimese prayer wheel."
msgstr "A genuine Sikkimese prayer wheel."

#: 701R20
msgctxt "701R20"
msgid "A bright looking young man, as you'd expect from Posh Express."
msgstr "A bright looking young man, as you'd expect from Posh Express."

#: 701R21
msgctxt "701R21"
msgid "One brochure on prayer wheels should be enough for any traveler."
msgstr "One brochure on prayer wheels should be enough for any traveler."

#: 701R24
msgctxt "701R24"
msgid "The Yeti skin, if that's what it is, belongs to Posh Express."
msgstr "The Yeti skin, if that's what it is, belongs to Posh Express."

#: 701R25
msgctxt "701R25"
msgid "The prayer wheel contains a prayer to protect travelers."
msgstr "The prayer wheel contains a prayer to protect travelers."

#: 701R35
msgctxt "701R35"
msgid "A sketch of a Yeti skin would be even more difficult to believe than the skin itself, and there is nothing else of interest to sketch here."
msgstr "A sketch of a Yeti skin would be even more difficult to believe than the skin itself, and there is nothing else of interest to sketch here."

#: 701R36
msgctxt "701R36"
msgid "I'd rather buy that unusual looking skin if there is a story behind it, and there is nothing else of interest to sketch here."
msgstr "I'd rather buy that unusual looking skin if there is a story behind it, and there is nothing else of interest to sketch here."

#: 701R37
msgctxt "701R37"
msgid "Hello, Taranjeet."
msgstr "Hello, Taranjeet."

#: 701R38
msgctxt "701R38"
msgid "I'd like to send a message to an associate of mine in Peiping. Her name is Mei Chen."
msgstr "I'd like to send a message to an associate of mine in Peiping. Her name is Mei Chen."

#: 701R39
msgctxt "701R39"
msgid "Dear Robert, with the help of scholars from the Imperial School, I have translated the early Chinese characters you sent me. They agree that the Chinese is a translation of the ancient Sikkimese script on the palm frond you found in the temple. I'll give you the translation when I see you next."
msgstr "Dear Robert, with the help of scholars from the Imperial School, I have translated the early Chinese characters you sent me. They agree that the Chinese is a translation of the ancient Sikkimese script on the palm frond you found in the temple. I'll give you the translation when I see you next."

#: 701R39A
msgctxt "701R39A"
msgid "It's good I'm staying with my grandmother. I can look after her, while I try to secure our travel permits. But Peiping is becoming a very frightening place, little resembling the fine city I remember as a child. If I don't see you when you return to Peiping, it's only because I'm spending almost every waking hour in government offices, trying to get our permits. I miss you with all my heart, May."
msgstr "It's good I'm staying with my grandmother. I can look after her, while I try to secure our travel permits. But Peiping is becoming a very frightening place, little resembling the fine city I remember as a child. If I don't see you when you return to Peiping, it's only because I'm spending almost every waking hour in government offices, trying to get our permits. I miss you with all my heart, May."

#: 701R40
msgctxt "701R40"
msgid "Taranjeet is an extremely helpful young man."
msgstr "Taranjeet is an extremely helpful young man."

#: 701R41
msgctxt "701R41"
msgid "For the life of me, I can't remember if I reminded my landlady to water the plants in my apartment."
msgstr "For the life of me, I can't remember if I reminded my landlady to water the plants in my apartment."

#: 701R42
msgctxt "701R42"
msgid "May will be able to find someone to translate the ancient Chinese characters from the temple."
msgstr "May will be able to find someone to translate the ancient Chinese characters from the temple."

#: 701X01
msgctxt "701X01"
msgid "Sat Sri Akal, Sahib. How may I assist you?"
msgstr "Sat Sri Akal, Sahib. How may I assist you?"

#: 701X02
msgctxt "701X02"
msgid "Ah, Mr. Ripley, there is a message for you."
msgstr "Ah, Mr. Ripley, there is a message for you."

#: 701X02A
msgctxt "701X02A"
msgid "There is a message for you."
msgstr "There is a message for you."

#: 701X03
msgctxt "701X03"
msgid "Ah, Mr. Ripley, there are messages for you."
msgstr "Ah, Mr. Ripley, there are messages for you."

#: 701X03A
msgctxt "701X03A"
msgid "There are messages for you."
msgstr "There are messages for you."

#: 701X04
msgctxt "701X04"
msgid "Does this gentleman reside in Sakim, sahib?"
msgstr "Does this gentleman reside in Sakim, sahib?"

#: 701X05
msgctxt "701X05"
msgid "Twenty-one centuries? I have not had the honor of working here that long."
msgstr "Twenty-one centuries? I have not had the honor of working here that long."

#: 701X06
msgctxt "701X06"
msgid "There are holy men at a temple near the village where I was born. It is said that they were here before all others."
msgstr "There are holy men at a temple near the village where I was born. It is said that they were here before all others."

#: 701X07
msgctxt "701X07"
msgid "Certainly, sahib."
msgstr "Certainly, sahib."

#: 701X07A
msgctxt "701X07A"
msgid "This road will take you to the Temple of the Hidden Way."
msgstr "This road will take you to the Temple of the Hidden Way."

#: 701X08
msgctxt "701X08"
msgid "Terenjit sahib."
msgstr "Terenjit sahib."

#: 701X09
msgctxt "701X09"
msgid "Yeti sahib."
msgstr "Yeti sahib."

#: 701X10
msgctxt "701X10"
msgid "No, Sahib, they are very rare."
msgstr "No, Sahib, they are very rare."

#: 701X11
msgctxt "701X11"
msgid "Sat Sri Akal, Mr. Ripley."
msgstr "Sat Sri Akal, Mr. Ripley."

#: 702G01
msgctxt "702G01"
msgid "You are a member of the temple!"
msgstr "You are a member of the temple!"

#: 702G02
msgctxt "702G02"
msgid "Forgive me, I was prepared to bar your way."
msgstr "Forgive me, I was prepared to bar your way."

#: 702G03
msgctxt "702G03"
msgid "We all must be vigilant, especially after last week. You may pass!"
msgstr "We all must be vigilant, especially after last week. You may pass!"

#: 702G04
msgctxt "702G04"
msgid "I understand. We all must question every day if we ever hope to find true enlightenment."
msgstr "I understand. We all must question every day if we ever hope to find true enlightenment."

#: 702G05
msgctxt "702G05"
msgid "How may I serve you?"
msgstr "How may I serve you?"

#: 702G06
msgctxt "702G06"
msgid "Questions can reveal the hidden way."
msgstr "Questions can reveal the hidden way."

#: 702G07
msgctxt "702G07"
msgid "Questioning, seeking, only by these may we find the hidden way."
msgstr "Questioning, seeking, only by these may we find the hidden way."

#: 702G08
msgctxt "702G08"
msgid "Only he who asks will learn."
msgstr "Only he who asks will learn."

#: 702G09
msgctxt "702G09"
msgid "The right question is worth a thousand wrong ones."
msgstr "The right question is worth a thousand wrong ones."

#: 702G10
msgctxt "702G10"
msgid "We all must help each other in our quests."
msgstr "We all must help each other in our quests."

#: 702G11
msgctxt "702G11"
msgid "Questions are but steps on the path to true enlightenment."
msgstr "Questions are but steps on the path to true enlightenment."

#: 702G12
msgctxt "702G12"
msgid "We believe in the testing of the faithful."
msgstr "We believe in the testing of the faithful."

#: 702G13
msgctxt "702G13"
msgid "We believe only through questioning can we find answers to that which puzzles us."
msgstr "We believe only through questioning can we find answers to that which puzzles us."

#: 702G14
msgctxt "702G14"
msgid "We believe that to learn one must study."
msgstr "We believe that to learn one must study."

#: 702G15
msgctxt "702G15"
msgid "We believe one may not reach true enlightenment until one has found the hidden way."
msgstr "We believe one may not reach true enlightenment until one has found the hidden way."

#: 702G16
msgctxt "702G16"
msgid "We do not believe in trial and error."
msgstr "We do not believe in trial and error."

#: 702G17
msgctxt "702G17"
msgid "We believe in method and reason."
msgstr "We believe in method and reason."

#: 702G18
msgctxt "702G18"
msgid "We believe anyone who proves himself worthy by throwing off the trappings of the outer world may join us."
msgstr "We believe anyone who proves himself worthy by throwing off the trappings of the outer world may join us."

#: 702G19
msgctxt "702G19"
msgid "We welcome questers from all lands."
msgstr "We welcome questers from all lands."

#: 702G20
msgctxt "702G20"
msgid "Only those of the temple may pass."
msgstr "Only those of the temple may pass."

#: 702R01
msgctxt "702R01"
msgid "The Temple of the Hidden Way crowns a mountaintop in a remote corner of the Himalayas."
msgstr "The Temple of the Hidden Way crowns a mountaintop in a remote corner of the Himalayas."

#: 702R01A
msgctxt "702R01A"
msgid "Some Buddhist influence in its construction, yet it's unlike anything I've ever seen."
msgstr "Some Buddhist influence in its construction, yet it's unlike anything I've ever seen."

#: 702R02
msgctxt "702R02"
msgid "While there are similarities to other temples in this part of the world, the temple of the hidden way is unique. The origins of the sect which resides here are lost in the mists of time."
msgstr "While there are similarities to other temples in this part of the world, the temple of the hidden way is unique. The origins of the sect which resides here are lost in the mists of time."

#: 702R03
msgctxt "702R03"
msgid "Those within guard their privacy well."
msgstr "Those within guard their privacy well."

#: 702R04
msgctxt "702R04"
msgid "The only way to reach the temple is through that ornate gateway, but I don't see a welcome map."
msgstr "The only way to reach the temple is through that ornate gateway, but I don't see a welcome map."

#: 702R05
msgctxt "702R05"
msgid "Wherever there is a gate, there is always a guard. This one is a substantial looking fellow with the gleam of a zealot in his eye."
msgstr "Wherever there is a gate, there is always a guard. This one is a substantial looking fellow with the gleam of a zealot in his eye."

#: 702R05A
msgctxt "702R05A"
msgid "Hope he speaks English."
msgstr "Hope he speaks English."

#: 702R05B
msgctxt "702R05B"
msgid "Wherever there is a gate, there is always a guard."
msgstr "Wherever there is a gate, there is always a guard."

#: 702R06
msgctxt "702R06"
msgid "I confess I was testing your vigilance, my friend."
msgstr "I confess I was testing your vigilance, my friend."

#: 702R07
msgctxt "702R07"
msgid "As you see, I am a member of the temple."
msgstr "As you see, I am a member of the temple."

#: 702R08
msgctxt "702R08"
msgid "Here's something that might interest you."
msgstr "Here's something that might interest you."

#: 702R09
msgctxt "702R09"
msgid "Uh... yes, I am."
msgstr "Uh... yes, I am."

#: 702R10
msgctxt "702R10"
msgid "Your vigilance is commendable."
msgstr "Your vigilance is commendable."

#: 702R11
msgctxt "702R11"
msgid "Don't be surprised if I ask further questions."
msgstr "Don't be surprised if I ask further questions."

#: 702R12
msgctxt "702R12"
msgid "Sorry to bother you again."
msgstr "Sorry to bother you again."

#: 702R13
msgctxt "702R13"
msgid "I had a couple more questions."
msgstr "I had a couple more questions."

#: 702R14
msgctxt "702R14"
msgid "I've returned!"
msgstr "I've returned!"

#: 702R15
msgctxt "702R15"
msgid "I came all the way back here because I wanted to ask you some more questions."
msgstr "I came all the way back here because I wanted to ask you some more questions."

#: 702R16
msgctxt "702R16"
msgid "Can you tell me more about the temple?"
msgstr "Can you tell me more about the temple?"

#: 702R17
msgctxt "702R17"
msgid "I'd like to hear what those of the temple believe."
msgstr "I'd like to hear what those of the temple believe."

#: 702R18
msgctxt "702R18"
msgid "If an outsider were interested in the sect, what would you tell him?"
msgstr "If an outsider were interested in the sect, what would you tell him?"

#: 702R19
msgctxt "702R19"
msgid "Can you tell me some key doctrines of the Temple of the Hidden Way?"
msgstr "Can you tell me some key doctrines of the Temple of the Hidden Way?"

#: 702R20
msgctxt "702R20"
msgid "Numerous Westerners are fascinated by Eastern religion. What would you tell them about your beliefs?"
msgstr "Numerous Westerners are fascinated by Eastern religion. What would you tell them about your beliefs?"

#: 702R21
msgctxt "702R21"
msgid "I'm not going to insult the guard by trying to bribe him."
msgstr "I'm not going to insult the guard by trying to bribe him."

#: 702R32
msgctxt "702R32"
msgid "The only access to the temple is through this gateway."
msgstr "The only access to the temple is through this gateway."

#: 703A01
msgctxt "703A01"
msgid "The wise man bends the rope others might cut."
msgstr "The wise man bends the rope others might cut."

#: 703B01
msgctxt "703B01"
msgid "Every creature has its purpose. It is better to catch a snake than to slay it."
msgstr "Every creature has its purpose. It is better to catch a snake than to slay it."

#: 703C01
msgctxt "703C01"
msgid "He who attracts unwanted attention must find that which excites his spectator more."
msgstr "He who attracts unwanted attention must find that which excites his spectator more."

#: 703D01
msgctxt "703D01"
msgid "The path to enlightenment may be traveled through study and prayer."
msgstr "The path to enlightenment may be traveled through study and prayer."

#: 703D02
msgctxt "703D02"
msgid "You are correct. I seek wisdom. Thank you for returning my prayer wheel."
msgstr "You are correct. I seek wisdom. Thank you for returning my prayer wheel."

#: 703R01
msgctxt "703R01"
msgid "The temple of the hidden way was crafted with stone and a hunger for knowledge."
msgstr "The temple of the hidden way was crafted with stone and a hunger for knowledge."

#: 703R02
msgctxt "703R02"
msgid "A prayer wheel."
msgstr "A prayer wheel."

#: 703R03
msgctxt "703R03"
msgid "I'm looking for the path to enlightenment. Can you help me?"
msgstr "I'm looking for the path to enlightenment. Can you help me?"

#: 703R04
msgctxt "703R04"
msgid "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for grace."
msgstr "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for grace."

#: 703R05
msgctxt "703R05"
msgid "The wheel is fixed in place."
msgstr "The wheel is fixed in place."

#: 703R06
msgctxt "703R06"
msgid "I can't budget."
msgstr "I can't budget."

#: 703R07
msgctxt "703R07"
msgid "Guess this isn't one of the five I need to move."
msgstr "Guess this isn't one of the five I need to move."

#: 703R08
msgctxt "703R08"
msgid "There's already a prayer wheel in place."
msgstr "There's already a prayer wheel in place."

#: 703R09
msgctxt "703R09"
msgid "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for stillness."
msgstr "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for stillness."

#: 703R10
msgctxt "703R10"
msgid "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for love."
msgstr "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for love."

#: 703R11
msgctxt "703R11"
msgid "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for serenity."
msgstr "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for serenity."

#: 703R12
msgctxt "703R12"
msgid "There's the prayer wheel of wisdom."
msgstr "There's the prayer wheel of wisdom."

#: 703R13
msgctxt "703R13"
msgid "The guard would never let me take any of the temple's prayer wheels. I'd better put them back."
msgstr "The guard would never let me take any of the temple's prayer wheels. I'd better put them back."

#: 704E01
msgctxt "704E01"
msgid "The slowest of creatures may still walk farther than a man."
msgstr "The slowest of creatures may still walk farther than a man."

#: 704F01
msgctxt "704F01"
msgid "The path to enlightenment may be traveled through study and prayer."
msgstr "The path to enlightenment may be traveled through study and prayer."

#: 704F02
msgctxt "704F02"
msgid "You are correct. I seek serenity. Thank you for returning my prayer wheel."
msgstr "You are correct. I seek serenity. Thank you for returning my prayer wheel."

#: 704H01
msgctxt "704H01"
msgid "There is no reward too great for one who restores a man's honor."
msgstr "There is no reward too great for one who restores a man's honor."

#: 704I01
msgctxt "704I01"
msgid "The hammer may also be the tongs."
msgstr "The hammer may also be the tongs."

#: 704R01
msgctxt "704R01"
msgid "The Temple of the Hidden Way was crafted with stone and a hunger for knowledge."
msgstr "The Temple of the Hidden Way was crafted with stone and a hunger for knowledge."

#: 704R04
