msgid "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for perfection."
msgstr "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for perfection."

#: 705J01
msgctxt "705J01"
msgid "The path to enlightenment may be traveled through study and prayer."
msgstr "The path to enlightenment may be traveled through study and prayer."

#: 705J02
msgctxt "705J02"
msgid "You are correct. I seek peace. Thank you for returning my prayer wheel."
msgstr "You are correct. I seek peace. Thank you for returning my prayer wheel."

#: 705J03
msgctxt "705J03"
msgid "I guard the path to enlightenment, but you have shown yourself possessed of insight beyond your years. You too may now follow the hidden way."
msgstr "I guard the path to enlightenment, but you have shown yourself possessed of insight beyond your years. You too may now follow the hidden way."

#: 705J04
msgctxt "705J04"
msgid "Find the prayer of enlightenment. The way will now be open to you."
msgstr "Find the prayer of enlightenment. The way will now be open to you."

#: 705K01
msgctxt "705K01"
msgid "Salvation may begin with the flame of insight."
msgstr "Salvation may begin with the flame of insight."

#: 705L01
msgctxt "705L01"
msgid "Though the path be in darkness, the way is open to those who seek the light."
msgstr "Though the path be in darkness, the way is open to those who seek the light."

#: 705N01
msgctxt "705N01"
msgid "The path to enlightenment may be traveled through study and prayer."
msgstr "The path to enlightenment may be traveled through study and prayer."

#: 705N02
msgctxt "705N02"
msgid "You are correct. I seek insight. Thank you for returning my prayer wheel."
msgstr "You are correct. I seek insight. Thank you for returning my prayer wheel."

#: 705R04
msgctxt "705R04"
msgid "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for insight."
msgstr "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for insight."

#: 705R06
msgctxt "705R06"
msgid "There's the prayer wheel of peace."
msgstr "There's the prayer wheel of peace."

#: 705R07
msgctxt "705R07"
msgid "You've studied longer than any of the others. Have you found the path to enlightenment?"
msgstr "You've studied longer than any of the others. Have you found the path to enlightenment?"

#: 705R08
msgctxt "705R08"
msgid "But where is the hidden way?"
msgstr "But where is the hidden way?"

#: 705R09
msgctxt "705R09"
msgid "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for compassion."
msgstr "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for compassion."

#: 705R13
msgctxt "705R13"
msgid "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for purity."
msgstr "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for purity."

#: 705R14
msgctxt "705R14"
msgid "According to this, the wheel contains the prayer for truth. I wonder if that is the prayer he seeks."
msgstr "According to this, the wheel contains the prayer for truth. I wonder if that is the prayer he seeks."

#: 705R14A
msgctxt "705R14A"
msgid "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for truth."
msgstr "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for truth."

#: 705R15
msgctxt "705R15"
msgid "There's the prayer wheel of insight."
msgstr "There's the prayer wheel of insight."

#: 706O01
msgctxt "706O01"
msgid "The signs of the earth are sometimes the opposite of what they appear."
msgstr "The signs of the earth are sometimes the opposite of what they appear."

#: 706P01
msgctxt "706P01"
msgid "The path to enlightenment may be traveled through study and prayer."
msgstr "The path to enlightenment may be traveled through study and prayer."

#: 706P02
msgctxt "706P02"
msgid "You are correct. I seek truth. Thank you for returning my prayer wheel."
msgstr "You are correct. I seek truth. Thank you for returning my prayer wheel."

#: 706Q01
msgctxt "706Q01"
msgid "Growing things were never meant to be shaped to man's desire."
msgstr "Growing things were never meant to be shaped to man's desire."

#: 706R04
msgctxt "706R04"
msgid "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for charity."
msgstr "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for charity."

#: 706R09
msgctxt "706R09"
msgid "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for enlightenment."
msgstr "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for enlightenment."

#: 706R10
msgctxt "706R10"
msgid "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for wisdom."
msgstr "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for wisdom."

#: 706R11
msgctxt "706R11"
msgid "There's the prayer wheel of truth."
msgstr "There's the prayer wheel of truth."

#: 706R12
msgctxt "706R12"
msgid "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for discipline."
msgstr "The prayer wheel contains the prayer for discipline."

#: 706R23
msgctxt "706R23"
msgid "Mazes. I hate mazes."
msgstr "Mazes. I hate mazes."

#: 706R24
msgctxt "706R24"
msgid "I feel like I'm the only human being on this mountaintop."
msgstr "I feel like I'm the only human being on this mountaintop."

#: 706R25
msgctxt "706R25"
msgid "To the faithful, the hidden way has been found at last and the sacred texts recovered. We go now to spread the doctrine of the questing mind throughout the land. Join us. Golly!"
msgstr "To the faithful, the hidden way has been found at last and the sacred texts recovered. We go now to spread the doctrine of the questing mind throughout the land. Join us. Golly!"

#: 706R26
msgctxt "706R26"
msgid "I don't need the prayer wheel anymore."
msgstr "I don't need the prayer wheel anymore."

#: 706R27
msgctxt "706R27"
msgid "I'd better leave that here. Others of the faithful may want to read it."
msgstr "I'd better leave that here. Others of the faithful may want to read it."

#: 707R01
msgctxt "707R01"
msgid "The top of the temple is a stone cupola without any apparent entry point from the outside."
msgstr "The top of the temple is a stone cupola without any apparent entry point from the outside."

#: 707R02
msgctxt "707R02"
msgid "I'd lose it if I dropped it down there."
msgstr "I'd lose it if I dropped it down there."

#: 707R03
msgctxt "707R03"
msgid "You see similar wooden statuary all over Asia. These are especially fine."
msgstr "You see similar wooden statuary all over Asia. These are especially fine."

#: 707R04
msgctxt "707R04"
msgid "The grate was designed to let air and light through to the interior of the temple."
msgstr "The grate was designed to let air and light through to the interior of the temple."

#: 707R04A
msgctxt "707R04A"
msgid "The grate was designed to let air and light through to the interior of the temple. An unusual architectural feature to say the least."
msgstr "The grate was designed to let air and light through to the interior of the temple. An unusual architectural feature to say the least."

#: 707R05
msgctxt "707R05"
msgid "An ornate room with no apparent entrance."
msgstr "An ornate room with no apparent entrance."

#: 708R01
msgctxt "708R01"
msgid "I'm not going through there without light. I could wander around down here for eternity."
msgstr "I'm not going through there without light. I could wander around down here for eternity."

#: 708R02
msgctxt "708R02"
msgid "This room has a stale forgotten air about it, as if no feet have walked here for centuries."
msgstr "This room has a stale forgotten air about it, as if no feet have walked here for centuries."

#: 708R10
msgctxt "708R10"
msgid "This dismal room is not worth sketching."
msgstr "This dismal room is not worth sketching."

#: 709R01
msgctxt "709R01"
msgid "An ancient chamber beneath the temple of the hidden way."
msgstr "An ancient chamber beneath the temple of the hidden way."

#: 709R02
msgctxt "709R02"
msgid "That looks like a chisel on the floor. It's probably laying there since this room was built."
msgstr "That looks like a chisel on the floor. It's probably laying there since this room was built."

#: 709R03
msgctxt "709R03"
msgid "The handle of the chisel is an elaborately contrived likeness of a yeti, the abominable snowman of the Himalayas. Fascinating."
msgstr "The handle of the chisel is an elaborately contrived likeness of a yeti, the abominable snowman of the Himalayas. Fascinating."

#: 709R11
msgctxt "709R11"
msgid "This dismal room is not worth sketching."
msgstr "This dismal room is not worth sketching."

#: 709R12
msgctxt "709R12"
msgid "That looks like an incense burner of a very antique design. Who knows how long ago it was forgotten here?"
msgstr "That looks like an incense burner of a very antique design. Who knows how long ago it was forgotten here?"

#: 709R13
msgctxt "709R13"
msgid "Fascinating construction. The incense burner has three bowls. For different herbs, I would imagine. I must get the writing on the bowls translated."
msgstr "Fascinating construction. The incense burner has three bowls. For different herbs, I would imagine. I must get the writing on the bowls translated."

#: 710R01
msgctxt "710R01"
msgid "What on earth is that strange contraption hanging from the ceiling?"
msgstr "What on earth is that strange contraption hanging from the ceiling?"

#: 710R02
msgctxt "710R02"
msgid "That ladder is far too high to reach. The entire thing looks incredibly complicated."
msgstr "That ladder is far too high to reach. The entire thing looks incredibly complicated."

#: 710R03
msgctxt "710R03"
msgid "What does it remind me of? Oh, no! The old baron's laboratory! I don't think I can go through something like that again."
msgstr "What does it remind me of? Oh, no! The old baron's laboratory! I don't think I can go through something like that again."

#: 710R04
msgctxt "710R04"
msgid "The rope is attached to the machinery."
msgstr "The rope is attached to the machinery."

#: 710R05
msgctxt "710R05"
msgid "Secures the rope in place."
msgstr "Secures the rope in place."

#: 710R06
msgctxt "710R06"
msgid "I don't have a clue what that is."
msgstr "I don't have a clue what that is."

#: 710R07
msgctxt "710R07"
msgid "I wish it were always that easy."
msgstr "I wish it were always that easy."

#: 710R08
msgctxt "710R08"
msgid "The rope is attached to the machinery."
msgstr "The rope is attached to the machinery."

#: 710R09
msgctxt "710R09"
msgid "The ladder is attached up above."
msgstr "The ladder is attached up above."

#: 710R10
msgctxt "710R10"
msgid "I can't reach it from here."
msgstr "I can't reach it from here."

#: 710R11
msgctxt "710R11"
msgid "It's firmly bolted in place."
msgstr "It's firmly bolted in place."

#: 710R18
msgctxt "710R18"
msgid "This dismal room is not worth sketching."
msgstr "This dismal room is not worth sketching."

#: 710R20
msgctxt "710R20"
msgid "Can this complicated mechanism really have been constructed just to lower the ladder? And when was it installed? This temple was built centuries ago."
msgstr "Can this complicated mechanism really have been constructed just to lower the ladder? And when was it installed? This temple was built centuries ago."

#: 710R21
msgctxt "710R21"
msgid "The latter was wonderfully simple to get my hands on."
msgstr "The latter was wonderfully simple to get my hands on."

#: 711R01
msgctxt "711R01"
msgid "The interior of the cupola holds books created from palm fronds."
msgstr "The interior of the cupola holds books created from palm fronds."

#: 711R02
msgctxt "711R02"
msgid "Some religious treatise written in ancient Sikkimese, I'd wager."
msgstr "Some religious treatise written in ancient Sikkimese, I'd wager."

#: 711R03
msgctxt "711R03"
msgid "This must be Liu's book. There are Chinese characters lined up next to the Sikkimese glyphs."
msgstr "This must be Liu's book. There are Chinese characters lined up next to the Sikkimese glyphs."

#: 711R04
msgctxt "711R04"
msgid "What a spectacular view!"
msgstr "What a spectacular view!"

#: 711R05
msgctxt "711R05"
msgid "The ladder leads back down to that nasty maze in the bowels of the temple."
msgstr "The ladder leads back down to that nasty maze in the bowels of the temple."

#: 711R06
msgctxt "711R06"
msgid "All I need are the glyphs inscribed on it."
msgstr "All I need are the glyphs inscribed on it."

#: 711R07
msgctxt "711R07"
msgid "The book belongs to the Temple of the Hidden Way and should remain here."
msgstr "The book belongs to the Temple of the Hidden Way and should remain here."

#: 711R08
msgctxt "711R08"
msgid "Ripley, where do you get ideas like that? If you took the ladder, you'd be trapped in here."
msgstr "Ripley, where do you get ideas like that? If you took the ladder, you'd be trapped in here."

#: 711R18
msgctxt "711R18"
msgid "Those icons are solid gold."
msgstr "Those icons are solid gold."

#: 711R19
msgctxt "711R19"
msgid "The icons belong to the temple."
msgstr "The icons belong to the temple."

#: 801F01
msgctxt "801F01"
msgid "(Chinese)"
msgstr "(Chinese)"

#: 801F02
msgctxt "801F02"
msgid "(Chinese)"
msgstr "(Chinese)"

#: 801F02A
msgctxt "801F02A"
msgid "(Chinese)"
msgstr "(Chinese)"

#: 801F03
msgctxt "801F03"
msgid "(Chinese)"
msgstr "(Chinese)"

#: 801F06
msgctxt "801F06"
msgid "(Chinese)"
msgstr "(Chinese)"

#: 801M01
msgctxt "801M01"
msgid "(Chinese)"
msgstr "(Chinese)"

#: 801M02
msgctxt "801M02"
msgid "(Chinese)"
msgstr "(Chinese)"

#: 801M03
msgctxt "801M03"
msgid "There are a lot of men digging on the other side of Mount Lee. He says great trucks rumble past at all hours, shaking the earth."
msgstr "There are a lot of men digging on the other side of Mount Lee. He says great trucks rumble past at all hours, shaking the earth."

#: 801M04
msgctxt "801M04"
msgid "They disturb the harmony of his rice. Robert, are we too late?"
msgstr "They disturb the harmony of his rice. Robert, are we too late?"

#: 801M05
msgctxt "801M05"
msgid "Getting past Quang's men won't be easy."
msgstr "Getting past Quang's men won't be easy."

#: 801M06
msgctxt "801M06"
msgid "He says our land is in pain from the invaders and now these grave robbers, as he calls them."
msgstr "He says our land is in pain from the invaders and now these grave robbers, as he calls them."

#: 801M10
msgctxt "801M10"
msgid "Where did they come from?"
msgstr "Where did they come from?"

#: 801M11
msgctxt "801M11"
msgid "But how can they be here?"
msgstr "But how can they be here?"

#: 801M12
msgctxt "801M12"
msgid "(Chinese)"
msgstr "(Chinese)"

#: 801M13
msgctxt "801M13"
msgid "He says it's a very good shovel."
msgstr "He says it's a very good shovel."

#: 801R01
msgctxt "801R01"
msgid "It's a Japanese zero!"
msgstr "It's a Japanese zero!"

#: 801R02
msgctxt "801R02"
msgid "What is he saying, May?"
msgstr "What is he saying, May?"

#: 801R03
msgctxt "801R03"
msgid "They may have dug down to the tomb, but if they'd found a way in, Quang would not have stolen my notes."
msgstr "They may have dug down to the tomb, but if they'd found a way in, Quang would not have stolen my notes."

#: 801R04
msgctxt "801R04"
msgid "No!"
msgstr "No!"

#: 801R05
msgctxt "801R05"
msgid "It's what they are, right enough. And we have to find a way to stop them."
msgstr "It's what they are, right enough. And we have to find a way to stop them."

#: 801R06
msgctxt "801R06"
msgid "I wish I had something specific to ask that fellow."
msgstr "I wish I had something specific to ask that fellow."

#: 801R09
msgctxt "801R09"
msgid "This match won't last long as it is. No point lighting it out here in broad daylight."
msgstr "This match won't last long as it is. No point lighting it out here in broad daylight."

#: 801R10
msgctxt "801R10"
msgid "As if this fellow didn't have a hard enough life. Now the threat of war hangs over his head."
msgstr "As if this fellow didn't have a hard enough life. Now the threat of war hangs over his head."

#: 801R11
msgctxt "801R11"
msgid "Not many rice patties, but lovingly tended."
msgstr "Not many rice patties, but lovingly tended."

#: 801R12
msgctxt "801R12"
msgid "A small but sturdily built farmhouse."
msgstr "A small but sturdily built farmhouse."

#: 801R13
msgctxt "801R13"
msgid "Mount Li, an artificial mountain, and underneath in the first emperor's tomb, the emerald seal. The key to China, perhaps all of Asia."
msgstr "Mount Li, an artificial mountain, and underneath in the first emperor's tomb, the emerald seal. The key to China, perhaps all of Asia."

#: 801R13A
msgctxt "801R13A"
msgid "Mount Li, an artificial mountain covering the first emperor's tomb."
msgstr "Mount Li, an artificial mountain covering the first emperor's tomb."

#: 801R14
msgctxt "801R14"
msgid "The farm's root cellar."
msgstr "The farm's root cellar."

#: 801R15
msgctxt "801R15"
msgid "If I knew where to dig, that shovel might come in handy."
msgstr "If I knew where to dig, that shovel might come in handy."

#: 801R15A
msgctxt "801R15A"
msgid "That shovel might come in handy."
msgstr "That shovel might come in handy."

#: 801R16
msgctxt "801R16"
msgid "A lovingly tended vegetable garden."
msgstr "A lovingly tended vegetable garden."

#: 801R17
msgctxt "801R17"
msgid "A low fence, fashioned from scraps of wood, surrounds the vegetable garden."
msgstr "A low fence, fashioned from scraps of wood, surrounds the vegetable garden."

#: 801R18
msgctxt "801R18"
msgid "Earthen jugs, probably made by the farmer's own hands."
msgstr "Earthen jugs, probably made by the farmer's own hands."

#: 801R19
msgctxt "801R19"
msgid "What's this? Broken China? There's something horribly symbolic in that. No! Wait!"
msgstr "What's this? Broken China? There's something horribly symbolic in that. No! Wait!"

#: 801R20
msgctxt "801R20"
msgid "May, these are bits of terracotta sculptures. Here's part of a hand."
msgstr "May, these are bits of terracotta sculptures. Here's part of a hand."

#: 801R21
msgctxt "801R21"
msgid "The old baron's letter mentioned row upon row of Terracotta soldiers, guarding the first emperor's treasures."
msgstr "The old baron's letter mentioned row upon row of Terracotta soldiers, guarding the first emperor's treasures."

#: 801R22
msgctxt "801R22"
msgid "Bits of terracotta soldiers."
msgstr "Bits of terracotta soldiers."

#: 801R23
msgctxt "801R23"
msgid "A farm in the shadow of Mount Lee."
msgstr "A farm in the shadow of Mount Lee."

#: 801R25
msgctxt "801R25"
msgid "Broken pieces of pottery won't be of much use."
msgstr "Broken pieces of pottery won't be of much use."

#: 801R25A
msgctxt "801R25A"
msgid "But it might be helpful to learn their origin."
msgstr "But it might be helpful to learn their origin."

#: 801R26
msgctxt "801R26"
msgid "I can't simply take this man's shovel. It's his primary tool for scratching out a living on this farm."
msgstr "I can't simply take this man's shovel. It's his primary tool for scratching out a living on this farm."

#: 801R27
msgctxt "801R27"
msgid "I don't have time to discover this fellow will only part with that shovel if I present him with a rare vegetable from Tibet or something. May, tell the fellow I'd like to buy a shovel. Then he can buy a new one."
msgstr "I don't have time to discover this fellow will only part with that shovel if I present him with a rare vegetable from Tibet or something. May, tell the fellow I'd like to buy a shovel. Then he can buy a new one."

#: 801R28
msgctxt "801R28"
msgid "There you are, my good man. With that, you can buy a new farm."
msgstr "There you are, my good man. With that, you can buy a new farm."

#: 801R29
msgctxt "801R29"
msgid "I can't see much from up here."
msgstr "I can't see much from up here."

#: 801R30
msgctxt "801R30"
msgid "May, come look at this!"
msgstr "May, come look at this!"

#: 801R31
msgctxt "801R31"
msgid "What's the matter with the fellow? He's never seen American dollars before."
msgstr "What's the matter with the fellow? He's never seen American dollars before."

#: 801R32
msgctxt "801R32"
msgid "He's never seen American dollars before."
msgstr "He's never seen American dollars before."

#: 801R42
msgctxt "801R42"
msgid "Oh, I lost my pencil at the Hall of Classics. I forgot to get a new one."
msgstr "Oh, I lost my pencil at the Hall of Classics. I forgot to get a new one."

#: 801R43B
msgctxt "801R43B"
msgid "Placeholder. He's never seen American dollars before. And even if he had, how could he possibly tell the denominations without them being different colors?"
msgstr "Placeholder. He's never seen American dollars before. And even if he had, how could he possibly tell the denominations without them being different colors?"

#: 801R43C
msgctxt "801R43C"
msgid "Placeholder, what's the matter with the fellow? He's never seen American dollars before."
msgstr "Placeholder, what's the matter with the fellow? He's never seen American dollars before."

#: 801R44
msgctxt "801R44"
msgid "Oh, a single match. Well, it'll have to do."
msgstr "Oh, a single match. Well, it'll have to do."

#: 802R01
msgctxt "802R01"
msgid "A sack of rice. Undoubtedly homegrown."
msgstr "A sack of rice. Undoubtedly homegrown."

#: 802R02
msgctxt "802R02"
msgid "Hmm... that must be where the farmer unearthed those pieces of terracotta. There's a fragment still embedded in the wall."
msgstr "Hmm... that must be where the farmer unearthed those pieces of terracotta. There's a fragment still embedded in the wall."

#: 802R03
msgctxt "802R03"
msgid "There's a fragment of terracotta embedded in the wall."
msgstr "There's a fragment of terracotta embedded in the wall."

#: 802R04
msgctxt "802R04"
msgid "Better move the rice sack. Wouldn't do to damage the farmer's meager supply."
msgstr "Better move the rice sack. Wouldn't do to damage the farmer's meager supply."

#: 802R05
msgctxt "802R05"
msgid "Great, Scott. A hand fashioned from terracotta. I wonder if it's part of a statue that was damaged when they built the tomb and discarded it. No. Twelve feet underground?"
msgstr "Great, Scott. A hand fashioned from terracotta. I wonder if it's part of a statue that was damaged when they built the tomb and discarded it. No. Twelve feet underground?"

#: 802R06
msgctxt "802R06"
msgid "It's no use. I'll need something to dig it out."
msgstr "It's no use. I'll need something to dig it out."

#: 802R07
msgctxt "802R07"
msgid "I'll need the shovel to dig it up."
msgstr "I'll need the shovel to dig it up."

#: 802R08
msgctxt "802R08"
msgid "It's still stuck in the wall pretty good. I'd better dig some more."
msgstr "It's still stuck in the wall pretty good. I'd better dig some more."

#: 802R09
msgctxt "802R09"
msgid "It's black as sin in there."
msgstr "It's black as sin in there."

#: 802R10
msgctxt "802R10"
msgid "The farmer stores his produce down here in the cool of the cellar."
msgstr "The farmer stores his produce down here in the cool of the cellar."

#: 802R11
msgctxt "802R11"
msgid "That urn looks like a huge bottle of ketchup."
msgstr "That urn looks like a huge bottle of ketchup."

#: 802R12
msgctxt "802R12"
msgid "A heap of potatoes."
msgstr "A heap of potatoes."

#: 802R13
msgctxt "802R13"
msgid "The Farmer's Root Seller."
msgstr "The Farmer's Root Seller."

#: 802R14
msgctxt "802R14"
msgid "I'd better leave the Poor Farmer's Produce where it is."
msgstr "I'd better leave the Poor Farmer's Produce where it is."

#: 802R15
msgctxt "802R15"
msgid "There appears to be an entire Terracotta soldier embedded in this wall."
msgstr "There appears to be an entire Terracotta soldier embedded in this wall."

#: 802R16
msgctxt "802R16"
msgid "The dirt wall was very thin here between the root cellar and some sort of large cave."
msgstr "The dirt wall was very thin here between the root cellar and some sort of large cave."

#: 803M01
msgctxt "803M01"
msgid "What happened?"
msgstr "What happened?"

#: 803M02
msgctxt "803M02"
msgid "Well done!"
msgstr "Well done!"

#: 803M03
msgctxt "803M03"
msgid "Robert! Is this..."
msgstr "Robert! Is this..."

#: 803R01
msgctxt "803R01"
msgid "Oh, uh... I saw an urn filled with oil, deduced at once that it was a primitive lamp, and simply set alight."
msgstr "Oh, uh... I saw an urn filled with oil, deduced at once that it was a primitive lamp, and simply set alight."

#: 803R02
msgctxt "803R02"
msgid "Yeah, elementary."
msgstr "Yeah, elementary."

#: 803R03
msgctxt "803R03"
msgid "Yes, it must be. We've broken through into the tomb itself."
msgstr "Yes, it must be. We've broken through into the tomb itself."

#: 803R04
msgctxt "803R04"
msgid "At some point an earth tremor must have collapsed a portion of the wall."
msgstr "At some point an earth tremor must have collapsed a portion of the wall."

#: 803R05
msgctxt "803R05"
msgid "The paint on the mural is faded, but it's still breathtaking."
msgstr "The paint on the mural is faded, but it's still breathtaking."

#: 803R06
msgctxt "803R06"
msgid "One of the Terracotta soldiers has toppled."
msgstr "One of the Terracotta soldiers has toppled."

#: 803R07
msgctxt "803R07"
msgid "The statue must have been on the outside of the wall. Whatever damaged the wall also smashed it. Then it fell through when I dislodged it."
msgstr "The statue must have been on the outside of the wall. Whatever damaged the wall also smashed it. Then it fell through when I dislodged it."

#: 803R08
msgctxt "803R08"
msgid "Amazing, the oil still burns after all these centuries."
msgstr "Amazing, the oil still burns after all these centuries."

#: 803R10
msgctxt "803R10"
msgid "One of the urns has fallen on its side."
msgstr "One of the urns has fallen on its side."

#: 803R11
msgctxt "803R11"
msgid "This room is so vast and empty. I wonder what its purpose was."
msgstr "This room is so vast and empty. I wonder what its purpose was."

#: 803R13
msgctxt "803R13"
msgid "The statue is in pieces and not of much use."
msgstr "The statue is in pieces and not of much use."

#: 803R14
msgctxt "803R14"
msgid "There's nothing in this chamber even remotely small enough to take."
msgstr "There's nothing in this chamber even remotely small enough to take."

#: 803R19
msgctxt "803R19"
msgid "We haven't come all this way to turn back now."
msgstr "We haven't come all this way to turn back now."

#: 804R06
msgctxt "804R06"
msgid "The first in a row of seven soldiers wearing green skirts."
msgstr "The first in a row of seven soldiers wearing green skirts."

#: 804R07
msgctxt "804R07"
msgid "The second in a row of seven soldiers wearing green skirts."
msgstr "The second in a row of seven soldiers wearing green skirts."

#: 804R08
msgctxt "804R08"
msgid "The third in a row of seven soldiers wearing green skirts."
msgstr "The third in a row of seven soldiers wearing green skirts."

#: 804R09
msgctxt "804R09"
msgid "The fourth in a row of seven soldiers wearing green skirts."
msgstr "The fourth in a row of seven soldiers wearing green skirts."

#: 804R10
msgctxt "804R10"
msgid "The fifth in a row of seven soldiers wearing green skirts."
msgstr "The fifth in a row of seven soldiers wearing green skirts."

#: 804R11
msgctxt "804R11"
msgid "The sixth in a row of seven soldiers wearing green skirts."
msgstr "The sixth in a row of seven soldiers wearing green skirts."

#: 804R12
msgctxt "804R12"
msgid "The seventh in a row of seven soldiers wearing green skirts."
msgstr "The seventh in a row of seven soldiers wearing green skirts."

#: 804R15
msgctxt "804R15"
msgid "The weight of Mount Li has taken a toll on the ceiling of this corridor."
msgstr "The weight of Mount Li has taken a toll on the ceiling of this corridor."

#: 804R20
msgctxt "804R20"
msgid "It's too heavy to lift, but I might be able to push it."
msgstr "It's too heavy to lift, but I might be able to push it."

#: 804R25
msgctxt "804R25"
msgid "The chariot won't budge an inch."
msgstr "The chariot won't budge an inch."

#: 805M01
msgctxt "805M01"
msgid "Then Quang made it this far."
msgstr "Then Quang made it this far."

#: 805R01
msgctxt "805R01"
msgid "A massive door is set in the eastern wall of this room."
msgstr "A massive door is set in the eastern wall of this room."

#: 805R02
msgctxt "805R02"
msgid "The door looks to be solid jade."
msgstr "The door looks to be solid jade."

#: 805R03
msgctxt "805R03"
msgid "That hole looks newer than the one we entered through."
msgstr "That hole looks newer than the one we entered through."

#: 805R04
msgctxt "805R04"
msgid "Yes, this earth is freshly turned, and there's a footprint as well."
msgstr "Yes, this earth is freshly turned, and there's a footprint as well."

#: 805R05
msgctxt "805R05"
msgid "Maybe..."
msgstr "Maybe..."

#: 805R05A
msgctxt "805R05A"
msgid "But if so, where is he now?"
msgstr "But if so, where is he now?"

#: 805R06
msgctxt "805R06"
msgid "I suspect that hole is how Quang planned to enter the tomb. I wonder if he is here now."
msgstr "I suspect that hole is how Quang planned to enter the tomb. I wonder if he is here now."

#: 805R06A
msgctxt "805R06A"
msgid "Obviously the hole through which Quang entered the tomb."
msgstr "Obviously the hole through which Quang entered the tomb."

#: 805R07
msgctxt "805R07"
msgid "A beam of wood about three feet long is broken away from the ceiling."
msgstr "A beam of wood about three feet long is broken away from the ceiling."

#: 805R10
msgctxt "805R10"
msgid "The Terracotta soldiers are holding intricately crafted shields."
msgstr "The Terracotta soldiers are holding intricately crafted shields."

#: 805R10A
msgctxt "805R10A"
msgid "The Terracotta soldiers are holding an intricately crafted shield."
msgstr "The Terracotta soldiers are holding an intricately crafted shield."

#: 805R11
msgctxt "805R11"
msgid "The shield is sheathed in copper and has a wooden backing."
msgstr "The shield is sheathed in copper and has a wooden backing."

#: 805R12
msgctxt "805R12"
msgid "The paint on the mural has faded, but it's still breathtaking."
msgstr "The paint on the mural has faded, but it's still breathtaking."

#: 805R13
msgctxt "805R13"
msgid "The chariot is functioning remarkably well, considering its age."
msgstr "The chariot is functioning remarkably well, considering its age."

#: 805R15
msgctxt "805R15"
msgid "The soldier is far too big to take."
msgstr "The soldier is far too big to take."

#: 805R18
msgctxt "805R18"
msgid "Numbers, colors, push and pull... I have the feeling Master Lu has given me the key to open that door. If only I could figure it out."
msgstr "Numbers, colors, push and pull... I have the feeling Master Lu has given me the key to open that door. If only I could figure it out."

#: 805R19
msgctxt "805R19"
msgid "I haven't interpreted Master Lu's instructions correctly."
msgstr "I haven't interpreted Master Lu's instructions correctly."

#: 805R20
msgctxt "805R20"
msgid "Ripley, it can't go any further. And after pushing it in here, you certainly don't want to push it back again."
msgstr "Ripley, it can't go any further. And after pushing it in here, you certainly don't want to push it back again."

#: 805R23
msgctxt "805R23"
msgid "The shield may come in handy, but I don't see a way to use it here."
msgstr "The shield may come in handy, but I don't see a way to use it here."

#: 805R24
msgctxt "805R24"
msgid "The wooden beam might be useful, but I don't see a use for it here."
msgstr "The wooden beam might be useful, but I don't see a use for it here."

#: 805R25
msgctxt "805R25"
msgid "There's no place to wedge the beam to pry open the door."
msgstr "There's no place to wedge the beam to pry open the door."

#: 805R34
msgctxt "805R34"
msgid "I have to figure a way to get that door open."
msgstr "I have to figure a way to get that door open."

#: 805R36
msgctxt "805R36"
msgid "It's too heavy to lift."
msgstr "It's too heavy to lift."

#: 806M01
msgctxt "806M01"
msgid "It's quiet. What happened to him?"
msgstr "It's quiet. What happened to him?"

#: 806M02
msgctxt "806M02"
msgid "But who killed him?"
msgstr "But who killed him?"

#: 806M03
msgctxt "806M03"
msgid "But how?"
msgstr "But how?"

#: 806M08
msgctxt "806M08"
msgid "Robert!"
msgstr "Robert!"

#: 806R01
msgctxt "806R01"
msgid "Looks like Quang found out first-hand that a little knowledge can be a dangerous thing."
msgstr "Looks like Quang found out first-hand that a little knowledge can be a dangerous thing."

#: 806R02
msgctxt "806R02"
msgid "I suspect Master Lu."
msgstr "I suspect Master Lu."

#: 806R03
msgctxt "806R03"
msgid "Until we discover that, we'd best proceed with caution."
msgstr "Until we discover that, we'd best proceed with caution."

#: 806R04
msgctxt "806R04"
msgid "This corridor appears to serve no particular purpose, but Quang's body suggests that appearances can be deceiving."
msgstr "This corridor appears to serve no particular purpose, but Quang's body suggests that appearances can be deceiving."

#: 806R05
msgctxt "806R05"
msgid "The same decorative pattern lines both walls of this corridor."
msgstr "The same decorative pattern lines both walls of this corridor."

#: 806R06
msgctxt "806R06"
msgid "I feel air moving against my hand. The dark spots are not part of the pattern at all. They're cleverly contrived openings."
msgstr "I feel air moving against my hand. The dark spots are not part of the pattern at all. They're cleverly contrived openings."

#: 806R07
msgctxt "806R07"
msgid "Kwan wasn't shot from behind, or farther along the corridor. He was shot from the side. No, both sides."
msgstr "Kwan wasn't shot from behind, or farther along the corridor. He was shot from the side. No, both sides."

#: 806R08
msgctxt "806R08"
msgid "Notice the stone slabs, May? Quang lies on the first. I suspect each slab triggers a mechanism of some sort."
msgstr "Notice the stone slabs, May? Quang lies on the first. I suspect each slab triggers a mechanism of some sort."

#: 806R08A
msgctxt "806R08A"
msgid "Each slab triggers a mechanism of some sort."
msgstr "Each slab triggers a mechanism of some sort."

#: 806R09
msgctxt "806R09"
msgid "That can only be the second century B.C. Chinese equivalent of a doorknob. It must be how Quang closed the jade door after him."
msgstr "That can only be the second century B.C. Chinese equivalent of a doorknob. It must be how Quang closed the jade door after him."

#: 806R10
msgctxt "806R10"
msgid "He came to a nasty and pointed end."
msgstr "He came to a nasty and pointed end."

#: 806R11
msgctxt "806R11"
msgid "The chariot is functioning remarkably well, considering its age."
msgstr "The chariot is functioning remarkably well, considering its age."

#: 806R14
msgctxt "806R14"
msgid "May's holding up wonderfully. She's quite a gal."
msgstr "May's holding up wonderfully. She's quite a gal."

#: 806R15
msgctxt "806R15"
msgid "It's lodged too deeply in the wall to be removed."
msgstr "It's lodged too deeply in the wall to be removed."

#: 806R16
msgctxt "806R16"
msgid "With the barbs on the head of that bolt, it would be a long and unpleasant task removing it from Quang's body."
msgstr "With the barbs on the head of that bolt, it would be a long and unpleasant task removing it from Quang's body."

#: 806R17
msgctxt "806R17"
msgid "However, Quang got the Jade door closed, it's jammed now."
msgstr "However, Quang got the Jade door closed, it's jammed now."

#: 806R18
msgctxt "806R18"
msgid "The crank doesn't fit in the hole."
msgstr "The crank doesn't fit in the hole."

#: 806R19
msgctxt "806R19"
msgid "Those bolt holes run from the floor to above my head. The shields wouldn't protect my entire body."
msgstr "Those bolt holes run from the floor to above my head. The shields wouldn't protect my entire body."

#: 806R20
msgctxt "806R20"
msgid "Better move to one side, May. I have an idea."
msgstr "Better move to one side, May. I have an idea."

#: 806R21
msgctxt "806R21"
msgid "May has little use for the crank right now."
msgstr "May has little use for the crank right now."

#: 806R23
msgctxt "806R23"
msgid "It's too heavy to lift."
msgstr "It's too heavy to lift."

#: 806R24
msgctxt "806R24"
msgid "Like a slot for a crank."
msgstr "Like a slot for a crank."

#: 806R25
msgctxt "806R25"
msgid "I saw Quang's flashlight flicker and die when we entered. It's of no use now."
msgstr "I saw Quang's flashlight flicker and die when we entered. It's of no use now."

#: 806R25A
msgctxt "806R25A"
msgid "Quang's flashlight is dead."
msgstr "Quang's flashlight is dead."

#: 806R26
msgctxt "806R26"
msgid "Now that it's broken, the flashlight is useless."
msgstr "Now that it's broken, the flashlight is useless."

#: 806R27
msgctxt "806R27"
msgid "Quang's hat has been skewered to the corridor wall."
msgstr "Quang's hat has been skewered to the corridor wall."

#: 806R28
msgctxt "806R28"
msgid "Quang's punctured hat won't be of much use to anyone anymore."
msgstr "Quang's punctured hat won't be of much use to anyone anymore."

#: 807M01
msgctxt "807M01"
msgid "What happened?"
msgstr "What happened?"

#: 807M02
msgctxt "807M02"
msgid "Robert, that door must weigh several tons."
msgstr "Robert, that door must weigh several tons."

#: 807M10
msgctxt "807M10"
msgid "Robert, are you sure it's safe?"
msgstr "Robert, are you sure it's safe?"

#: 807R01
msgctxt "807R01"
msgid "Another of Master Lu's little jokes for the unwary."
msgstr "Another of Master Lu's little jokes for the unwary."

#: 807R02
msgctxt "807R02"
msgid "The corridor ends in yet another trap. A low passage with a deadly stone block for its roof."
msgstr "The corridor ends in yet another trap. A low passage with a deadly stone block for its roof."

#: 807R03
msgctxt "807R03"
msgid "A precisely painted dragon motif surrounds the doorway."
msgstr "A precisely painted dragon motif surrounds the doorway."

#: 807R04
msgctxt "807R04"
msgid "It's identical to the slot by the door at the other end of the corridor."
msgstr "It's identical to the slot by the door at the other end of the corridor."

#: 807R05
msgctxt "807R05"
msgid "That slot is different from the holes which held the crossbow bolts."
msgstr "That slot is different from the holes which held the crossbow bolts."

#: 807R06
msgctxt "807R06"
msgid "A centuries old artifact reduced to matchsticks."
msgstr "A centuries old artifact reduced to matchsticks."

#: 807R09
msgctxt "807R09"
msgid "Traversing that passage could be a depressing experience."
msgstr "Traversing that passage could be a depressing experience."

#: 807R10
msgctxt "807R10"
msgid "The wooden post will prevent the crank from turning and the stone block falling."
msgstr "The wooden post will prevent the crank from turning and the stone block falling."

#: 807R11
msgctxt "807R11"
msgid "The wooden beam has canted the stone block enough so that it will no longer fall."
msgstr "The wooden beam has canted the stone block enough so that it will no longer fall."

#: 807R12
msgctxt "807R12"
msgid "The crank raises the stone block in the passage."
msgstr "The crank raises the stone block in the passage."

#: 807R13
msgctxt "807R13"
msgid "May's holding up wonderfully. She's quite a gal."
msgstr "May's holding up wonderfully. She's quite a gal."

#: 807R14
msgctxt "807R14"
msgid "Uh, just checking for hidden switches."
msgstr "Uh, just checking for hidden switches."

#: 807R22
msgctxt "807R22"
msgid "That beam looks sturdy enough to hold the door, but we'll have to open the door first."
msgstr "That beam looks sturdy enough to hold the door, but we'll have to open the door first."

#: 807R23
msgctxt "807R23"
msgid "The post is wedged in there pretty good. I'll have to move it before I can take the crank."
msgstr "The post is wedged in there pretty good. I'll have to move it before I can take the crank."

#: 807R23A
msgctxt "807R23A"
msgid "The post is wedged in there pretty good."
msgstr "The post is wedged in there pretty good."

#: 807R24
msgctxt "807R24"
msgid "May has little use for the crank right now."
msgstr "May has little use for the crank right now."

#: 807R25
msgctxt "807R25"
msgid "If Master Lu has an unlimited supply of crossbow bolts, we might as well just pack it in right now."
msgstr "If Master Lu has an unlimited supply of crossbow bolts, we might as well just pack it in right now."

#: 807R26
msgctxt "807R26"
msgid "The long beam is irretrievably wedged under the stone slab."
msgstr "The long beam is irretrievably wedged under the stone slab."

#: 807R27
msgctxt "807R27"
msgid "The broken chariot is useless."
msgstr "The broken chariot is useless."

#: 808M01
msgctxt "808M01"
msgid "Robert, you removed the shovel!"
msgstr "Robert, you removed the shovel!"

#: 808M10
msgctxt "808M10"
msgid "And the Emerald Seal?"
msgstr "And the Emerald Seal?"

#: 808R01
msgctxt "808R01"
msgid "A cavernous chamber that drops to a deep abyss shrouded in darkness."
msgstr "A cavernous chamber that drops to a deep abyss shrouded in darkness."

#: 808R02
msgctxt "808R02"
msgid "Unusual bridge. It appears to be attached to that circular section of wall, and unsupported below."
msgstr "Unusual bridge. It appears to be attached to that circular section of wall, and unsupported below."

#: 808R03
msgctxt "808R03"
msgid "That section of wall looks exactly like a giant wheel."
msgstr "That section of wall looks exactly like a giant wheel."

#: 808R04
msgctxt "808R04"
msgid "That chain must control some sort of mechanical device."
msgstr "That chain must control some sort of mechanical device."

#: 808R05
msgctxt "808R05"
msgid "That looks like a slot for a crank."
msgstr "That looks like a slot for a crank."

#: 808R06
msgctxt "808R06"
msgid "The crank is in the slot."
msgstr "The crank is in the slot."

#: 808R07
msgctxt "808R07"
msgid "The system that supplies oil to those urns would be impressive even today."
msgstr "The system that supplies oil to those urns would be impressive even today."

#: 808R09
msgctxt "808R09"
msgid "The Terracotta Soldier has stood watch for countless centuries."
msgstr "The Terracotta Soldier has stood watch for countless centuries."

#: 808R10
msgctxt "808R10"
msgid "One of the Terracotta soldiers has toppled into the abyss."
msgstr "One of the Terracotta soldiers has toppled into the abyss."

#: 808R11
msgctxt "808R11"
msgid "That hole reminds me of a flood control duct. But why so high from the floor of this chamber?"
msgstr "That hole reminds me of a flood control duct. But why so high from the floor of this chamber?"

#: 808R12
msgctxt "808R12"
msgid "A passageway continues into the distance. The immensity of the tomb is staggering."
msgstr "A passageway continues into the distance. The immensity of the tomb is staggering."

#: 808R13
msgctxt "808R13"
msgid "I can just see another staircase down there, and what looks like a door. I can't make out any way down to them."
msgstr "I can just see another staircase down there, and what looks like a door. I can't make out any way down to them."

#: 808R14
msgctxt "808R14"
msgid "Caverns measureless to man."
msgstr "Caverns measureless to man."

#: 808R15
msgctxt "808R15"
msgid "There's a hole drilled into this end of the bridge."
msgstr "There's a hole drilled into this end of the bridge."

#: 808R15A
msgctxt "808R15A"
msgid "It looks as if it were designed to line up with the hole in the chasm wall."
msgstr "It looks as if it were designed to line up with the hole in the chasm wall."

#: 808R16
msgctxt "808R16"
msgid "The two holes are the same size."
msgstr "The two holes are the same size."

#: 808R17
msgctxt "808R17"
msgid "There's a hole in the wall in the far side of the chasm."
msgstr "There's a hole in the wall in the far side of the chasm."

#: 808R17A
msgctxt "808R17A"
msgid "It looks as if it were designed to line up with the hole in the bridge."
msgstr "It looks as if it were designed to line up with the hole in the bridge."

#: 808R18
msgctxt "808R18"
msgid "May's holding up wonderfully. She's quite a gal."
msgstr "May's holding up wonderfully. She's quite a gal."

#: 808R19
msgctxt "808R19"
msgid "Must be the first emperor's doorbell."
msgstr "Must be the first emperor's doorbell."

#: 808R23
msgctxt "808R23"
msgid "I don't know what to say."
msgstr "I don't know what to say."

#: 808R26
msgctxt "808R26"
msgid "May, put the crank in the slot and turn it."
msgstr "May, put the crank in the slot and turn it."

#: 808R27
msgctxt "808R27"
msgid "Turn the crank again."
msgstr "Turn the crank again."

#: 808R28
msgctxt "808R28"
msgid "When you tried to turn the crank, it sounded as if something bumped against your end of the bridge."
msgstr "When you tried to turn the crank, it sounded as if something bumped against your end of the bridge."

#: 808R29
msgctxt "808R29"
msgid "The bolt banged against your end of the bridge."
msgstr "The bolt banged against your end of the bridge."

#: 808R30
msgctxt "808R30"
msgid "Sorry, May. I'm not thinking. You can't cross yet."
msgstr "Sorry, May. I'm not thinking. You can't cross yet."

#: 808R31
msgctxt "808R31"
msgid "I can't take the shovel while the bridge is in that position."
msgstr "I can't take the shovel while the bridge is in that position."

#: 808R32
msgctxt "808R32"
msgid "The mechanism is jammed."
msgstr "The mechanism is jammed."

#: 808R33
msgctxt "808R33"
msgid "The shovel fits nicely in the hole."
msgstr "The shovel fits nicely in the hole."

#: 808R34
msgctxt "808R34"
msgid "Now what?"
msgstr "Now what?"

#: 808R35
msgctxt "808R35"
msgid "The post is much too large for the whole."
msgstr "The post is much too large for the whole."

#: 808R41
msgctxt "808R41"
msgid "A horrible way to go, even for someone like him."
msgstr "A horrible way to go, even for someone like him."

#: 808R42
msgctxt "808R42"
msgid "The first emperor has reclaimed it, thanks to Master Lu."
msgstr "The first emperor has reclaimed it, thanks to Master Lu."

#: 809M01
msgctxt "809M01"
msgid "Robert, it's magnificent. It's as if all of China were laid out before us."
msgstr "Robert, it's magnificent. It's as if all of China were laid out before us."

#: 809M02
msgctxt "809M02"
msgid "Robert, where are you going?"
msgstr "Robert, where are you going?"

#: 809M03
msgctxt "809M03"
msgid "You can't swim across the lake, can you?"
msgstr "You can't swim across the lake, can you?"

#: 809M04
msgctxt "809M04"
msgid "You don't know how deep the lake is, do you?"
msgstr "You don't know how deep the lake is, do you?"

#: 809M05
msgctxt "809M05"
msgid "What on earth are you doing?"
msgstr "What on earth are you doing?"

#: 809R01
msgctxt "809R01"
msgid "The old baron was right. This tomb deserves to be the eighth wonder of the world."
msgstr "The old baron was right. This tomb deserves to be the eighth wonder of the world."

#: 809R01A
msgctxt "809R01A"
msgid "This tomb deserves to be the eighth wonder of the world."
msgstr "This tomb deserves to be the eighth wonder of the world."

#: 809R02
msgctxt "809R02"
msgid "Ancient China, lovingly recreated in miniature."
msgstr "Ancient China, lovingly recreated in miniature."

#: 809R03
msgctxt "809R03"
msgid "That lake is mercury. Thousands upon thousands of gallons of pure mercury."
msgstr "That lake is mercury. Thousands upon thousands of gallons of pure mercury."

#: 809R04
msgctxt "809R04"
msgid "Qin She Huangdi's mausoleum. Even in death he was an emperor of all he surveyed."
msgstr "Qin She Huangdi's mausoleum. Even in death he was an emperor of all he surveyed."

#: 809R05
msgctxt "809R05"
msgid "The river is mercury."
msgstr "The river is mercury."

#: 809R06
msgctxt "809R06"
msgid "Each building has been carefully built to scale."
msgstr "Each building has been carefully built to scale."

#: 809R07
msgctxt "809R07"
msgid "A dragon's head carved from marble."
msgstr "A dragon's head carved from marble."

#: 809R07A
msgctxt "809R07A"
msgid "I wonder what function it serves."
msgstr "I wonder what function it serves."

#: 809R08
msgctxt "809R08"
msgid "Terracotta soldiers, but far more immense than any we've encountered so far."
msgstr "Terracotta soldiers, but far more immense than any we've encountered so far."

#: 809R09
msgctxt "809R09"
msgid "That gate dwarfs those in the Forbidden City itself."
msgstr "That gate dwarfs those in the Forbidden City itself."

#: 809R10
msgctxt "809R10"
msgid "A small dam keeps the mercury from entering that channel."
msgstr "A small dam keeps the mercury from entering that channel."

#: 809R11
msgctxt "809R11"
msgid "May's holding up wonderfully. She's quite a gal."
msgstr "May's holding up wonderfully. She's quite a gal."

#: 809R12
msgctxt "809R12"
msgid "No, I don't know what I was thinking."
msgstr "No, I don't know what I was thinking."

#: 809R13
msgctxt "809R13"
msgid "Mercury poisoning is a horrible way to die."
msgstr "Mercury poisoning is a horrible way to die."

#: 809R14
msgctxt "809R14"
msgid "No, you're right. It may be impossible to walk across."
msgstr "No, you're right. It may be impossible to walk across."

#: 809R15
msgctxt "809R15"
msgid "I need some means of crossing that lake of mercury."
msgstr "I need some means of crossing that lake of mercury."

#: 809R16
msgctxt "809R16"
msgid "That wouldn't do me much good."
msgstr "That wouldn't do me much good."

#: 809R17
msgctxt "809R17"
msgid "I can't reach the bottom, but I've learned what I needed to know. I won't be waiting across the lake."
msgstr "I can't reach the bottom, but I've learned what I needed to know. I won't be waiting across the lake."

#: 809R18
msgctxt "809R18"
msgid "It would be too hard to balance on a single shield."
msgstr "It would be too hard to balance on a single shield."

#: 809R19
msgctxt "809R19"
msgid "I'm not completely sure, but whatever it is, it appears to be working."
msgstr "I'm not completely sure, but whatever it is, it appears to be working."

#: 809R32
msgctxt "809R32"
msgid "This is maddening. I can't believe I forgot to get a new pencil."
msgstr "This is maddening. I can't believe I forgot to get a new pencil."

#: 809R33
msgctxt "809R33"
msgid "Decorative urns line the walkway."
msgstr "Decorative urns line the walkway."

#: 809R34
msgctxt "809R34"
msgid "Majestic mountains rise above incredibly detailed cities and farms."
msgstr "Majestic mountains rise above incredibly detailed cities and farms."

#: 810R01
msgctxt "810R01"
msgid "Master Lu, you served the First Emperor well. You may not have found the secret to eternal life, but you created an incredible monument befitting a man who wanted all history to begin with him. I salute you, Master Lu."
msgstr "Master Lu, you served the First Emperor well. You may not have found the secret to eternal life, but you created an incredible monument befitting a man who wanted all history to begin with him. I salute you, Master Lu."

#: 810R02
msgctxt "810R02"
msgid "The final resting place of the first emperor of China, Jinxia Huangdi."
msgstr "The final resting place of the first emperor of China, Jinxia Huangdi."

#: 810R03
msgctxt "810R03"
msgid "Inside that magnificent sarcophagus rests the man who declared history would begin with him. The man who sent Master Lu on an incredible journey, combing the globe for the elusive elixir of life."
msgstr "Inside that magnificent sarcophagus rests the man who declared history would begin with him. The man who sent Master Lu on an incredible journey, combing the globe for the elusive elixir of life."

#: 810R04
msgctxt "810R04"
msgid "The First Emperor's Seal of Office."
msgstr "The First Emperor's Seal of Office."

#: 810R04A
msgctxt "810R04A"
msgid "At last!"
msgstr "At last!"

#: 810R05
msgctxt "810R05"
msgid "It looks like a drain. Why would there be a drain in front of the sarcophagus?"
msgstr "It looks like a drain. Why would there be a drain in front of the sarcophagus?"

#: 810R06
msgctxt "810R06"
msgid "Leave without the seal? After all this? Frippley, are you nuts?"
msgstr "Leave without the seal? After all this? Frippley, are you nuts?"

#: 810R07
msgctxt "810R07"
msgid "How much blood has been spilled by those who would use this? How much more will be spilled if it falls into the wrong hands?"
msgstr "How much blood has been spilled by those who would use this? How much more will be spilled if it falls into the wrong hands?"

#: 810R07A
msgctxt "810R07A"
msgid "Master Lu, I understand you wanted the world to be united in peace and harmony before the first Emperor's seal was found. I'm sorry that hasn't happened. Our world is just as troubled as it was in your day. But if I leave the seal here, it will be used in the name of power and conquest and destruction. And I know that you didn't want that."
msgstr "Master Lu, I understand you wanted the world to be united in peace and harmony before the first Emperor's seal was found. I'm sorry that hasn't happened. Our world is just as troubled as it was in your day. But if I leave the seal here, it will be used in the name of power and conquest and destruction. And I know that you didn't want that."

#: 810R08
msgctxt "810R08"
msgid "On the other hand, I could leave it here."
msgstr "On the other hand, I could leave it here."

#: 810R09
msgctxt "810R09"
msgid "I have a bad feeling about this."
msgstr "I have a bad feeling about this."

#: 810R17
msgctxt "810R17"
msgid "This is maddening. I can't believe I forgot to get a new pencil."
msgstr "This is maddening. I can't believe I forgot to get a new pencil."

#: 810R18
msgctxt "810R18"
msgid "Incredible! Master Lu's ingenious lighting system continues to illuminate even the farthest reaches of the tomb."
msgstr "Incredible! Master Lu's ingenious lighting system continues to illuminate even the farthest reaches of the tomb."

#: 811B01
msgctxt "811B01"
msgid "Keep perfectly still, Mr. Ripley. That goes for your charming companion as well."
msgstr "Keep perfectly still, Mr. Ripley. That goes for your charming companion as well."

#: 811B02
msgctxt "811B02"
msgid "Yes, believe it or not."
msgstr "Yes, believe it or not."

#: 811B03
msgctxt "811B03"
msgid "You did my work for me. I am in your debt."
msgstr "You did my work for me. I am in your debt."

#: 811B04
msgctxt "811B04"
msgid "We had a difference of opinion about the Emerald Seal. He was unwilling to put it into its proper use."
msgstr "We had a difference of opinion about the Emerald Seal. He was unwilling to put it into its proper use."

#: 811B05
msgctxt "811B05"
msgid "Hardly. I'm very sincere in my desire to rid the world of death, Fuhrer."
msgstr "Hardly. I'm very sincere in my desire to rid the world of death, Fuhrer."

#: 811B05A
msgctxt "811B05A"
msgid "He doesn't have the competitive spirit necessary to win."
msgstr "He doesn't have the competitive spirit necessary to win."

#: 811B06
msgctxt "811B06"
msgid "Think about it, Mr. Ripley. That seal belonged to a man born into a time not unlike ours, a time of turmoil and division."
msgstr "Think about it, Mr. Ripley. That seal belonged to a man born into a time not unlike ours, a time of turmoil and division."

#: 811B07
msgctxt "811B07"
msgid "A visionary. The old China is dead. The time is ripe for a new dawn in the East. Not a Nazi dawn, nor the rising sun of the Japanese."
msgstr "A visionary. The old China is dead. The time is ripe for a new dawn in the East. Not a Nazi dawn, nor the rising sun of the Japanese."

#: 811B08
msgctxt "811B08"
msgid "I'm going to miss you. I really will. It has been an interesting contest. It is unfortunate you won't be around to witness my triumph. Now, you can hand me the seal, one gentleman to another, or I can remove it from your lifeless fingers."
msgstr "I'm going to miss you. I really will. It has been an interesting contest. It is unfortunate you won't be around to witness my triumph. Now, you can hand me the seal, one gentleman to another, or I can remove it from your lifeless fingers."

#: 811B09
msgctxt "811B09"
msgid "I confess to you, I sometimes also cheat at tennis. My line calls."
msgstr "I confess to you, I sometimes also cheat at tennis. My line calls."

#: 811B09A
msgctxt "811B09A"
msgid "Whatever it takes to win."
msgstr "Whatever it takes to win."

#: 811B09B
msgctxt "811B09B"
msgid "We seem to be running out of time. I have no desire to be trapped inside a giant thermometer. The seal, Mr. Ripley, if you please."
msgstr "We seem to be running out of time. I have no desire to be trapped inside a giant thermometer. The seal, Mr. Ripley, if you please."

#: 811B10
msgctxt "811B10"
msgid "You fool! You could have broken it!"
msgstr "You fool! You could have broken it!"

#: 811M01
msgctxt "811M01"
msgid "Who is he, Robert?"
msgstr "Who is he, Robert?"

#: 811M02
msgctxt "811M02"
msgid "What good is the seal to you?"
msgstr "What good is the seal to you?"

#: 811R01
msgctxt "811R01"
msgid "Baron Von Seltzer."
msgstr "Baron Von Seltzer."

#: 811R02
msgctxt "811R02"
msgid "No wonder you let me search your house for the key. I played right into your hands, didn't I?"
msgstr "No wonder you let me search your house for the key. I played right into your hands, didn't I?"

#: 811R03
msgctxt "811R03"
msgid "Why did your father hide the key from you?"
msgstr "Why did your father hide the key from you?"

#: 811R04
msgctxt "811R04"
msgid "You're not one of those fascist fellows after all, are you?"
msgstr "You're not one of those fascist fellows after all, are you?"

#: 811R05
msgctxt "811R05"
msgid "So, if another man possessed it, an opportunist..."
msgstr "So, if another man possessed it, an opportunist..."

#: 811R06
msgctxt "811R06"
msgid "You'd rather it was the rising sun of the old barren."
msgstr "You'd rather it was the rising sun of the old barren."

#: 811R07
msgctxt "811R07"
msgid "Baron, you disappoint me. A sportsman like you, shooting an unarmed man and woman."
msgstr "Baron, you disappoint me. A sportsman like you, shooting an unarmed man and woman."

#: 811R08
msgctxt "811R08"
msgid "Gosh, I'm glad you're good at that!"
msgstr "Gosh, I'm glad you're good at that!"

#: 814R06
msgctxt "814R06"
msgid "The first in a row of seven soldiers wearing purple skirts."
msgstr "The first in a row of seven soldiers wearing purple skirts."

